title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix cake mix as directed.
Mix rhubarb and sugar; let stand for 10 minutes.
Pour over cake mix.
Pour 1 pint whipping cream over all.
Dust with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Combine fruit, sugar, cornstarch, salt and lemon juice.
Line iron skillet or pie pan with pastry.
Fill with berries.
Dot with butter.
Moisten pastry edge.
Put top crust on.
Cut upper crust in several places.
Bake at 425° for about 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake about 30 minutes more.

title: katrina's pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving 2 tablespoons juice.
Melt butter in 13 x 9 x 2 pan and stir in sugar.
Arrange pineapple on sugar. Sprinkle with pineapple juice and 3/4 of the cereal.
Prepare cake mix, stirring remaining cereal in mix.
Pour cake into pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Let cool 5 minutes.	Turn over 1 minute before removing pan.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat. Add onion and saute until translucent.
Add broccoli and continue cooking for 5 minutes or bright green. Add soup and Cheez Whiz, stirring until cheese melts. Stir broccoli mixture into the rice.
Fold in the mushrooms and water chestnuts.
Transfer the mixture to a buttered 2-quart casserole. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: deep dish peach pie
directions: Place peaches in Pam-sprayed baking dish.
Combine sugar, cinnamon, flour and salt.
Sprinkle mixture over peaches. Sprinkle on lemon juice and dot with butter.
Cover filling with prepared pie pastry, rolled thin.
Bake at 400° about 35 minutes or until peaches are tender.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: mincemeat cookies
directions: Soften butter and cream with sugar.
In roaster pan mix all dry ingredients.
Add butter and sugar; knead.
Add mincemeat and drained raisins.
Mix and knead.
Looks dry but roll on floured board no less than 1/4 inch thick.
Bake in 400° oven for 12 minutes.
Do not brown tops.

title: super nacho
directions: In a large skillet, cook meat until browned; drain.
Add seasoning mix and water. Bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until meat is cooked and flavors have blended. Set aside.
Spread bean dip to cover bottom of a 12 to 14-inch pizza pan.
Sprinkle with cheeses. Top with the meat mixture, then sprinkle with chilies.
Broil 5 to 7 minutes or until cheese is bubbly and brown.
Around edge of pan, arrange a border of lettuce, then tomatoes, then tortilla chips.
Place mound of guacamole topped with sour cream in center.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Cook zucchini and onions in pan with small amount of water until tender.
Drain.
Combine soup and sour cream.
Stir in grated carrots.
Fold in drained zucchini and onion.
Combine melted butter and stuffing mix.
Spread half in bottom of casserole.
Spoon zucchini mixture over.
Sprinkle rest of mix over zucchini.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: oh henry! bars
directions: Bring sugar and syrup to a boil.
Stir in peanut butter.
Stir in cereal.
Put mixture in 9 x 13-inch pan (buttered).
Don't press too firmly or it will be too hard.
Melt chips and spread on top. Can be made and leave off chocolate chips, if desired.

title: bread pudding
directions: Pour into greased dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: hawaiian chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken with
salt
and
pepper.
Melt butter. Brown chicken on both
sides.
Use medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook, turning chicken often until liquid is gone and chicken looks glazed but not dry.

title: hamburg noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add tomato juice and cheese.
Stir over low heat until cheese melts.
Add mushrooms.
Pour over noodles. Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: zucchini boats
directions: Wash and cut medium size potatoes in lengthwise wedges.
Brush cut sides with beaten egg whites.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and oregano.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: never-fail divinity
directions: Cook the sugar, corn syrup and water in a heavy saucepan. Cook until syrup reaches a firm ball stage.
Beat egg whites with salt until stiff, moist peaks form.
Add half the syrup gradually to egg whites, beating constantly.
Return remaining syrup to stove to boil again, then gradually beat into egg whites and continue beating until dry.
Add vanilla and nuts, beating in by hand.
Drop by spoonful on wax paper.
Cool.
For Christmas, add red and green food coloring.

title: rhubarb jam
directions: Boil hard 6 to 7 minutes. Take off stove. Add Jell-O and stir well. Put in jars and store in the refrigerator.

title: microwave pepperoni melt
directions: Slice roll in half.
Layer bottom with Provolone, pepperoni, mushrooms or onions, pickle, broccoli, Mozzarella cheese and Parmesan cheese.
Microwave on High for 1 minute.
Place top of roll on sandwich and microwave 30 seconds more.
Makes 1 sandwich.

title: swiss cheese bread
directions: Slice bread diagonally. Place Swiss cheese in every slice. Put bread on foil on cookie sheet.
Mix the remaining ingredients with the melted butter.
Pour over bread.
Seal foil. Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: spaghetti omelet
directions: Cook spaghetti; place in skillet with small amount of butter. Beat eggs; add cheese and mushrooms.
Add to spaghetti in skillet until eggs are done.

title: lynn's pepper steak
directions: Brown steak in butter. Add garlic, onions and pepper. Cook approximately 3 minutes. Add tomatoes and mushrooms.
Blend together the cornstarch, water, soy sauce, sugar and salt.
Add blended ingredients.
Simmer until steak is tender or put ingredients in a roaster pan and bake 1/2 hour at 350°.
Serve over rice.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut. Spread evenly over bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix.
Pour mixture over nuts and coconut.
In medium bowl, blend together sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crock-pot stroganoff
directions: Put all in container and put in oven or put in slow cooker and cook all day.
If in oven, cook all day at 250°.
Serve over noodles, rice or potatoes.
Serves 4 people.

title: basic pizza dough
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Stir flour, sugar and salt in a bowl.
Add yeast and water mixture.
Stir again and add oil.
Mix again until dough forms a ball. Place on a floured board and knead for 5 minutes.
Place dough in a greased bowl, cover and let rise in a warm place.

title: mexican salad dressing
directions: Gradually add oil to other ingredients and keep beating until oil doesn't separate.
Add onion last, if desired.

title: buster bars
directions: Combine cookies and butter; pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Spoon ice cream over crumbs.
Sprinkle with peanuts.
Place in freezer.

title: half moon pie crust
directions: Pinch off and roll in small balls.
Roll out and put your fruit in and close edges.
Fry in skillet.

title: mrs. totts salad
directions: Place head lettuce on bottom of large bowl.
Place scallions as next layer, stalks celery as next layer.
Mix mayonnaise with garlic powder, sugar, lemon juice, salt and
pepper.
Spread on top of layers and sprinkle with bacon bits on top.

title: spicy beef pocket sandwiches
directions: Over medium heat, cook beef until browned.
Add onion, cook until limp.
Drain and discard fat.
Mix in chili sauce, water and seasonings.
Cook, uncovered, stirring often, for 5 minutes.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms.
Cut up stems in little pieces and cook in butter.
Mix Stove Top stuffing with sauteed mushrooms.
Stuff mushrooms.
Dip mushrooms into butter so they won't shrink.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Saute onion in margarine.
In large soup pot, put 6 cups water and 6 chicken bouillon cubes.
Bring to a boil; add onion and broccoli.
Bring back to boil and add Velveeta and milk.
Bring down to simmer and add noodles that have been cooked, drained and rinsed.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Makes a lot of soup.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Mix oil and garlic powder together in pan.
Add potatoes. Turn to coat.
Bake in 400° oven for 1/2 hour or until potatoes are brown.
Makes 1 serving.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: Cook cabbage in boiling, salted water for 5 minutes; drain. Saute onion in oil.
Add rice and garlic, ketchup, salt and pepper. Cook 2 to 3 minutes on medium, stirring.
Add beef and cook 3 to 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add consomme.
Separate cabbage leaves.
Using a slotted tablespoon, place 1 rounded tablespoon of meat on each leaf.
Roll and secure with toothpick.
Place rolls in Dutch oven.
Pour on tomato juice.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: burrito roll-ups
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients, mixing well.
Spread 1 heaping tablespoonful of cream cheese mixture on each tortilla. Tightly roll tortillas and wrap in wax paper.
Chill 8 hours.
Slice each tortilla into 1-inch slices and serve with salsa.
Yields 7 dozen servings.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss together broccoli, bacon, raisins and onion.
Blend together Miracle Whip, sugar and vinegar.
Mix all together.
Let stand overnight.

title: cherry dream
directions: Melt margarine and add to cracker crumbs mixed with sugar. Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish (lightly greased). Bake at 325° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: marshmallow dessert
directions: Blend cream cheese and pineapple (juice too) until smooth. Fold in marshmallows and Cool Whip.
Put in refrigerator.
Cut into squares.

title: fantasy cookies
directions: of this I'm very glad,

title: crunchy chicken nuggets
directions: In a small bowl, place milk and egg.
Mix together with fork by beating slightly.
On a piece of wax paper, place potato chip crumbs and mix with thyme and pepper.
Line shallow baking pan with foil and spray with vegetable cooking spray.
Dip each nugget of chicken in egg-milk mixture, then roll in seasoned chip crumbs. Arrange in a single layer on foil lined baking pan.
Repeat until all nuggets are arranged in pan.
Let sit 15 minutes.
Drizzle melted margarine over nuggets and place in a 425° oven for about 30 minutes or until nuggets are brown and crisp and fork can be inserted in chicken with ease.
Makes 6 servings.

title: broccoli-mushroom spaghetti
directions: Cook broccoli as directed on package; drain.
Stir in mushrooms, margarine, salt and pepper.
Heat over low heat, stirring occasionally until mushrooms are hot, about 5 minutes. Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain.
Toss spaghetti, broccoli mixture, Parmesan cheese and lemon juice.

title: pride of iowa oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Use greased cookie sheets.
With electric mixer, beat sugars and butter together until light and fluffy.
Beat in eggs and vanilla.
Sift together flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda onto waxed paper.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, nuts and coconut.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto prepared pan.
Space about 1-inch apart.
Bake about 8 minutes.
Store cookies in airtight container with waxed paper between layers.

title: potluck potatoes
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in 13 x 7 x 9-inch baking dish, greased with butter.
Top with cornflake crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Prepare noodles in chicken broth according to package.
Saute first 5 ingredients, cooking until tender.
Add layers of chicken, noodles and vegetables.
Add broth if it looks dry.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Add cheese on top.
Brown about 10 minutes. Serves 10 to 12 people.

title: florida fried shrimp
directions: Peel and clean veins of shrimp.
Mix egg and flour.
Dip shrimp in flour and then egg mixture.
Then roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in olive oil or vegetable oil until golden brown, on both sides.
Serves 3.

title: crock-pot roast with cranberry gravy
directions: Brown brisket in hot oil on all sides.
Remove to crock-pot. Brown onions in the meat pan to get flavor.
Add more oil, if needed, and scrape up flavorings.
Pour onions over roast in crock-pot.
Add tomato sauce to meat pan to get loose all the flavorings.
Mix in cranberry sauce, also.
Dump liquid over roast and onions.
Simmer 3 to 6 hours in crock-pot on low or until meat is tender.
Can be cooled and refrigerated up to 2 days.
Reheat, covered, over medium-low heat, about 30 minutes.
Serve meat sliced with gravy to pass.

title: caramel bars
directions: Mix cake, butter and 1/3 cup milk (dry and thick).
Pat 1/2 mix into pan (9 x 13-inch); bake for 6 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix chicken, both soups, Ro-Tel, broth and chopped onion in mixing bowl.
In a casserole dish, put layer of Doritos, the layer of chicken mixture and cheese.
Alternate mixture until both are used.
Top with remainder of cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hot chili dip
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.
Serve immediately with taco or tortilla chips as dippers.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries.
Mix cake mix.
Use strawberry juice instead of water in cake mix.
Add 5 drops of red food coloring to cake mix.
Follow rest of cake box directions to bake cake.
Let cake cool.
Leave cake in pan.
Pour strawberries on top of cake. Mix yogurt and Cool Whip.
Spread over strawberries.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: chicken spectacular
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
It calls for 2 1/3 cups of water and I used 1 1/2 cups of my chicken broth and 1 cup of water.
Mix all ingredients together (can use your hands for easy mixing).
Cook at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.
Spray pan before baking.
Makes a big batch.

title: rice and broccoli
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine, then add 1/2 cup of chopped onions and saute.
Add 1 can of cream of mushroom soup, 1/4 pound of Velveeta cheese and a 10 ounce package of frozen chopped broccoli, thawed.
Heat ingredients and when cheese has melted, add cooked rice.
Mix well and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: french toast
directions: Add milk and egg in a mixing bowl.
Add grease to frypan and put on medium.
Add bread to the mixture and dip each side of bread for a couple seconds.
Add bread to pan.
Done when golden brown on both sides.

title: marinated flank steak
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients. Place in a large Ziploc bag. Add flank steak and marinate for 12 hours. Remove steak from marinade and place on hot grill. Cook until desired doneness. Slice very thin. Place on a bed of wild rice with grilled vegetables to the side. Enjoy! Serves 4.

title: spiced zucchini bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and set aside.
Beat eggs lightly in a large mixing bowl; add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Beat until creamy.
Stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Add dry ingredients, stirring only until dry ingredients are moistened. Pour into 2 well-greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Cool for 10 minutes and turn out on rack to cool.

title: pineapple cheese ball
directions: Beat cheese with a fork until smooth.
Gradually stir in pineapple, 1 cup of nuts, green pepper, onion and salt.
Form into a ball and roll in remaining nuts.
Wrap in plastic wrap and chill. May garnish with pineapple rings, maraschino cherries and parsley.

title: ranch dip
directions: Place ingredients in mixing bowl. Stir until blended and smooth.
Pour into container and refrigerate 1 hour to blend flavors. Can be stored for several weeks.
Use on salad greens or as a dip for raw vegetables (broccoli, carrots, squash, celery, tomato or seasonal vegetables).
Yields 2 cups.

title: texas millionaires
directions: Mix sugars, Karo, butter and 1 cup Pet milk.
Cook until hard boil, then pour in 2nd cup of milk.
Don't let it stop boiling. Cook until it forms a soft ball in cold water.
Mix in pecans and vanilla.
Spoon out on buttered wax paper.
Chill overnight or until firm.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix flour with baking soda.
Combine oleo, sugars, vanilla and pudding; mix in large bowl.
Beat until smooth and creamy.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour mixture, stir in chocolate chips.
Batter will be stiff.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.
Use ungreased cookie sheet.
These are really good.

title: tortellini salad
directions: Chill at least a couple of hours.
Add tomatoes and Parmesan just before serving.

title: sue pierce's sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Shape into small balls.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: rich pecan pie
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine syrup, margarine and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to a boil gently for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly. Mix the eggs, vanilla and salt.
Gradually stir in cool syrup mixture.
Pour over chocolate chips in pie plate crust.
Arrange pecan halves on top of pie.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes until knife comes clean.
Cool.

title: peach muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spray twelve 2 1/2-inch muffin pan cups with nonstick vegetable cooking spray.

title: ranch chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 3 ingredients; set aside.
Separately combine the last 3 ingredients; mix well.
Add to chicken mixture and toss well to coat.
Chill.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: classic chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and cover.
Chill for several hours before serving.

title: wild rice casserole
directions: Cook rice according to directions.
Cook sausage and drain. Cook onion and celery until soft.
Add rest of the ingredients, except pecans.
Pour mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except chocolate chips, for 2 minutes or until well blended.
Fold in chocolate chips.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 325° for 60 to 65 minutes or until tests done.
Cool in pan for 15 minutes.
Flip on cake plate and dust with powdered sugar.

title: chocolate squares
directions: In medium saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips and peanut butter until smooth.
Remove from heat.
Add pecans, raisins and mini marshmallows.
Mix until well blended.
Pour into buttered 8 x 8-inch pan.
Chill 2 hours before serving.
Enjoy!

title: pork chop jambalaya
directions: Season and brown pork chops in a little cooking oil.
Drain excess grease after pork chops are browned.
Add Kitchen Bouquet, green onions and a little water.
Boil around 10 to 15 minutes (hard boil), then add your rice, water and salt (stir).
Put on low heat and cover.
Cook around 30 minutes or until rice is done. Serves 4 to 5 people.

title: cheesy potato bake
directions: Mix soup, cheese, onions and sour cream in a bowl.
Put potatoes in bottom of pan and pour the mixture over top of the potatoes; put dry stuffing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: scalloped potatoes mexicali
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Boil until tender.
Butter a large casserole dish.
Preheat oven then 325° to 350°.
Make a layer of potatoes, then onion, green pepper, cheese and part of the cream of mushroom soup, then another layer of potatoes, jalapeno pepper, cheese and mushroom soup.
Keep alternating layers until ingredients are gone.
Bake for about 25 to 30 minutes or until part of liquid is absorbed and cheese begins to look a little brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix and bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.

title: puffs
directions: Cream margarine and cheese with electric mixer.
Add flour; mix well.
Stir in sausage until well blended.
Chill.
Remove 1 tablespoon mixture at a time and roll into a ball.

title: lemonade punch for fifty
directions: Mix lemonade by directions on can.
Add pineapple juice and sugar.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cut bread into small pieces and place in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cook sausage and drain.
Spoon over bread.
Sprinkle cheese on sausage.
Beat eggs with milk.
Pour over cheese.
Soak overnight, covered, in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, on 350° until brown for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Press sugar cookie dough into a pizza or cookie pan. Bake at 400° for 10 to 15 minutes. Cool crust completely.

title: black bottoms
directions: Mix together cream cheese, egg, 1/3 cup sugar and 1/8 teaspoon of salt.
Add chocolate chips.

title: chicken cheese puff
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Salt.
Mix butter, flour, half and half, milk and eggs while cooking.
In a casserole dish, layer cubed chicken and 5 slices American cheese; repeat.
Then pour liquid mixture over top.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: mexican turkey cutlets with fresh salsa
directions: Coarsely chop green onions and red pepper.
Combine in small bowl with chilies and liquid, 3 tablespoons oil and pepper sauce. Cover and refrigerate.
In a bowl, beat egg with 1 tablespoon oil, garlic and spices.
Place chips on waxed paper.
Dip cutlets into egg mixture, then chips.
Brown cutlets in 2 tablespoons hot oil 3 to 4 minutes on each side.
Serve with salsa.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Combine sugar, cocoa, butter and milk in 6 to 8 quart boiler. Bring to boil over LOW heat.
Boil about 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; add vanilla, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Drop by teaspoon full on waxed paper.
Work fast.

title: chicken-rice casserole
directions: Wash rice and mix with all ingredients except breast halves. Pour in casserole.
Add chicken and sprinkle with a little of reserved onion soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: lemon cheese cake
directions: Cream butter; add sugar gradually.
Sift together flour and baking powder.
Add to butter, alternately with milk and flavoring.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: nutty buddy dessert bars
directions: Crush Oreos. Add melted margarine to crushed cookies.
Mix slightly to moisten.
Press into 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Cut ice cream into slices and place on top of cookie mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Drizzle chocolate syrup onto Cool Whip.
Swirl with knife.
Top with crushed pecans or roasted peanuts.
Freeze. When ready to serve, cut into bars and enjoy.

title: hot water cocoa cake
directions: Mix together eggs, sugar, cocoa, Nucoa, flour and baking powder.
Mix well.

title: braciole(italian beef rolls)
directions: Place mixture of hard-boiled eggs, garlic salt, parsley, Parmesan cheese, salt, pepper and sage on 4 slices of meat. Cover each slice with 4 remaining pieces of meat and toothpick around the edges.
Saute in 3 tablespoons olive oil with sliced onion until lightly brown.
Dissolve bouillon cube in 1 cup water and add to meat, along with salt and pepper.
Cover and cook until tender, about 45 minutes.
Saute mushrooms in butter; add to meat rolls.
Five minutes before serving, add 1/4 cup Marsala wine. Remove toothpicks and serve.

title: cream cheese fudge
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk, beating until smooth. Gradually beat in sugar. Blend in chocolate and vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Press into a buttered 8 x 4-inch or 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Chill until firm, about 1 hour.
Cut into squares.
Makes 1 pound or about 20 pieces.

title: apricot cheese delight salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Add apricot juice.
Fold in apricots, pineapple and marshmallows.
Chill until firm.
Add topping.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Add beaten egg and mix.
Add apples and mix until moisture from apples makes a cake-like batter.
Pour into well greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: cream cheese icing
directions: Cream margarine and cheese.
Add sugar and vanilla. Beat until creamy and smooth.

title: deviled ham balls
directions: Combine deviled ham, onion and cream cheese in bowl. Mix well. Shape into small balls.
Roll in pecans.
Chill.
Place on serving plate.
Place toothpicks in each one.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: m&m cookies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients (it is very sticky and stiff to mix). Drop on cookie sheet and place M&M's on top of each cookie.
Bake at 375° until done.

title: easy breakfast
directions: You will need a bowl.
Mix cereal and milk into bowl. Strawberries or bananas are optional.
Eat hearty.

title: three week cole slaw
directions: Use a large bowl.
Makes big batch.
Combine cabbage, peppers, onion, carrots and sugar.
Mix well.
Mix together the oil, vinegar, celery seed and salt.
Bring to a hard boil.
Pour over cabbage mixture and stir very well.
Store in refrigerator in airtight container.
Let stand at least 3 days.
Flavor improves as it stands.
Will keep at least a month.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar and butter; beat in eggs.
Mash bananas, flour, dry ingredients and sour cream.
Pour into 1 greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: peppered london broil
directions: Brush steak with olive oil. Combine seasonings and rub on both sides of steak. Chill until ready to grill. Cook over medium-hot coals until desired doneness is achieved. Slice the steak in thin strips and serve with the juice from the meat.

title: zucchini pineapple cookies
directions: Mix together sugar, shortening, zucchini, pineapple and egg. Add flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Mix well.
Add vanilla, raisins, dates and nuts.
Mix. Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fudge waffles
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt and cocoa.
Set aside.
Combine melted butter, sugar and large eggs.
Add dry ingredients to butter; mix alternating with buttermilk.
Add vanilla, nuts and chocolate morsels.
Bake in waffle iron.
Serve with ice cream or whipped topping.

title: easy peanut butter blossoms(makes 5 dozen)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, beat condensed milk, peanut butter, egg and vanilla until smooth.
Add biscuit mix; mix well.
Chill at least 1 hour.

title: raspberry puddin cake
directions: To
this add enough flour to make soft batter.
Fold in 1 quart berries or cherries that have been drained well.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Bake on cookie sheet 15 to 20 minutes in preheated 350° oven.
Serve warm. These may be frozen on a cookie sheet and then placed in plastic bags.

title: shrimp nadine
directions: In a large frying pan, saute onion and pepper in 2 teaspoons butter. Add soup, sour cream and shrimp.
Stir until well blended. Serve over white rice.

title: our surprise dessert
directions: Put all ingredients in a
bowl and mix until wet.
Pour into a buttered baking dish. Sprinkle with 1/2 cup brown sugar and nuts, if you wish. Bake at
350°	for
minutes
in 9 x 13-inch pan. Serve warm with cream or ice cream.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in blender and blend until smooth.
Taste for seasoning and add more garlic, onion salt or sauce, if desired.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Melt butter in a skillet over medium heat; add sugar and pepper.
Stir continuously until smooth. Add pecans; stir until pecans are coated. Remove immediately from heat and let cool on wax paper.

title: neapolitan casserole
directions: Saute ground beef, onion, green pepper, garlic, basil, fennel seed and red pepper, stirring frequently until meat is browned and vegetables are tender (about 20 minutes).
Drain off fat.

title: snickerdoodles cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together thoroughly.
Sift together flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt and stir in.
Chill dough. Roll into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and cinnamon.
Place about 2 inches apart on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until lightly browned but still soft.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.
Makes 5 dozen 2-inch cookies.

title: bean chowder
directions: Cover beans with water; stir in soda and soak overnight. Drain and wash beans thoroughly to remove soda; add 1 1/2 cups water, bacon fat and salt.
Cover and cook beans 1 1/2 to 2 hours until tender.
Brown ground beef; add onion and cook until onion is transparent.
Add to beans.
Blend tomatoes in blender until of smooth consistency and add to beans.
Add ketchup and chili seasoning.
Cover.
Bring to a boil on medium high heat; simmer 45 minutes.
Serve piping hot.

title: bishops chocolate pie
directions: Whip together pudding, milk and ice cream. Place in graham cracker crust. Shave
candy bar on top. Put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Cook 10 minutes over low heat. Add garlic, broccoli, soup and Cheez Whiz.
Add to rice.
Mix. Sprinkle with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: jag
directions: Put butter in saucepan with onion, linguica, soy sauce and garlic salt.
Let simmer for 15 minutes.
Add rice.
Mix together. Cover pot and let cook on medium-low heat for about 1/2 hour.
Turn heat to low and cook until done.

title: congo bars
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar; let cool.
Mix rest of ingredients and add to above.
Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: gooey bars
directions: Mix together cake mix, egg, margarine and vanilla.
Press into large 10 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over the mixture (optional).
Cream together the cream cheese, confectioners sugar and eggs.
Put on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.
Try with other cake mixes.

title: eat your guts out potato
directions: Cook potato in oven or microwave.
Split the baked potato in half.
Place on plate and refrigerate until cool.

title: jefferson davis pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Mix sugars and flour together. Add softened butter, 1 cup of the cream, eggs, nutmeg and vanilla until well blended. Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, reduce heat to 350° and cook 45 to 50 minutes or until set.
Take the rest of the cream and beat according to directions on carton. Add 1 tablespoon sugar and 1 tablespoon vanilla. Spread on top.

title: meat ball bitochki
directions: Mix well, meat, bread, salt, seed, pepper, onion and 2 tablespoons sour cream.
Form into balls; roll in bread crumbs.

title: caesar salad
directions: Add garlic to oil; let stand overnight.
Discard garlic.
Place romaine in large salad bowl.
Sprinkle with salt, pepper and Worcestershire.
Coddle egg for 1 1/2 minutes; break into middle of salad.
Pour lemon juice and wine vinegar over egg.
Toss lightly to mix well.
Add remaining ingredients, tossing after each addition.
Adjust servings if necessary.
Serve immediately.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick apple butter
directions: Cook apples; put through colander until smooth.
Measure 14 cups applesauce in kettle.
Add sugar, jello and cinnamon candy. Bring to full boil and cook 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Put into hot jars and seal with hot lids.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, rice and seasonings together and form into meat balls.
Mix soups together and mix with meat balls.
Bake 1 hour at 350° or until soups are thick and brown.

title: sugar free apple pecan muffins
directions: Combine sugar, flour, baking powder, cinnamon and lemon zest in mixing bowls.
Beat eggs with milk in separate bowl.
Combine liquid with dry ingredients only enough to moisten well, then fold in apples and pecans.
Spoon into 12 greased muffin cups and bake in 400° oven for 18 to 20 minutes.
(Note:
Approved for diabetics.)

title: chocolate pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift flour, sugar and cocoa; add butter to dry ingredients, eggs and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake for 30 minutes or until crusted over.

title: mother's cherry cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in eggs 1 at a time.
Add flour and baking powder.
Coat raisins and cherries in additional flour and mix in batter by hand.
Line loaf pan with waxed paper; pour batter in pan.
Place in a cold oven; set at 350° and bake 1 1/2 hours.

title: nacho dip
directions: Place cream cheese in 9-inch round serving dish and place into microwave on Low; melt for one minute.
Spread cream cheese over bottom of dish.
Spread salsa sauce over the cream cheese, then sprinkle the cheese over salsa.
Then cover with Saran Wrap.
Place in microwave for 5 minutes on Medium-high or until cheese melts. Take out of microwave and let stand for one minute.

title: banana split cake
directions: Bake cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch or 11 x 14-inch pan.
Cream together butter, powdered sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat well and spread on cake.
Slice bananas; dip in pineapple juice and layer on cream filling on cake.
Spread with well drained pineapple, then spread Cool Whip over pineapple.
Sprinkle with chopped maraschino cherries and chopped nuts.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly cream the shortening and sugar; add eggs and molasses.
Beat well.
Sift dry ingredients. Add to creamed mixture alternately with coffee and cold water. Drop from teaspoon onto greased cookie sheet.
Bake 15 minutes. Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: ham and cheese sandwich
directions: Put mayonnaise on the bread and the mustard, then cheese, ham, salad and tomato.
Put the other piece of bread on.

title: classic waldorf salad
directions: In medium bowl, combine mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice and salt.
Add apples and celery.
Toss to coat well.
Cover.
Chill. Just before serving, sprinkle with walnuts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Place apples and undiluted, thawed apple juice in a large pan. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for 5 minutes. Dissolve the cornstarch in a small amount of water.
Stir this into the apples.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, for about 10 minutes or until the apples begin to soften and mixture thickens.
Add cinnamon.
Place in an unbaked pie shell; dot with margarine.
Cover with top crust.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Boil water, 2 sticks oleo and 4 tablespoons of cocoa; beat in 2 cups of sugar, flour and eggs.
Add sour cream.
Pour into greased 10 x 15-inch cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Ice when cooled.

title: barbecued meat loaf
directions: Combine beef, crumbs, onion, egg, salt and pepper with 1/2 can tomato sauce; mix.
Shape into a loaf; place in a baking pan. Combine remaining ingredients; pour over loaf in pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.
Baste several times while baking.

title: pineapple pie
directions: Mix milk and lemon juice.
Add all other ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: pineapple-cheese-marshmallow salad
directions: Drain and save juice from pineapple tidbits.
Cube cheese; mix with marshmallows.

title: library soup(serves 5)
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Drain off fat.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook slowly for 1 1/2 hours.
If desired, add any other vegetable from refrigerator like chopped celery, a carrot or shredded cabbage.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook, cool and bone chicken.
Combine the first 4 ingredients, including liquid of the mushrooms, in your casserole dish.
Melt margarine; combine with chicken broth and stuffing.
Spread over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes in an 11 x 13-inch pan. Serves 6 to 8.

title: diet oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream oil and sugars; add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add remaining ingredients; chill. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: creamy saucy chicken(soo easy and soo good!)
directions: Skin and defat your favorite meaty pieces of chicken.
Arrange in an oblong baking dish.
Pour the soup plus a can of water over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° until tender.
Remove foil to brown.

title: cranberry-apple crisp
directions: Spread apples in a buttered pan.
Spread cranberries over apples.
Mix other ingredients until crumbly.
Sprinkle over the cranberries.
Bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: buffalo chips
directions: Dip with ice cream scoop.
Bake 15 minutes on cookie sheet with foil shiny side up at 350°.

title: lime jello salad
directions: *I drain the can of crushed pineapple and finish the cup with orange juice.

title: blue cheese dressing
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender; cover and process on medium speed until smooth, about 1 minute.
Cover and refrigerate. Yield: 3 cups.

title: millionaire candy
directions: Melt caramel candy with milk.
Add pecans.
Roll into bite-size balls.
Melt chocolate chips and paraffin.
Dip balls in melted chocolate.
Place on wax paper to cool.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Preheat the oven to 350 degrees.

title: five minute fudge
directions: Combine butter, Carnation, sugar and salt in saucepan over medium heat.
Bring to a boil.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes; stir constantly.
(Start timing when mixture starts to "bubble" around edges of pan.)
Remove from heat.
Stir in marshmallows, chocolate, vanilla and nuts.
Stir vigorously for 1 minute (until marshmallows melt and blend).
Pour into an 8 or 9-inch square buttered pan.
Cool.
Cut in squares.
Makes 2 pounds.

title: blaukraut(german)
directions: Remove	 cabbage
core.
Shred	cabbage
finely.
Saute onion in Crisco; add cabbage, apples, salt, vinegar and sugar. Add water or	beef broth.
Stir well.
Cover; cook over medium heat.	Add more liquid, broth or water, to keep from sticking. Cook until tender (1 to 1 1/2 hours).

title: pecan bars
directions: Blend all dry ingredients together.
Then blend in margarine. Add eggs and vanilla last.
Mixture will be very stiff.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.

title: old timey cocoa fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients over medium heat and bring to a boil. Cook until soft ball stage. Remove from heat and add the butter, vanilla and nuts. Stir until it loses its gloss.
Pour into buttered platter.
Let cool before cutting.
This is
a real dark chocolate candy.

title: baked stuffed shrimp
directions: Peel and devein shrimp; butterfly.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Mix rest of ingredients together and place over shrimp. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Place under broiler for 2 minutes or until browned.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Pour all the ingredients into a bowl and mix until fluffy (about 3 minutes). Grease Bundt pan. Preheat oven 30 minutes before baking. Bake for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stew
directions: Place meat in a Dutch oven and sprinkle dry onion soup over meat.
Barely cover with water and add garlic and bay leaves. Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer until meat is tender, about 2 hours.
Check often and add water if necessary. Meat should always be covered.
When meat is tender, remove it from the pot.
Add potatoes, carrots and onions to the pot and cook, covered, for 10 minutes.
Add cabbage wedges and mushrooms; cook, covered, 15 to 20 minutes more.
Cut meat into 1-inch cubes and add to pot; reheat.
Drain liquid from meat and vegetables and reserve; remove bay leaves.
Make a gravy by adding thickening to liquid.
Serves 8.

title: new year's day coleslaw
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
(Coleslaw always accompanies black-eyed peas on New Year's Day!)

title: calypso dip
directions: Mix all together until creamy.
Good with chips or veggies.

title: chicken strata
directions: Butter 2 slices of bread and cut into cubes for topping; set aside.
Cut remaining bread into cubes.
Place bread cubes in bottom of greased baking dish.
Combine chicken, vegetables, mayo and seasoning.
Spoon over bread cubes.
Combine eggs and milk and beat.
Pour over ingredients in casserole.
Cover and chill 1 hour or overnight.
Spoon soup from can over top.
Sprinkle topping cubes on top.
Bake at 325° for 50 minutes.
Sprinkle cheese over top the last few minutes.

title: banana walnut cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat with electric mixer. Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: big softies
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand for 10 minutes. Drain raisins, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices into a bowl.
Add shortening, sugar, eggs and reserved liquid.
Beat until smooth, about 2 minutes.
Stir in raisins and oats.
Chill dough.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake in preheated moderate oven (350°) about 15 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen large cookies.

title: rice krispie treat
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in skillet and bring to a boil. Remove and add Rice Krispies.
Spoon on wax paper.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix sugar, shortening, egg, honey and lemon extract.
Stir remaining ingredients.
Roll and cut.
Bake 7 minutes or until golden brown.

title: bread sticks
directions: Roll bread sticks in the chopped herbs; brush with beaten egg and bake according to directions on package.
Dried and/or fresh herbs are suitable for this recipe.

title: marzette
directions: Brown ground chuck and chopped onions; drain. Add olives, mushrooms, tomato juice and egg noodles. Cook in skillet on low heat for approximately 20 to 25 minutes or until noodles are tender and most of the juice is absorbed. Cover with Mozzarella cheese and let stand until melted. Serve with garlic bread and salad.

title: squaw corn
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into greased casserole.
Bake 30 minutes at 400°.

title: beef liver ole
directions: Dredge beef liver in 3 tablespoons flour.
Saute the onion slices in hot shortening for 2 minutes. Add liver and brown gently.
Remove onion and liver to a warm plate.
Add remaining flour to drippings. Stir in all other ingredients except green onions until the sauce is thick and smooth.
Return liver and onion to pot and simmer for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with green onion garnish.
Serves 4 people.

title: "mom's" golden punch
directions: Mix all together, except the ginger ale.
Put into a punch bowl.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale to taste.

title: cheese ball(small)
directions: Have everything at room temperature.
Grate the Cheddar cheese and add chopped olives and softened cream cheese.
Add onion or garlic salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Using wax paper, roll into a ball.
Roll in nuts or chipped beef.
Serve with crackers. Very quick and tasty!

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Heat broth to boiling.
Add chicken and pasta or rice.
Heat. Yields 6 to 8 pints (16 servings).

title: fresh blueberry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Blend 1/2 cup sugar and the cornstarch in medium saucepan.
Stir in blueberries and lemon juice.
Cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens and boils.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Pour into 2-quart casserole; place in oven while preparing biscuit topping.
Measure flour, tablespoon sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Add shortening and milk.
Cut through shortening six times.
Mix until dough forms ball.
Drop dough by spoonfuls into hot fruit.
Bake uncovered 25 to 30 minutes or until biscuit topping is golden brown.
Serve warm. Makes 6 servings.

title: strawberry nutrition milkshake
directions: Combine ingredients in blender except cinnamon.
Blend until frothy.
Pour into tall glasses.
Dash with cinnamon.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar, beat thoroughly.
Add flour and baking powder; beat until smooth.
Heat milk and butter, but do not boil. Add to mixture, a little at a time, beating all the time.
Flavor with vanilla or lemon.
Bake in layers or a mold at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Check when smell.
Makes 3 layer cake.

title: united states-southwest chili
directions: In a large skillet, brown beef with onion, green pepper and garlic.
Pour off fat.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dream cheesecake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.

title: pralines
directions: Combine sugar, buttermilk, soda and Karo syrup.
Cook until soft ball (about 240°).
Add pecans, margarine and vanilla. Remove from heat.
Beat until creamy and drop on buttered cookie sheets.

title: harvest time apple squares
directions: Combine flour, brown and white sugars and cinnamon.
Cut in margarine until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Reserve 1/2 crumb mixture.
Combine cream cheese and milk until well blended. Stir in walnuts, egg and vanilla.
Press into a greased pan.
Pour over crust.
Top with apples and sprinkle with reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian baked beans and franks
directions: Drain pineapple.
Mix all ingredients together.
Cook in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate walnut zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until lemon colored.
Beat in sugar and oil.
Add chocolate, vanilla and zucchini.
Sift flour with salt, cinnamon, baking powder and soda.
Add nuts and mix well.
Grease and flour 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: pineapple pound cake
directions: Combine cake mix, yogurt and eggs.
Blend at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at medium speed.
Fold in fruit and nuts.
Pour batter into greased, floured Bundt pan or 10-inch tube pan.

title: sweet hot pork medallions
directions: Remove excess fat from pork tenderloin; slice into 1 inch thick pieces; pound each slice between two pieces of plastic wrap until they are approx. 1/2 inch thick. Season pork medallions with garlic powder and pepper flakes.
Preheat large skillet over medium high heat and spray with non-stick cooking spray; add tsp. of olive oil.
Fry each medallion for approximately 3 minutes on each side (make sure they get done all the way through).
Put medallions into serving dish and keep warm.

title: quick potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in large baking dish and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: cheesy broccoli bake(a christmas tradition)
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
In 3-quart saucepan, cook onion in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in flour.
Add water. Cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Blend in cheese spread. Remove from heat.
Stir in broccoli, then eggs.
Transfer to a 1 1/2-quart round casserole.
Top with cornflake crumbs.

title: jelly roll
directions: In a bowl, combine flour, baking powder and salt.
In another bowl, combine beaten eggs and sugar.
Blend in water and vanilla. Slowly add flour mixture.

title: rice dressing
directions: Use heavy pot on top of stove.
Brown pork roast that has been stuffed with garlic and salted and peppered.
Add all the chopped vegetables.
Boil 4 sets of giblets and run through food chopped.
Add to other ingredients.
Add steamed rice.
(Can steam rice in water used to boil giblets.)
Cook very slowly on top of stove, covered.
Add more broth if needed.

title: nutty cheese log
directions: In small skillet melt butter until bubbly.
Add pecans.
Saute over low heat until lightly brown and crisp, about 5 minutes, stirring often.
Cool; chop fine.
Stir in seasoned salt and parsley; set aside.

In small bowl of mixer beat cheese, milk, mustard, worcestershire and pepper sauces until well blended. Chill until firm enough to shape foil, with metal spatula or moistened hand, mold cheese mixture in 7 inch log.	Roll in nut mixture; wrap airtight.
Chill until firm.	Good with crackers and fruit.

title: pumpkin pie mix
directions: Mix well and pour into pie shell.
Place in an oven preheated to 425° for 15 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and bake for 35 to 40 minutes more.

title: easy pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into 2 deep dish 9-inch pie shells.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: shrimp louisianne
directions: Melt margarine in skillet; saute vegetables.
Add raw peeled shrimp and saute a little longer.
Stir in flour, salt and chili powder.
Add milk gradually and cook 5 minutes over low heat.
Add catsup and parsley.
Cook, covered, 10 to 15 minutes.
Serve over rice with French bread or crackers.

title: drop donuts
directions: Beat egg until light. Add milk, dry ingredients and melted butter until blended.
Drop by spoon into hot oil.
Cook until light brown.

title: chewy bars
directions: Mix cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Pat in bottom of a 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Cream 2 eggs, powdered sugar and cream cheese for 5 minutes.
Spread over mixture in dish.
Bake 45 minutes at 325°. Cool and cut in squares.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter thoroughly.
Add sugar; cream.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating for 2 minutes per egg.
Add water.
Add flour, baking powder and vanilla.
Bake in a well-greased tube pan on top shelf at 325° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.

title: grand marnier dip
directions: Beat yolks with sugar in double boiler with electric mixer for 10 minutes (2 inches of water in pan).
Remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 of the Grand Marnier.
Cool and refrigerate until chilled. (Can do ahead.)
Beat 1 cup heavy cream until almost stiff.
Fold into other ingredients.
Stir in balance of Grand Marnier.
Serve with pineapple, cantaloupe, honeydew, strawberries or watermelon.

title: royal angel food cake
directions: Trim crust from angel cake.
Tear cake into pieces.
Combine egg yolks, 3/4 cup of sugar, lemon juice and peel.
Cook over hot, not boiling water, until mixture coats spoon.
Remove from heat and then add gelatine softened in cold water.
Cool until partially set.
Fold in egg whites beaten with remaining 3/4 cup sugar.
Add yellow food coloring.
Arrange a third of cake pieces loosely in bottom of 10-inch tube pan.
Pour over a third of custard mixture so it will run between cake pieces.
Continue until there are 3 layers of cake and 3 of custard.
Chill until firm.
Invert on cake plate and fill center with whipped cream.
Serves 8.

title: fruit juice punch
directions: Do not dilute lemonade or orange juice.
Mix all fruit juices and sugar together.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add ginger ale at the last minute just before serving.
Makes enough for 25 people.

title: pineapple dream pie
directions: Combine coconut and butter.
Press into pie pan and bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Cool.
In saucepan, combine gelatin and pudding and stir in milk.
Cook until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.
Stir in concentrate and chill until partially set.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add pineapple and pour into crust.
Chill 5 to 6 hours.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together (may use a blender or mixer). Grease quart dish with margarine or butter.
Pour mixture into dish and dot with butter or margarine.
Cook at 400° at least 40 minutes.
Top should be a nice brown, otherwise it will be watery.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients, then add beaten eggs and vanilla. Stir in flour, soda, salt and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or so.
Do not overbake.

title: hobo supper
directions: Arrange patties in casserole dish.
Top each one with onion slice. Put sliced potatoes next and pour Veg-All over top of potatoes.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chili sauce
directions: Scald and peel tomatoes.
Put through sieve.
Strain and save juice.
Mince other vegetables.
Mix sugar, salt and spices.
Add all ingredients to tomato juice.
Cook 1 hour and stir often to avoid sticking to pan.
Should be thickened when done.
Seal in hot, scalded jars.

title: milky way cake
directions: Melt candy bars with 1 stick margarine.
Cream the sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Add eggs to butter and sugar mixture and blend. Add alternately the flour, baking soda and buttermilk to batter, then add melted candy mixture and pecans.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.

title: ice water pie crust
directions: Mix flour, shortening and salt.
Add water and vinegar; mix sparingly.
For best results, place ingredients in a cool place (fridge) an hour before making crust.
Makes 1 double or 2 singles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: company potatoes
directions: Allow potatoes to thaw.
Mix together sour cream and grated cheese.
Add soup, butter, onions, salt and pepper.
Add potatoes. Put in 9 x 13-inch glass pan.
Top with 1 cup buttered bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until bubbly.

title: creamy fruit salad
directions: Combine apples, banana, orange sections and grapes in medium-sized bowl. Toss well with reserved orange juice and yogurt. Sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.

title: ritz cracker cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler.
Spread peanut butter between 2 Ritz crackers and then dip in melted chocolate.
Place on waxed paper until chocolate hardens.

title: hot dog casserole
directions: Cut sausage in 6 to 8 pieces.
Slice almost in half, longways, and brown in skillet.
Mix onions and mustard in prepared mashed potatoes.
Put potatoes on sausage or hot dogs; top with 1/2 slice cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven until cheese is melted.

title: overnight salad
directions: In a large bowl layer ingredients.
Spread the mayonnaise over top.
Sprinkle sugar on the very top.
Refrigerate overnight. Toss just before serving.

title: quick chocolate cake
directions: Add all dry ingredients, then sift.
Add milk and eggs. Add oleo
last.
Bake
in
a
greased 9 x 9-inch pan in a 350° until cake tests done.

title: chocolate lush
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl, combine flour, butter or oleo and walnuts.
Blend well.
Pat mixture into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes and let cool.

title: chili
directions: Fry meat until all meat is warm.
Add other ingredients and cook about	30
minutes
in
Dutch	oven or heavy skillet. Stir frequently	to
keep from scorching.
In pressure cooker, cook 12 to 15 minutes at 10 pounds pressure.

title: chocolate torte
directions: In
medium bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
In large mixer bowl,
cream
butter
and sugar until light and fluffy. Beat
in almond paste, egg yolks, melted chocolate and flour. Fold
in beaten
egg whites, just until blended.
Spread in a greased
and cocoa-dusted
8-inch
round cake pan.
Bake in a 350°
oven
for 30
minutes.
Cool 10 minutes and turn out on rack.
Center may sink a bit.
When cool, glaze.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil casserole.
Place a layer of potatoes; sprinkle flour, then layer of onion.
Sprinkle each layer with flour.
Alternate potatoes with onion.
Season with salt and pepper.
Heat milk and margarine together and pour over potatoes.
Cover casserole and bake 1 hour.
Remove cover and bake 1/2 hour longer to brown.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and beat until smooth. Pour into a 9-inch pie shell. Bake at 425° for 35 minutes or until set.

title: 3 layer pie
directions: Press flour, butter and pecans in the bottom of the pan and brown in oven at 350°.
Let this cool.
Mix powdered sugar, 1 to 2 cups
Cool Whip and cream cheese; spread on crust.
Mix chocolate pudding, vanilla pudding and milk; put on top of layer No. 2.
Put Cool Whip on top.
Keep in refrigerator.

title: toasted pumpkin seeds
directions: Clean and dry seeds.
Melt butter.
Mix in salt.
Stir seeds in salted butter.
Bake at 250° on a cookie sheet until brown and crisp.
Stir a couple of times.

title: super bowl dip
directions: Mix dressing and sour cream.
Sprinkle peppers and olives over mix.
Sprinkle cheeses on top.
Use Fritos to scoop.
Delicious!

title: tuna casserole
directions: Put tuna in casserole dish.
Combine nuts, 3/4 can of noodles, onion and celery.
Mix in can of soup.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and put rest of noodles on top and garnish with mandarin orange slices.

title: thelma ellison's norwegian meatballs
directions: In a large bowl, beat beef, egg, crumbs, milk, celery salt, pepper, nutmeg and onion with electric mixer at high speed until mixture is very smooth and light.
Dip hands in cold water and shape meat mixture into 1-inch balls.
Melt butter in large heavy skillet over medium heat.
Add meatballs without crowding and cook until browned, shaking pan occasionally to brown evenly.
Remove from skillet with slotted spoon.
Stir flour into pan drippings until smooth.
Cook 3 minutes until browned, stirring constantly. Stir in broth and cook, stirring, until slightly thickened. Return meatballs to skillet.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 15 minutes or until meatballs are cooked through.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Combine together and press into 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 325° for 15 minutes.
Let cool; add together xxx sugar, 1 cup Cool Whip and cream cheese; beat together and spread onto cooled crust.
Beat pudding mix and milk; pour over cheese mixture.
Chill; next, spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Garnish with chopped pecans.

title: cam's shrimp etouffee
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter until soft.
Add soups, tomatoes and shrimp.
Heat until warm throughout.
Serve over rice.
For extra dash, season with Crystal hot sauce.

title: turnip green soup
directions: Bring the first 5 ingredients to a boil and then add the turnip greens and salt and pepper to taste. Bring back to a boil; cover and simmer for 30 minutes or until turnips are tender. Serve with a fresh hot pone of bacon cornbread.

title: raspberry custard pie
directions: Beat eggs together well.
Mix separately sugar, flour and cinnamon.
Then mix with eggs and add milk.
Mix in berries.
Add to crust and bake at 400° for 10 minutes and then at 350° for 1/2 to 3/4 hour until it sets and is not sloppy.

title: strawberry ice cream
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add sugar to jello.
Let cool.
Beat together eggs, milk, cream, vanilla and strawberries. Add to jello and mix.
Pour in freezer can and freeze.

title: buttermilk custard pie
directions: Prepare 9-inch pie shell and set aside.
Mix sugar and flour. Blend in butter, eggs, buttermilk, orange extract and orange rind. Beat until mixture is very smooth.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° about 45 to 50 minutes or until pie is set.

title: adobe bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream Crisco, butter and sugar; beat in the whole egg and two egg yolks.
Sift flour, baking powder and salt together; combine the two mixtures and blend thoroughly. Spread batter in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts, chocolate chips and marshmallows over batter.
Beat 2 egg whites stiff; fold in brown sugar.
Spread over top of cake.
Bake 35 minutes.
Cool, then cut into bars.
Great warm or cold.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs.
Mix cocoa and coloring in a cup, then add to first mixture.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder and add with buttermilk.
Fold in soda and vinegar.
Pour into pans.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: holiday cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients until light and fluffy. Combine flour, baking powder and salt; blend into creamed mixture.

Divide dough in half and chill 1 hour. On lightly floured surface, roll dough to 1/8 inch thickness. Cut in desired shapes with 2 1/2 inch cookie cutters. Brush lightly with milk. Sprinkle with colored sugar or decorations. Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° about 6 to 8 minutes. Cool slightly; remove from pan.

title: italian jumbo shells
directions: Fry sausage and hamburger; drain.
Cook jumbo shells.
Cool in a single layer on wax paper or foil to keep from sticking together. Combine all ingredients except spaghetti sauce.
Spread a thin layer of spaghetti sauce in bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Fill shells and place on sauce, open side down.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: First Step (Tomato Sauce):
Chop 1 large onion, garlic and parsley fine and fry slightly in the hot olive oil or salad oil. Add tomatoes, tomato paste, bay leaves, salt, pepper and water and stir until well mixed.
Toss in the beef, breaking it up into little pieces with a fork or spoon.
Cook over low heat 45 minutes.
Stir occasionally.

title: carol's cheesecake
directions: Whip egg whites until they form peaks.
Gradually add sugar, vanilla and vinegar.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Spread on waxed paper or brown paper on a cookie sheet in a circle, slightly smaller than desired size.
Bake one hour at 275°.
Turn off oven and leave meringue several hours to dry.
Top with whipped cream, fresh fruit and toasted almonds (kiwi fruit and strawberries are perfect).

title: canederli dumplings
directions: Cube day old Vienna bread.
Fry bacon and chop.
Add milk to bread and let stand 15 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients (bacon, salami, cheese, eggs and flour).
Mix thoroughly.
Spoon to form balls and drop into a pan of boiling water.
(Test one first to see if it holds together.
If not, add a little more flour.)
Boil in water for 1 minute; remove.
Heat broth; add 1/2 can water and bring to boil.
Place dumplings in boiling broth.
Cover and steam for 20 minutes.
Garlic clove may be added to broth, if desired. Serve with broth, gravy or sauerkraut.

title: mushrooms florentine
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions.
Drain well and squeeze out excess liquid.
Spoon spinach evenly into bottom of shallow casserole.
Sprinkle with salt, onions, margarine and 1 cup Cheddar cheese.
Rinse and dry mushrooms and saute in skillet until tender.
Spoon mushrooms over cheese layer in casserole.
Sprinkle garlic powder over mushrooms and top with 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until bubbly.

title: baby ruth bars
directions: Bring to a boil the sugar and syrup.
Take off the stove and add the peanut butter.
Blend peanut butter in with sugar and syrup mixture. Add the Special K.
Pour into buttered Pyrex dish. Melt the chocolate chips and 6 ounces of peanut butter.
Spread over the Special K mixture.

title: taco salad
directions: Cook and stir ground beef in a 10-inch skillet until brown; drain.
Stir in water, chili powder, salt, garlic powder, red pepper and kidney beans.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Mix lettuce, cheese, olives, tomatoes and onions.
Pour ground beef on top and toss.
Divide among taco shells and garnish with avocado and sour cream.

title: speedy spuds
directions: Put the potatoes in a bowl and let them thaw a little.
Add the other ingredients.
Mix and bake for 90 minutes.

title: hearty breakfast pizza
directions: Prepare pizza crust dough according to directions and spoon onto pizza pan.
In separate container combine Egg Beaters, cooked crumbled sausage, shredded Cheddar cheese, mushrooms, salt and pepper.
Spread mixture on pizza crust and top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: corn meal pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat eggs and add sugar, butter, flour and meal and blend well.
Then add milk and vanilla.
Pour into three unbaked pie shells and bake in a 350° oven until done.
Test by inserting knife in center of pie.
Makes three pies.

title: party rye toast
directions: Combine all ingredients and spread on party rye bread slices. Bake at 300° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve warm as an appetizer.

title: corny cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Generously grease a cast iron skillet with up to 1/4 cup vegetable oil.
Preheat the pan in the oven or on the stove over medium high heat.
Mix ingredients together in a large bowl, stirring until well blended.
Pour batter into preheated skillet and bake until golden brown or about 30 minutes. If making individual servings in smaller pans, they require shorter cooking time.

title: knox blox
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine unflavored gelatine and Jell-O gelatin.
Add hot, boiling water.
Dissolve thoroughly.
Pour into oblong pan (13 x 9-inch) and let it set for several hours (or overnight) in the refrigerator.
Cut into squares and serve. Enjoy.

title: fruit coffee cake
directions: Mix the flour, salt, sugar and shortening until crumbly.
Save half the mixture for topping.
To remaining batter, add baking powder, soda and spices.
Mix thoroughly and add milk and eggs. Pour into two 8-inch pans.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs and add fruit of choice.
May use preserves.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable soup
directions: Fry hamburger; drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Cook about 3 hours.

title: peach jam
directions: Combine peaches and water.
Cook gently for 10 minutes.
Add sugar; stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to a boil very slowly, then cook rapidly for about 15 minutes or until thick.
Pour boiling hot into jars and seal.
Makes 4 pints.

title: apricot salad
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick, stirring constantly.
When cool, add 1 cup whipped cream or Dream Whip.
Spread over gelatin and top with grated American cheese.

title: cool grape salad
directions: Wash and pull all stems from the grapes.
Add the container of frozen Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Add box of jello.
Stir well, until all lime jello mix has dissolved.
Chill 1/2 hour.
Very cool and very good!

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat eggs into mixture, one at a time.
Mix in mashed bananas and flour mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into greased loaf pan.
Makes one loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: perfect quiche lorraine
directions: Line a 10-inch quiche dish or pie pan with pastry.
Trim excess pastry around edges.
Bake at 400° for 3 minutes.
Remove from oven and gently prick with a fork.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Let cool on rack.
Fry bacon until crisp; drain.
Crumble bacon and place in pastry shell.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Pour over the cheese in pastry shell. Bake at 375° for 65 minutes or until set.

title: stuffed peppers for two
directions: Cut off top of green pepper; remove seeds.
Cook 5 minutes in boiling water to cover.
Drain and set aside.
Combine ground beef, rice, 1/4 cup tomato sauce and remaining ingredients.
Stuff peppers with mixture and place in a small baking pan.
Pour remaining tomato sauce over stuffed peppers.
Cover and bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes or until meat is done.
Recipe can be increased for more than two.

title: fried cakes(doughnuts)
directions: Use as little flour as possible to mix well.

title: barbara's beef pinwheels with gravy
directions: Combine Bisquick, basil and water. Knead 5 times; roll out in a rectangle shape. Combine the beef and gravy.
Spread on top. Roll up in jellyroll fashion and cut into 1/2-inch slices.

title: corn bread dressing
directions: *Save the other half for giblet gravy.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw and squeeze liquid from frozen spinach before adding to other ingredients.
Makes about 3 cups.
Make this dip special by serving in a hollowed round loaf of bread.
Cut the bread you remove into cubes and use as dippers.
Have miniature bread sticks and crackers on hand for added variety.

title: million dollar fudge
directions: Mix the Hershey bars (broken), chocolate chips, vanilla, marshmallow cream and butter or margarine in a 4 to 6-quart container.
Mix the sugar and evaporated milk in a 4 to 6-quart saucepan.
Let sugar and milk come to a boil.
After it starts boiling, cook for 6 minutes.
Pour mixture of sugar and evaporated milk over the remaining ingredients and blend until smooth and creamy. After mixture is completely blended, add the chopped pecans.
Drop balls of mixture onto wax paper with a tablespoon. Let stand 4 to 6 hours or until completely chilled before removing from paper.

title: boiled icing
directions: Bring sugar and water to a boil.
Cook to soft ball (240°) stage.
Beat egg whites and cream of tartar until very stiff.
Pour syrup over egg whites, beating well.
Add vanilla; beat well.
This needs to be beaten 5 to 7 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together by hand.
Chill overnight.
Cut up loaf of French or rye bread in bite size pieces.
Serve with dip.

title: shirley kiser's fruit salad
directions: Combine fruit and sprinkle with dry pudding and Tang.

title: snowballs
directions: You will need a large bowl, spoon and plate.

title: quick and easy chowder
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter about 5 minutes.
Place frozen fillets on top and simmer 10 minutes.
Add rest of the ingredients.
Simmer 15 minutes.

title: roger's dried beef dip
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix all ingredients together and place in a baking/serving dish. Bake for 15 minutes. Serve warm with crackers.

title: orange yeast rolls
directions: Mix together in a bowl until it becomes lukewarm:
scalded milk, margarine, sugar and dash of salt.
Then add yeast, dissolved in water, well-beaten eggs, and orange juice.
Blend well and add 5 cups sifted flour and mix.
Dough will be soft.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Turn out on floured surface.
Knead.
Place in greased bowl; cover with towel and let set until double.
Punch down and let set 15 more minutes.
Form into rolls, let rise and bake about 12 minutes at 400°.

title: chiles rellenos
directions: Roast chiles and peel.
Stuff chiles with cheese.
Cut in long strips.
Cover the stuffed chiles with flour.
Mix the egg white until fluffy and add the yolk.
Beat for 5 minutes.
When mixture is ready, dip chiles in mixture and put in hot oil until brown. Turn to other side until brown.

title: golden chicken
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Arrange chicken in dish; bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Turn chicken and cover with soup.
Sprinkle with almonds and bake 20 minutes longer.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: ham roll-ups
directions: Take a slice of ham and put cream cheese on it; place on green onion across the ham and roll it up.
Slice it in 1-inch rolled slices fastened with toothpicks.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken in water with bay leaf.
Salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Use 2 or 3 celery tips of plain.
Pull meat off bone and dice in bite size pieces.
(Save broth and skim off fat.)
Put meat and fat in skillet and add chopped vegetables.
Cook until tender.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Shred chicken into small pieces and set aside.
Mix soup and Ro-Tel together and add chicken.
Crush Doritos and put them in the bottom of a 3-quart casserole dish.
Pour mixture of soup, Ro-Tel and chicken over chips.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: Mix cake by directions and set aside. Generously grease and flour 9 x 12 pan. Sprinkle coconut and pecans in bottom of pan. Cream oleo, cream cheese and powdered sugar until well blended and fluffy. Pour cake mix over coconut and pecans and spread evenly. Drop large spoonfuls of cream cheese mixture over cake mix. Do not touch sides of pan with mixture. Bake 55 minutes at 350°. Do not overbake. Let cool 25 minutes. Turn out on board. Topping will come out.

title: cream cheese and dry beef dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with crackers.

title: sugar cookies(like grandmaw made!)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar and eggs until smooth with uniform small lumps.
Add salt, baking powder and 2 cups of flour.
Blend together, then add milk and vanilla.
Mix again; now call someone else to start mixing for you so you can add the rest of the flour and laugh.
Add 1 cup of flour at a time until the rest of the flour is in; if mixture is still sticky to the touch, add more flour until it doesn't stick to your hand.
Roll out on a floured surface.
Cut in 3 to 4-inch ovals, about 1/2-inch thick.
Bake at 350° to 375° until done.

title: baked salmon salad
directions: Drain and flake salmon, reserving juice.
Combine flaked salmon and liquid with all other ingredients except potato chips. Spoon into a greased 1-quart casserole dish.
Top with chips. Bake at 450° for 15 minutes or until heated through.

title: country wheat bread
directions: About 2 hours before serving or day ahead:
In large bowl, combine salt, yeast, and whole wheat flour.
In small saucepan, over low heat, heat 1 2/3 cups water until very warm (125° to 130°).

title: cinnamon rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in milk.
Add shortening, margarine, eggs, sugar, salt and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Beat with mixer as long as possible.
(When adding flour, add until dough is no longer sticky.)
Cover and place in a warm place until double in bulk.
Punch down.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken, cool, debone and chop (reserve broth).
Fry bacon.
Remove when done.
In bacon grease cook onion, green pepper and celery.
Cook all, then crumble in bacon.
Cook spaghetti in broth until done.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix all and put in 2 baking dishes.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese (optional).
Bake at 350° until it gets good and hot.

title: super chili
directions: In a large heavy pot, over medium heat, brown beef in a little olive oil.
Stir in onion.
Add soy sauce, black pepper, V-8, tomato puree, taco mix and water.
Add bell peppers, tomato and garlic.
Process in food processor with a little water, 3 cans of beans, leaving one can of beans whole.
Add gravy and 1/8 cup hot sauce for medium hot chili.
Simmer 30 minutes, stirring often. Serve with shredded Cheddar cheese and Italian bread.
Serves 8.

title: deviled beef
directions: Place all ingredients in slow cooker and stir.
Cover and cook 10 hours on low or 5 hours on high.
Stir only near end of cooking time.
Or cook for 2 1/2 hours in 325° oven.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chocolate fruit dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except fruit in small bowl; stir with whisk until smooth.
Cover; refrigerate until well chilled.
Serve with assorted fresh fruit.
Cover and refrigerate leftover dip.

title: bananas au rum
directions: Cut bananas in half, then slice lengthways.
Melt butter in frying pan.
When hot, add bananas.
Brown on both sides.
Add sugar while browning.
Add rum and flambe (set on fire to burn off alcohol).
Spoon over coffee ice cream.

title: bayou blackened chicken
directions: Dry chicken pieces and coat with seasoned flour.
Heat oil and butter in large heavy skillet.
Brown chicken slowly on both sides. When brown, remove from skillet.
In small skillet, add more oil and butter if needed, cook mushrooms and chopped onions about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with garlic, salt, pepper and herbs while cooking.
Add wine or broth and black-eyes.
Heat just to boiling. Arrange chicken on top, pushing pieces into beans a bit.
Add tomatoes and juice (1/4 cup).
Cover and simmer 10 minutes until chicken is tender.

title: triple treats candy
directions: Melt over hot (not boiling) water the milk chocolate morsels and shortening; stir until morsels melt and mixture is smooth. Remove from heat.
Pour half of melted morsels into an 8-inch square greased and foil lined pan; spread evenly.
Refrigerate until firm (about 15 minutes).

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients 1 day ahead.
Cover tightly and store in refrigerator until serving time.
Cut broccoli into flowerets and cook Stripples until crisp.
Break Stripples into small pieces.
Mix broccoli, onion and Stripples together.
Just before serving, add cheese and mix in dressing.

title: polish wedding cake
directions: Cream oleo, oil and sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg yolks one at a time.
Sift flour and soda.
Add with buttermilk and beat well. Add coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Put in 3 (8-inch) layer pans, greased, and bake at 350° until brown (about 25 minutes).

title: boursin
directions: Soften butter and cream cheese.
Mix together with garlic. Add all other spices and mix well.
Serve with crackers.
Freezes well.

title: cobbler
directions: Mix the pie filling and lemon juice with 1/4 cup sugar.
Set aside.
Melt butter in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sift together flour, remaining cup of sugar and baking powder.
Stir in milk. Add berry mixture.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not stir. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yield:
6 servings.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Add soup, margarine and chopped peanuts and mix well.
Melt margarine and pour over bread crumbs. Pour broccoli mixture in greased casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer first 5 ingredients in the order given in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix together mayonnaise and sugar.
Spread over salad.
Top with cheeses and sprinkle with bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Cook spaghetti; rinse and drain.
Mix Miracle Whip with milk together.
Dice eggs, onions and pepper.
Add these and other ingredients with dressing mixture.
Pour over spaghetti, mixing well.
Place in covered container and refrigerate for at least 6 hours.

title: gladys beach's corn
directions: Melt butter and soften cream cheese.
Stir in corn and jalapeno.
Heat all together.

title: peach or pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar. Spread over bottom of well-greased cooker. Add pineapple slices and place cherries in the center of each one. Prepare cake according to package directions, using pineapple juice for part of liquid. Spoon cake batter into cooker over top of fruit. Cover cooker with 2 tea towels and then with its own lid. Cook on high 1 hour and then on low 3 to 4 hours. Allow cake to cool for 10 minutes. Then run knife around edge and invert cake onto large platter.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut eggs in halves.
Take yolks out; mash with a fork.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, salt and pepper; mix well.
If mixture seems too dry, add a little more mayonnaise.
Put mixture back in egg whites with a fork or spoon.
Sprinkle top with paprika.

title: homemade skillet hash
directions: Brown chopped meat in pan.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Remove meat from skillet.
Brown potatoes in butter with onion.
Add meat to potatoes.
Cook 1/2 hour.
Stir as necessary.

title: barbecue pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops in small amount of oil (drain) and put in baking dish.
Mix soup with ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and onion.
Pour mixture over the chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake 2 hours at 375°.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Cook vegetables with butter and season to taste.
Drain onions and mushrooms.
Mix all vegetables, onions and mushrooms and place in casserole.
Spread soup (undiluted) over top.
Sprinkle cheese over soup.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes, or until cheese is melted and browned.

title: nacho layer dip
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Mix in taco seasoning mix and sour cream.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with lettuce, tomatoes, onions and cheese.

title: st. helena stewed neck bones
directions: Wash neck bones.
Place
in
large
pot
with
water to cover. Cook over medium
heat for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Add
onion.
Cook until meat leaves the bone and very little liquid is left.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Brown beef, onions, salt and pepper.
Drain and spread in pie plate.
Mix milk, Bisquick and eggs; pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean (5 to 8 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes and serve.

title: spam and potatoes
directions: Melt butter and saute onions in butter until clear.
Add potatoes and cook until almost done.
Add diced Spam.
Cook another 3 to 5 minutes so that the Spam is heated through.
Add garlic powder and season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add additional seasonings if you wish.

title: veal scaloppine milanese
directions: If necessary, flatten the veal.
Season the flour with salt and pepper and sift it onto a sheet of waxed paper.
Lightly beat the eggs in a shallow dish.
