Mix breadcrumbs and Parmesan together in small bowl and spread on another sheet of waxed paper.
Lay each veal scaloppine in the seasoned flour to coat, then turn to coat other side.
Use 2 forks to dip each veal in the beaten egg and coat it thoroughly.
Press each veal into the breadcrumb/cheese mixture, coating both sides evenly.
Chill in refrigerator, uncovered, while sauteing peppers.
Finely chop the garlic.
Strip the oregano leaves from the stems, reserving 6 of the top sprigs for garnish.
Finely chop the leaves.
Slice the peppers lengthwise into thin strips.
Heat the oil in a medium frying pan.
Add the garlic, bell pepper strips, salt and pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, 7 to 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; add the chopped oregano and taste for seasoning.
Keep warm while cooking the scaloppine.
Slice the lemon for garnish and set aside. Heat half of the butter and 1 tablespoon olive oil in a large frying pan.
Add 2 to 3 scaloppine to the pan and fry over medium-high heat until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn the scaloppine with the 2-pronged fork and continue cooking until brown on the outside and no longer pink in the center, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Transfer to a plate lined with paper towels and keep warm.
Add remaining butter and oil and fry remaining veal, adding more oil, if necessary.
Transfer the scaloppine to individual plates and garnish with a lemon slice and a sprig of oregano. Spoon bell pepper strips alongside.

title: layered salad
directions: After washing vegetables, dry thoroughly.
Slice lettuce fine. Layer lettuce, onions, peppers and celery.
Spread mayonnaise on top.
Sprinkle sugar, black pepper and cheese.
Crumble bacon and spread over all.
Leave covered 8 to 12 hours.

title: broccoli-cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan, melt the butter in the oven.
Remove.
In a bowl, beat the eggs.
Then add flour, milk, salt and baking powder.
Mix well.
Add cheese and broccoli (or spinach) and blend.
Pour into buttered pan and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Remove and cool 10 minutes to set.
Cut into bite-size squares.
Serve with toothpicks.
Can freeze by placing squares on cookie sheet.
Freeze solid and then place into plastic bags.
To serve after frozen, heat about 12 minutes at 325° or microwave.

title: homemaker's holiday
directions: Prepare Creamettes according to package directions.
Drain. Combine soup, milk and cheese.
Simmer, stirring occasionally until cheese is melted.
Mix macaroni, cheese sauce, luncheon meat and green pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: miniature cream puffs(chicken filled)
directions: Bring butter and water to a boil in saucepan.
Reduce heat. Add flour, all at one time, stirring rapidly.
Cook and stir until mixture leaves sides of pan.
Remove from heat.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Beat until mixture looks satiny and breaks off when spoon is raised.
Drop from teaspoon onto ungreased baking sheets.
Bake in a 425° oven for 20 to 30 minutes, until brown.

title: rainy day pizza
directions: Spread sauce on each slice of bread.
Lay pepperoni on and top with cheese.
Place on cookie sheet and broil until cheese melts (or use toaster oven).
Easy for kids.

title: world's best onion sandwich
directions: Mix the first five ingredients and marinate sliced onions for 3 to 4 hours.
Increase the amount of marinade used as you increase the amount of onions.
After marinating, butter bread on both sides.
Make sandwich out of sliced onions.
Toast on grill. Sliced tomato is good on the sandwich.

title: german potato salad
directions: Combine and refrigerate overnight.

title: supper casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions in skillet; cook celery about 10 minutes in salted water, then drain.
Add soups and celery to meat and onions. Mix well with 1/2 can chow mein noodles.
Put mixture in greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Spread remaining noodles on top and bake about 45 minutes in 350° oven.

title: heath bar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk and beat well.
Stir in flour and vanilla, mixing well. Spread into 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle immediately with Heath bars.
Cool completely in pan before cutting into squares.
Makes about 30 bars.

title: melissa's brownies
directions: Melt margarine in a large bowl in the microwave for less than 1 minute.
Add sugar and mix well.
Beat in eggs, one at a time. Add vanilla and cocoa.
Add the other ingredients.
Stir until all are blended.
Spread mixture into a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, which has been sprayed with oil.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until brownies pull away from side of pan.
Do not overbake.

title: fried rice
directions: In large skillet, cook and stir rice, onion and celery in oil over medium heat until rice is golden brown and onion is tender. Add other ingredients except green pepper.
Reduce heat.
Simmer 18-20 minutes, stirring occasionally until rice is tender.
Stir in green pepper.
Simmer 10 minutes longer.

title: apple cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, cinnamon and salt together.
Beat eggs and sugar; add oil, flour and flavoring.
Stir in apples and nuts. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour into pie.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes.

title: blackberry royal wine bundt cake
directions: In a large mixing bowl, stir together cake mix and gelatin. Add eggs, cooking oil and Mogen David Royal wine.
Blend well! Pour batter into heavily greased Bundt pan and bake in preheated 325° oven for 40 to 45 minutes or until inserted toothpick comes out clean.
Cool and invert pan to remove cake.

title: strawberry cream pie
directions: In a double boiler, put sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Add scalded milk.
Cook until thick.
Add a small amount of the mixture to the eggs.
Add egg mixture to contents of the double boiler.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Chill.
Add strawberries and pour into pie shell.
Refrigerate.
Top with whipped cream when serving.

title: french chicken bake
directions: In skillet, heat 6 tablespoons margarine over medium heat. Add mushrooms and celery.
Saute 5 minutes.
Strain and set aside, reserving juices.

title: polish sausage
directions: Wash and slice sausage lengthwise or whole.
Lay sausage, meat side down, in frying pan. Add onion and bell pepper.
Cook on low heat until vegetables are of desired consistency. Good over rice or in hot dog roll. Smells like the fair!

title: chili con carne
directions: Stir tomatoes and liquid from kidney beans, tomato sauce and seasonings. Heat until boiling. Reduce heat; simmer 1 hour and 15 minutes. Stir in beans; simmer, stirring occasionally, about 15 minutes or until desired consistency.

title: halibut steaks
directions: Combine brandy, lemon juice, dill weed and bay leaf.
Place steaks in shallow pan in a single layer.
Top with onion and lemon slices.
Pour brandy mixture over.
Refrigerate and let stand an hour or longer before cooking.
Drain steaks, reserving marinade. Place steaks on grill over hot coals.
Combine chili sauce and butter with marinade.
Baste steaks often with mixture as they broil.
Cook about 5 minutes each side, just until fish is cooked through and flakes easily.
Sprinkle with salt to taste.
Makes 4 servings.

title: sylvia's jezebel sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Serve as a sauce with ham or pour over cream cheese and serve with crackers.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix vanilla pie filling according to package.
Combine peanut butter and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Pour 1/2 peanut butter mixture in pie crust.
Pour vanilla pie on peanut butter mixture. Top with remaining peanut butter mixture.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: strawberry pretzel salad
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together and press in a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Let cool.
Mix together next 3 ingredients.
Spread on crust.
Mix together last 3 ingredients. Let gel slightly.
Pour over cream cheese mixture.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into squares.
Top with Cool Whip, if desired.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Cream butter (margarine will do, but butter makes it yummy) and sugar.
Add egg yolks and cream thoroughly.
Add pineapple and fold in egg whites, whipped cream (Cool Whip will do, but real cream makes it yummier), nuts and vanilla.
Place layer of wafers on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan, then layer the mixture until all pineapple mixture and crushed wafers are used. Top with wafers and refrigerate overnight.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put each of the first 5 ingredients
in large square container in order given.
Top with mixture of the salad dressing, sour cream and sugar.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and/or bacon bits. Refrigerate overnight.

title: ham loaf with raisin sauce
directions: Combine ingredients.
Press into 8 1/4 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf; then turn out into shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Makes 8 servings.

title: rhubarb orange custard pie
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 1/4 cup sugar gradually, beating well after each addition.
Add butter and orange juice to egg yolks; beat thoroughly.
Add remaining 1 cup sugar, flour and salt; beat well.
Add rhubarb to yolk mixture.
Stir well.
Gently fold in meringue.
Prepare pastry.
Make a high-fluted rim.
Pour mixture into the pastry-lined, fluted 9-inch pie pan.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees.

title: sunrise mini pizzas
directions: In a large bowl beat the eggs.
Add milk, salt and pepper. Melt butter in a skillet, add the egg mixture.
Cook and stir over medium heat until the eggs are set.
Remove from the heat and set aside.
Roll each dinner roll
into a 5 inch circle.
Place on greased baking sheets.
Spoon egg mixture evenly over crust. Sprinkle with bacon and cheese.
Bake at 350 degrees for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Yield 10 pizzas.

title: superb london broil
directions: In a shallow glass pan, combine steak sauce, lemon juice, onion and garlic.
Add steak; turn to coat and marinate for 1 hour.
Preheat grill.
Remove steak from marinade; season with salt and pepper and place on grill over medium-hot coals.
Grill until desired doneness (10 to 15 minutes for medium) basting often and turning once.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix peanut butter, cream cheese and sugar together.
Spread in graham cracker crust and freeze. Top with Cool Whip and serve.

title: sauce for cocktail meat balls
directions: Combine and simmer.
Pour over browned meat balls.
Serve warm.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Line Pyrex dish with Oreos.
Mix marshmallows, Cool Whip and candy.
Pour over Oreos.
Top with chopped pecans, if desired. Best to chill overnight.

title: hawaiian cake
directions: Cake:
Follow directions on cake mix plus add pineapple juice. Batter will be runny.
Pour into 15 x 10 1/2-inch jelly roll pan, well-greased.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: sticky popcorn
directions: Melt on stovetop or in microwave and pour over popcorn.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all juices together.
Add drinks and sugar.
Stir to dissolve.

title: gracie's quiche
directions: Tenderize onions, mushrooms and meat in oleo.
Spread over pie crust.
Grate cheese and dredge in the flour.
Put floured cheese on meat mixture.
Pour on the eggs mixed in the milk.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes, until custard is set.

title: finger paint
directions: Put Sloppy Joes in a bowl.
Stir it.
Put it on the sandwich and eat it.

title: bite-size fruit cakes
directions: Beat
oil
and
sugar
together.
Beat in eggs one at a time. Add vanilla.
Add soda, salt and flour, Mix well.
Stir in
fruit mixture.
Spoon batter into well greased muffin pans using
paper cups
if desired.
Fill about 3/4 full.
Press a candied pineapple, cherry, and pecan half into center of each. Bake
in preheated
oven
for
30 minutes or until cake springs back at touch of a finger.
Makes about 18.

title: ice cream(electric freezer)
directions: Add milk to rim on freezer.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients; simmer for 1 hour.
Serve with hot corn bread.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and garlic.
Simmer all but the last 5 ingredients for 10 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup taco sauce in the bottom of a 9 x 13 inch pan.
Lay enough tortillas to cover sauce and then cover tortillas with 1/2 cup taco sauce.
Add beef mixture and top with sour cream, corn and half of the cheese.
Top with a layer of tortillas.
Cover with remaining taco sauce and top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes. You can freeze this. Enjoy.

title: apricot nectar salad
directions: Mix the jello, 2 1/2 cups apricot nectar and boiling water; chill in oblong pan.
Boil 1 cup apricot nectar and add the egg, flour and sugar blended together.
Stir until thick; cool.
Add the Cool Whip; spread mixture over jello.

title: uncle ray's salsa dip
directions: Beat all ingredients until blended.
Serve with corn chips or nachos.

title: mexican lasagna
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In order listed, make two layers in pan.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Serve as side dish with tacos or as a main meal.

title: cinnamon cucumber rings
directions: Let the cucumbers get big and turn yellow.
Peel and cut large yellow cucumbers in half.
Scoop out seeds with a spoon, creating a cup of each half.
Cut them to make ring slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Put these to soak in the 8 1/2 quarts water and lime solution for 24 hours.
Drain and wash well with clear water. Cover with cold water; soak for 3 hours.
Drain.

title: liver fritada
directions: Make 1 1/2 cups rice and let simmer.
Fry bacon in a 12-inch skillet or Dutch oven until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Crumble bacon and reserve.
Drain fat from skillet, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Return 2 tablespoons to skillet.
Cook and stir onion in fat until tender, about 2 minutes.

title: pecan pie cookie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9-inch square baking pan.
In a medium bowl, combine 1 cup of flour, oats, butter and brown sugar until crumbly.
Press into baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes.

title: applewiches
directions: Take slice of toast, spread on margarine, then spread on peanut butter.
Add sliced apples.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and brown sugar.
Put in hot oven until ingredients start to meet. Leave oven door open.
Will only take a short time.

title: honey chicken
directions: Place chicken in pan.
Pour honey on top, making sure all pieces on chicken have some.
Sprinkle remaining ingredients on top.
Cover.
Place in preheated oven (350°) for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cranberry slush
directions: Mix in an ice cream pail.
Freeze, stirring once or twice. To serve, fill glass with 3/4 full of slush and add 7-Up.

title: potato salad
directions: In large kettle, cook potatoes until done.
Dice egg whites, celery, green peppers and onions.
Mix potatoes and vegetables and add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.

title: wanda's chicken and dumplings
directions: Separate dinner rolls into eight parts; put equal amounts of chicken on each.
Wrap chicken in each roll and place in baking dish, end side down.
Mix can of chicken soup with can of water. Pour over dumplings.
Cover and bake 45 minutes at 375°.

title: jezebel sauce
directions: Blend first 4 ingredients and chill.
Serve over cream cheese with Wheat Thins.

title: layered spinach salad
directions: Cook tortellini to desired doneness as directed on package. Drain and rinse with cold water.
In a large flat salad bowl or 9 x 13-inch baking dish, layer cabbage, spinach, tortellini, tomatoes and green onion.
Pour dressing over ingredients. Sprinkle with bacon. Cover and refrigerate until serving time. Serves 8.

title: fettuccine italiano
directions: Prepare fettuccine according to package directions.
Drain. Gradually add milk to combined mayonnaise and garlic in small saucepan.
Heat thoroughly, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and blend in egg.
Toss with hot fettuccine until well coated.
Add remaining ingredients and toss lightly.
Garnish with basil leaves, if desired. May substitute spaghetti for fettuccine. Yields 5 servings.

title: white punch
directions: Chill juice and Sprite. Mix with cream of coconut.
Serve with frozen ice ring made with additional pineapple juice.

title: carolina pound cake
directions: Combine sugar and Crisco.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour alternately with milk.
Finish adding ingredients and mix well. Beat a few seconds, using high speed mixer, then lower speed and beat several minutes.
Pour batter into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shrimp with garlic sauce
directions: Soak mushrooms in hot water for 20 minutes or until soft; drain.
Rinse in warm water; drain.
Squeeze out excess moisture. Remove and discard stems; cut caps into thin strips.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Grease a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Put in pizza dough, covering the bottom of pan.
Brown hamburger, then pour into pan.
Cover hamburger and sauce with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until the cheese is melted.

title: stuffed cabbage or cabbage rolls
directions: Boil large cabbage head until leaves can be pulled off head. Mix all remaining ingredients and roll into a ball; place in cabbage leaf.
Tuck ends in and place in pan.
Bake in tomato soup for 1 hour.

title: beer batter fish
directions: Heat oil (1 1/2 inches) in heavy saucepan or fryer to 350°. Lightly coat fish with 3 to 4 tablespoons Bisquick.
Mix 1 cup Bisquick, salt, egg and beer until smooth.
Dip fish into batter; scrape off excess batter.
Fry until golden brown.

title: microwave beef stew
directions: Put beef cubes in a 3-quart microproof casserole or baking dish.
Sprinkle with salt.
Combine gravy mix with 1 cup water; stir.
Pour over meat.
Cover and cook on High (maximum power) for 5 minutes; stir.
Cover and cook on 60 (bake) for 20 minutes.
Add celery, carrots and potatoes and stir lightly so that vegetables are covered with gravy.
Add more water for a thinner gravy and salt for the vegetables.
Cover and cook on 50 (simmer) for 25 to 30 minutes or until vegetables and meat are tender.
Remove from microwave and let stand for 5 minutes.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Cream together margarine and sugar.
Beat in eggs, vanilla and sour cream.
Add baking powder.
Sift together salt and flour and add to other ingredients. Pour half of batter in Bundt pan and sprinkle with mixture of nuts, cinnamon and sugar.
Pour in remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: braised celery
directions: Put the celery, parsley, onion and bouillon in a casserole; toss lightly.
Sprinkle with the salt, pepper and bacon.
Bake, covered, at 375° for 30 minutes.
Take out and sprinkle with the bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, for about 10 more minutes.
The bread crumbs will be brown.

title: sweet potato and apple
directions: Peel and slice potatoes and apples. Put in baking dish a layer of apples and then a layer of potatoes.
Cover with marshmallows. Put mix on top of apples and butter.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: easy mushroom gravy
directions: 1. Combine soup and 1 1/2 c. of water (broth) and add to droppings.
Stir well while heating to a boil. 2. Mix remaining water with flour.
Add to gravy when it boils stirring until it thickens.
Makes 3 to 3 1/2 cups of gravy.

title: orange creamsicle cake
directions: On cake mix directions, use milk instead of water and mix as usual with ingredients listed. Add the extract. Bake in 2 round cake pans. Let cool.

title: pineapple salad
directions: Cook very slowly the eggs, pineapple juice and sugar.
Stir constantly until thick.
Pour over pineapple mixture when cold. Serve with whipped cream.

title: easy oven beef stew
directions: Combine beef, onion, celery, carrots, potatoes and beans; place in an 11 x 7 x 2 1/2-inch casserole dish.
Combine tapioca, salt and sugar and sprinkle over meat and vegetables; add tomato juice.
Cover tightly with aluminum foil.
Bake at 250° for 4 hours.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all dry ingredients and then add liquids, pumpkin and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes in loaf pans (3 loaves, 45 minutes or 2 loaves, 60 minutes), that have been greased.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking soda, salt and cocoa.
Blend in butter, milk and vanilla.
Beat 3 minutes on high speed.
Add eggs.
Beat 3 minutes longer.
Pour into floured and greased cake pans. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes on wire racks.
Remove from pans.
Cool completely.
Frost with your favorite frosting.
Makes 2 layer cake or 1 oblong 13 x 9-inch cake.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Combine all ingredients except sausages or franks into small bowl.
Let stand 1 hour or overnight for flavors to blend.
Serve with grilled smoked sausage or franks.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.
Good also with barbecue or fowl, holiday times or family gatherings.

title: sour cream pecan pie
directions: Bake in
preheated
oven until crust is brown and filling is slightly puffy, 30 to 35 minutes.

title: easy fudge cake
directions: Melt 2 sticks butter or margarine and unsweetened chocolate. Add flour, sugar and well beaten eggs.
Add vanilla.
Pour into greased sheet cake pan and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Let cool. Cut into squares.

title: country sausage au gratin potatoes
directions: Stir and cook sausage and onion in oil until onions are tender, about 5 minutes.
Stir in potatoes. sauce mix, water and pepper.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat, cover and simmer 10 minutes longer.
Stir in carrots, simmer another 10 minutes.
Stir in broccoli.
Cover and cook until heated through well.

title: creamy chicken spread
directions: Combine first seven ingredients, mix well.
Stir in chicken, eggs, and green onion.

title: popovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Generously grease popover cups.
Pour milk into medium-sized mixing bowl.
Add flour and salt.
With rotary beater or wire whisk, beat until well blended.
Do not overbeat.
One at a time add the eggs, beating in each until completely blended.
Pour batter into cups filling 3/4 full.
Do not scrape bowl.
Bake at 425° for about 20 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 325° and continue baking 15 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Spray Bundt cake pan with Pam or Baker's Secret.
Mix together sugar and cinnamon and coat cake pan with mixture.
Beat together ingredients for 5 minutes.
Pour into coated Bundt pan.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: nutty crunch bar cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease the bottom and sides of a 9 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Bring to boil.
Simmer for 1 hour.
Put cut hot dogs in for last 15 minutes.

title: go-go-go scotch fudge
directions: Combine morsels and peanut butter in the top of double boiler. Place over hot (not boiling) water, stir until butterscotch melts and mixture is smooth.
Remove from water.
Add milk.
Stir until well blended.
Add black walnuts.
Turn into foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill until firm.
Cut in 1-inch squares.
Store in covered containers, if they last long enough.

title: microwave caramel corn
directions: Place corn in large paper sack.
Add nuts, if desired.
In a deep bowl combine butter, brown sugar, white Karo syrup and salt. Micro until it boils, then 2 more minutes.
Stir in soda.
Pour sauce over corn in bag and shake well.
Micro for 1 minute and 15 seconds.
Take out and shake well.
Micro again 1 minute and 25 seconds.
Tear bag open.
Spread out and cool.

title: cushaw pie
directions: Cook on top of stove and pour into baked pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: bean dip
directions: Step #1:
Spread bean dip in bottom of 13 x 9 x 2 glass pan.

title: icebox oatmeal wafers
directions: Cream together the Crisco and sugars.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Sift together the dry ingredients and blend well; mix into creamed mixture.
Add oatmeal and pecans; mix well.
Chill several hours of overnight.
Shape into 16 to 20 (2-inch) rolls. Wrap in wax paper, then wrap 4 to 6 rolls in foil and put in freezer.
Bake as needed.
Slice 1/4-inch thick.
Bake on oiled cookie sheets for 8 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 16 to 20 rolls.

title: batter bread
directions: Mix mixture until thin (not running).
Drop by spoon on well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° until top is brown.

title: spaghetti and meatballs
directions: Cook spaghetti.
Mix hamburger and Swedish meatball seasoning in a large bowl, cook in frying pan.
Add the flavoring envelope with the thickener to 2 cups milk.
Add 1/2 cup water with the meat mixture mixing evenly before cooking.
When meat is done, add the milk mixture and thickener, put all together and serve.

title: graham cracker fudge
directions: Mix crumbs and flour; set aside.
Melt oleo.
Add milk and sugar.
Boil 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chips.
Stir until melted.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir well.
Pour in pan and cool.

title: coreen's ono skillet spaghetti
directions: Brown all meats.
Drain fat.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer for 45 minutes.

title: blueberry french toast
directions: Mix flour, brown sugar and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until coarsely ground.
Turn slices of bread over and cover well with blueberries.
Sprinkle crumb mixture on top.
Bake 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve by slices or cut into squares.
(May top with slices of strawberries, if desired, instead of blueberries.)

title: nacho potato soup
directions: In a 3 qt. saucepan, combine the contents of the potato pkg, corn, tomatoes, and water; mix well.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15-18 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Add milk, cheese, and hot pepper sauce, if desired; cook and stir until cheese is melted.
Garnish with parsley, if desired.
Yields 6-8 servings.

title: potato cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl in order given.
Do not season potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or slightly longer.

title: lemon sandwich spread
directions: Cook the lemon juice and grated lemon until thickened.
Remove from heat and add nuts.
Use as sandwich filling.

title: cookie sheet cake
directions: Melt together butter, water and cocoa.
Mix flour, soda, sugar, cinnamon and salt together.
Add buttermilk, eggs and vanilla together.
Mix first and second mixtures together, then add third mixture.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350° in ungreased pan.

title: vanilla wafer cake
directions: Cream margarine; add sugar.
Beat until smooth; add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each.
Add vanilla.
Add wafers alternately with milk.
Add coconut and nuts.
Placed in a greased and floured angel food pan.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 to 2 hours. Makes 16 servings.

title: apple bread
directions: Mix together first 5 ingredients.
Then add dry ingredients and vanilla.
Bake in greased and floured pan about 60 minutes at 350°.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: dill dip
directions: Combine ingredients. Refrigerate 1 hour. Serve cold. (Yields 1 cup.)

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Cook chicken in boiling water, remove from bone and cut in small pieces.
Cook onion, celery and spaghetti in broth where chicken was cooked until tender.

title: sunday supper casserole
directions: Melt shortening; add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in flour and salt.
Add milk gradually.
Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until thickened and beginning to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in mustard and cheese.
Cut wieners in 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, wieners and cheese sauce in 2-quart buttered casserole dish.
Top with cheese sauce. Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix the eggs and then all other ingredients.
Put in greased pan.
Cook in oven at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up broccoli.
Use only flowerets.
Wash and soak in water in refrigerator for 2 hours or overnight.
Drain.
Mix together all ingredients.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Sift flour and cocoa.
Add to batter.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 10 x 14-inch pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with marshmallows.
Return to oven until marshmallows soften and run together.

title: roast wild goose
directions: Clean goose well.
Season with salt and pepper and vinegar. Place an onion in cavity.
Let stand overnight.
Remove onion. Dredge with flour and place in roasting pan in slow oven, 325°. Roast, uncovered, until tender and browned, 20 to 25 minutes per pound, basting with juices in pan.
Goose may be filled with stuffing, if desired.

title: beef-stuffed peppers
directions: Cook corn according to package directions, omitting salt and fat; drain and set aside.
Cut tops off peppers and remove seeds. Chop tops; set aside.
Cook peppers in boiling water 5 minutes. Drain peppers and set aside.

title: broccoli dish
directions: Cook broccoli and drain.
Save 1/2 cup juice.
Put juice, 1/2 oleo and diced cheese in saucepan over low heat until melted.
Put broccoli in dish and pour cheese mixture over dish.
Crush crackers and mix with 1/2 butter or oleo; place on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: california quiche
directions: Saute mushrooms, celery and onion in butter until limp; set aside.
Beat eggs; add cream, flour, salt, paprika and pepper sauce.
Beat well.
Stir in ham or bacon, cheese and wine.
Cover; chill.
It is best to chill overnight.

title: easy fudge candy
directions: Melt top three ingredients in double boiler.
Stir occasionally.
Drop by teaspoons on wax paper.

title: mini-chicken tostadas
directions: Mix and shape into 50 or 60 small balls.
Place 10 meat balls on 8 or 9-inch glass dish.
Cook in microwave oven 2 minutes. Drain.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet pickles from ripe cucumbers
directions: Cut cucumbers in half and peel.
Cut each half in quarters lengthwise.
Remove seeds.
Heat 2 cups water and coarse salt. Add ice water. Pour over cucumbers and chill for at least 12 hours.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar, Dream Whip and milk together.
Break angel food cake into small pieces and line bottom of pan.
Make layers of cake, mixture and pie filling to top of pan.

title: vinegar green salad
directions: Combine seasonings in liquid until sugar dissolves.
Stir in vegetables and let stand overnight.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream the eggs until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar. Fold in pumpkin and lemon juice.
Fold in flour, baking powder and pumpkin pie spice.
Pour into well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan.
Sprinkle with 1 cup finely chopped nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
(Use Teflon pan for best results.)
Quickly loosen sides with knife and turn onto thin towel sprinkled generously with powdered sugar.
Roll from wide side; let cool.
When cool, unroll and spread with creamed mixture.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Make turkey gravy this way:
Place gizzard, heart and neck in saucepan and cover with water.
Withhold the liver until near the end of the cooking, since it requires only 10 to 15 minutes.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup butter and corn flakes. Put them in baking dish. Sprinkle crushed corn flakes on top and drizzle remaining butter on top of corn flakes. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: fillet beef cantonese style
directions: Wash the beef, then cut into long strips.
Marinate in 1 tablespoon soy sauce, 1 tablespoon water, cooking wine and cornstarch for 30 minutes.
Heat the wok and add 1 cup of oil.
Fry the beef until it is done medium; remove and drain.
Heat the wok, then add 2 tablespoons of oil.
Stir-fry the onions until cooked. Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Mix in the beef and stir quickly.
Remove and stir.

title: chocolate smunchies
directions: Mix chocolate pudding according to directions on package, using nonfat milk.
Cool thoroughly. Mix peanut butter with pudding.
Drop 1 tablespoon onto 1 square graham cracker.
Place low calorie whipped topping on top of the pudding/peanut butter mixture.
Cover with second graham cracker square.
Freeze until ready to use.

title: fried okra
directions: Cut okra into 1-inch pieces; season to taste.
In small bowl, beat egg and add milk.
Dip okra in mixture and roll in corn meal. Fry in deep fat until crisp and brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: circus peanut salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 2 cups boiling water.
Add circus peanuts; stir until partially melted.
Add the cold water; let jell softly. Whip Dream Whip; stir into jello mixture.
Add the drained pineapple and pecans; stir well.
Refrigerate until jelled.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients and pour into a casserole dish.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: chocolate swirl cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Over hot, not boiling, water combine chocolate chips, 1/2 cup sugar and heat until chips melt and mixture is smooth.
Remove from heat and set aside.

title: chicken salad
directions: In a medium mixing bowl combine mayonnaise, sour cream, onion, curry powder, 1/4 tsp. salt and dash of pepper.
Stir in chicken and celery.
Cover and chill.
Serve on lettuce lined plates with popovers.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pork roast
directions: Place pork, onion, pepper, oil and seasonings in large crock-pot. Add water and cook on low for 8 to 12 hours.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Toss all ingredients with chilled dressing.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: easy cole slaw
directions: Cut cabbage, remove core with a sharp knife, slice each section into match size strips (about 2 to 4-inches).
Put into large bowl and knead about 5 minutes, until wilted.
Cut onion (a bit larger than a golf ball) finely.
Add to cabbage.
Mix with wooden spoon.
Add mayonnaise by heaping spoonfuls (approximately 4 ounces, or to your taste).
Add white vinegar, sugar and oil. Toss with wooden spoon until well combined.
Add salt to taste. Keep at room temperature for at least an hour.
Refrigerate coleslaw overnight.

title: cheese spread
directions: Mix ingredients well and serve with crackers. Store leftovers in a covered dish in the refrigerator.

title: no cook divinity
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients until stiff peaks form (using mixer on high speed).
Reduce speed on mixer to low and slowly add confectioners sugar and nuts.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Let dry 12 hours.
Turn over occasionally.
Store in airtight container.
Makes 5 dozen pieces.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat in saucepan until dissolved the gelatin, sugar and pineapple.
Cool, then add buttermilk, nondairy topping and nuts. Blend thoroughly and pour into mold.
Chill.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar, beating well at medium speed of an electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Combine flour and baking soda; add to creamed mixture, alternating with sour cream, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix just until blended after each addition.
Stir in flavorings.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 5 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes and remove from pan.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: In saucepan, mix sugar, vinegar, water, cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir well.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Pour over vegetables and chicken.

title: sherry broth sauce
directions: In small saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute longer.
Serve warm.

title: calvin's lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger and sausage; drain excess grease.
Prepare lasagna as directed.
Combine ingredients as follows:

1 layer lasagna, 1 layer hamburger, 1 can spaghetti sauce, 1 package cheese (Mozzarella or Cheddar), 1 layer of lasagna, 1 layer ham sausage, 1 can diced tomatoes (with sauce), 1 package cheese. Bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: baked cheese dip
directions: Cut beef into small pieces.
Soften cream cheese.
Mix all ingredients and spoon into the hollowed loaf of bread.
Bake at 325 degrees for 1 hour.
Serve
with Ritz crackers.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients except tortillas and cheese.
Layer tortillas (torn into bite size pieces), chicken mixture and cheese twice.
Bake 30 minutes or until cheese has melted and started to turn brown.
Serve with chips and salsa.

title: crumb cake
directions: Bake at 350° until top is firm enough to hold crumbs, about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: two egg chocolate pie
directions: Mix together and cook in a double boiler for 10 minutes.
Pour into pie shell and top with margarine and set in oven to brown for a bit.

title: crock-pot fajitas
directions: Cut flank steak or chicken into portions.
In any size crock-pot, combine meat, onion, green pepper, red pepper, jalapeno pepper, cilantro, garlic, chili powder, cumin, coriander and salt. Add tomatoes.
Cover and cook on low for 8 to 10 hours or on high 4 to 5 hours.
Remove meat from crock-pot and shred.
Return meat to crock-pot and stir.
To serve fajitas, spread meat mixture into flour tortillas and add favorite toppings.
Roll up tortillas. Serves 6 to 8.

title: chili
directions: Brown meat in shortening; set aside. Mix dry ingredients.
Mix meat and dry ingredients in a large pot.
Add next 4 ingredients. Cover with water; simmer 3 to 4 hours.
Add oats and cook until thick.

title: asian chicken cashew salad
directions: Combine the first six ingredients and refrigerate overnight. Add remaining ingredients just before serving over vegetable mix.

title: hamburger dip
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain excess grease.
Melt cheeses and mix hamburger and cheese together.
Add tomatoes and peppers.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: apple crisp
directions: Place apples in 8-inch greased pan.
Blend remaining ingredients until crumbly and spread over apples.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is golden brown.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease an 8 x 12-inch pan with butter or margarine.
Place bread slices in the bottom of the pan.
Spread cheese over the bread.
Then sprinkle the sausage over the cheese.
Mix the eggs, milk, salt, mustard and pepper and pour over the bread, cheese and sausage.
Let the mixture soak overnight and cook at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: barbecue meat loaf
directions: Combine ground beef, bread crumbs, milk, egg, onion, salt and pepper.
Mix and put in baking pan.
Cover with this sauce:
1/4 c. catsup, 2 Tbsp vinegar, 1 tsp chopped onion.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Grease and flour 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Beat brown sugar and margarine until light and fluffy.
Stir in zucchini, pineapple and eggs.
Add flour, baking soda, cinnamon, salt and allspice.
Blend well.
Fold in nuts and coconut.
Bake 60 to 70 minutes at 350° or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook the potatoes; peel and dice.
Combine with onion, salt, pepper and crumbled bacon.
In the bacon grease, add water, vinegar and sugar and boil.
Combine the flour with 1 tablespoon of water.
Pour into sauce.
Mix well.
Pour over potatoes and onions and serve hot.
For color, add chopped pimentos and green pepper to the onion, potatoes and bacon.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Prepare broccoli and lima beans as directed on package, then drain.
In a casserole dish, mix soups, sour cream and water chestnuts.
Stir in cooked broccoli and lima beans.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: In a large bowl, crush the vanilla wafers.
Chop cherries and pineapple and add to the crushed wafers.
Add the raisins and chopped nuts.
Add condensed milk and mix well until moist.
Place into a tube cake pan or several small loaf pans.
Refrigerate several hours.
(Spray cake pans with cooking spray for easy removal.)

title: south of the border dip
directions: Mix beans with 1/2 of sour cream and 1/2 of cheese.
Brown hamburger and add taco seasoning according to directions on package.
Spread a layer of bean mixture on bottom of casserole dish.
Spread hamburger for next layer.
Put rest of sour cream on next; put remaining bean mixture and top with remaining cheese. Cook at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chocolate apple bread
directions: Grease two 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a small bowl combine flour, salt, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Set aside.

title: two-corn casserole
directions: Melt butter in 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Add eggs and sour cream. Stir in both kinds of corn, salt and muffin mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes until set.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: great apple pie
directions: In a small bowl, combine sugars, flour and spices; set aside. In a large bowl, toss apples with lemon juice. Add sugar mixture; toss well to coat. Line a 9-inch pie pan with half the pastry. Place apple filling into crust; dot with butter. Top with remaining pastry; flute edges and cut slits in top. Beat the egg white until foamy; brush over pastry. Sprinkle sugar on top. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Increase temperature to 400° and bake 10 to 15 minutes more or until golden.

title: dora's chicken salad
directions: Grind chicken, eggs, celery, pickles and red pimento.
Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Add jar of Marzetti dressing.
Can add a little pickle juice and mustard if desired.
Chill before serving.

title: mamoose's cornbread dressing
directions: When cooking chicken, add a little celery seed or celery salt. It helps the taste of the broth.
You may also add a little butter or margarine.

title: beef and potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Brown beef and drain.
Place beef, broccoli and 1/2 can French fried onions in potato shell.
Combine soup, milk, 1 cup cheese and seasonings; pour over beef mixture.
Bake covered at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions; bake, uncovered, about 5 minutes longer.

title: lexington barbecue sauce
directions: Mix this together.
Put pork roast and sauce in crock-pot and cook.

title: connecticut beef stew
directions: Melt shortening; cook meat and onions until meat is brown and onions tender.
Add water, boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer for 50 minutes.

title: candied acorn squash rings
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Trim off ends of each squash.
Cut each squash crosswise into 4 rings (each almost 3/4-inch wide). Discard seeds and membrane from slices.
On nonstick pan, arrange rings in a single layer and sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with foil and bake until slightly tender, approximately 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vermicelli with tomato-basil sauce
directions: Cook vermicelli according to package directions, omitting the salt and fat; drain well, then set aside. Coat a Dutch oven with cooking spray; place over medium heat until hot.
Add onion and garlic; saute 5 minutes or until onion is tender. Stir in tomato, tomato sauce, basil and pepper.

Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Add vermicelli; cook, uncovered, until thoroughly heated, stirring occasionally. Transfer mixture to a large platter; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Yields 8 servings (155 calories and 8% fat per 1 cup serving).

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots to barely cooked; cool.
Mix sliced onions, green pepper and carrots.
Mix remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Cool.
Pour mixture over carrot mixture.
Cover and marinate 12 hours.
This dish can keep in refrigerator for 1 week.

title: chicken salad
directions: Put all together and mix. Serve on chef salads or in sandwiches.

title: pear cake
directions: Beat eggs, add sugar, oil and vanilla; mix well.
Add combined flour, salt, soda and spices.
Stir in pears and pecans.
Pour into 10 x 14-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes to 1 hour.

title: golden banquet punch
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add ginger ale last.
Pour over ice cubes.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together and use a large punch bowl. Serves 50.

title: sangria
directions: Combine liquid ingredients and float lemon and orange slices on top.
Add plenty of ice to punch bowl.

title: dexo ration cake
directions: Cream Dexo, sugar and vanilla until light; add egg yolks. Beat until fluffy.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk; mix well.
Beat egg whites until foamy; add corn syrup and beat until mixture holds peaks.
Fold into batter.
Pour into 2 greased and waxed paper lined 8-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Turn out on rack.
Cool.
Frost with any desired frosting.

title: veggie bars
directions: Unroll dough.
Place in lightly greased 15 x 10-inch jellyroll pan, pressing edges and perforations together to line bottom of pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 7- 8 minutes or until brown.
Cool. Combine in mixing bowl cream cheese mayonnaise, salad dressing mix and beat at medium speed for one minute or until smooth.
Spread over crust in pan.
Combine broccoli, cauliflower and sprinkle over cream cheese mixture mixture till covered.
Chill 8 hours.
Cut into squares.
May use your choice of veggies or use chopped ham for color; just use the amount of broccoli and cauliflower you like; be sure to press down vegetables a little into cream cheese.

title: sausage rice casserole
directions: Brown sausage; pour off fat.
Add pepper, onion, celery and rice.
Cook together until blended, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Top with cheese the last 5 minutes of cooking, if desired.

title: family christmas punch
directions: Chill ginger ale.
Combine cranberry, pineapple, lemon and orange juices with sugar and almond extract.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale and stir well.
Makes 4 1/2 quarts.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix and cook until thick; remove from heat and add strawberry Jell-O and food coloring.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Bake pie shell.
Put washed and drained berries in baked pie shell. Pour or spoon cooled filling over berries.
Top with whipped cream or Dream Whip.

title: mama's yeast rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast over warm water and set aside.
Combine milk and shortening, stirring until shortening is melted and mixture is lukewarm.
Combine yeast mixture with milk and shortening.
Add remaining ingredients and stir until all ingredients are combined. Knead until smooth.
Let rise in warm (not hot) place, covered until double its size.
Punch down, knead again and roll out onto floured surface.
Cut into desired shape (round cut doubled over, balls, etc).
Place on greased cookie sheet and let rise again. Bake at 400 degrees for 13 minutes.
Delicious eaten while warm.

title: mattie's bran muffins
directions: Mix
Raisin
Bran and sugar.
Beat eggs.
Add oil.
Add dry ingredients.
Add buttermilk, then stir in bran and sugar. Makes 3 quarts.
May be stored in refrigerator for a couple of weeks. Bake
as
you
wish in lined muffin tins at 400° until golden brown.

title: brenda's kosher dill pickles
directions: Boil all the ingredients while you pack your jars with cucumbers. To each jar, add 1 dill sprig, 1 pod of garlic and 1 red pepper.
Pour hot mixture over cucumbers and seal.

title: raspberry cream
directions: In bowl, mix ice cream, sherbet and juice concentrate until blended but not melted.
Serve in goblets topped with berries. Serves 6.

title: black joe cake
directions: Mix flour and other dry ingredients, then add eggs, oil, coffee, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased and lightly floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.
When cool, frost with your favorite icing.
My favorite is peanut butter.

title: swedish meat balls
directions: Put beef and next 7 ingredients in a bowl; mix well.
Form into 1-inch meat balls by rolling a small amount of meat at a time between palms of hands.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients in a large casserole.
Add onion soup and mushrooms.
Put chicken on top.
Bake in oven at 350° to 400° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until rice is tender.

title: basic white sauce
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan;
add flour and cook over low heat 1 or 2 minutes, stirring constantly.	Add
milk
and keep stirring until thick and smooth.
Add
seasoning
and
simmer. To enrich white sauce, combine 1 or 2 egg
yolks with 1 tablespoon sauce and add, beating well while sauce is hot.
You may thin sauce to desired consistency by adding a little hot milk. This sauce may be used in ala king,
macaroni,
cream
soup or whenever cream sauce is called for.

title: mayonnaise chicken
directions: Mix mayonnaise and soy sauce and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Cover with foil.

title: corn casserole 2
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Melt butter. In 9-inch pie pan, combine crushed cracker crumbs, garlic salt and pepper. Add lemon juice to the melted butter; stir to blend. Dip chicken in melted butter, then roll in seasoned crumbs.
Place chicken, skin side up, in ungreased 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle with remaining crumbs. Bake near center of 350° oven for 65 to 75 minutes or until chicken is fork tender.

title: snowy mashed potatoes
directions: Beat potatoes with a mixer, then add the cream cheese, sour cream and garlic powder.
Stir in the chives.
Place in a baking dish.
Sprinkle paprika and pats of butter on top.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
May be made the day before and refrigerated, then baked.

title: cornbread dressing
directions: Make pan of cornbread.	Melt butter and saute onion and celery until tender.
In large bowl, combine all ingredients, except broth
and	eggs.
Blend broth and eggs together, then blend in with cornbread mixture.
In lightly greased pan, bake 30 minutes at 450° or until brown.

title: the "100" cookie
directions: In large bowl mix sugar, brown sugar, oil, margarine, egg, vanilla, rice cereal, coconut and oats.
Sift together salt, flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Add to sugar mixture and mix well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto greased cookie sheets and bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.

title: apple custard coffee cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, combine biscuit mix, 1/4 cup sugar, milk and vanilla; mix well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
Toss apples with 1/4 cup sugar and 1/2 teaspoon cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
In a bowl, combine eggs, cream and remaining sugar.
Pour over apples; sprinkle with remaining cinnamon.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until knife inserted near center comes out clean. Serve warm.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and mayonnaise until blended.
Add other ingredients.
Serve with assorted crackers.

title: good baked chicken
directions: Spray oblong baking dish with cooking spray.
Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix chicken soup and sour cream together.
Pour over chicken (do not dilute).
Bake for 2 hours at 250°, uncovered. Sprinkle grated cheese on top, then sprinkle crackers over top. Pour on margarine.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes longer at 350° or until lightly browned.

title: pineapple frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cook over medium heat until thick.
Great spread over a yellow cake!

title: baked meat loaf alaska
directions: Combine gravy mix with ground beef, onion and black pepper. Shape into a loaf 2-inches high.
Prepare instant mashed potatoes according to package directions, adding 1 teaspoon of chopped chives.
Spread over meat loaf.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 minutes.
Top with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake until cheese melts.

title: lisa's fruit salad
directions: Add enough orange juice to reserved juice to make 3 cups liquid. Add juices to the 2 packages of tapioca pudding. Bring to a boil and cook until thickened.
Remove from heat and cool.
When cool, pour over the fruit and refrigerate. Chill several hours before serving.

title: fish stew
directions: Fry bacon in large pot.
Place potatoes, onions and fish in alternate layers until all are used.
Add tomato juice, paste and enough water to cover vegetables and fish.
Add seasoning.
Bring to boil and cook rapidly for 20 minutes, then add all 12 eggs. Break one at a time in a small bowl and pour on top of stew.
Cook 15 minutes longer.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onions until brown.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Simmer for 20 minutes.
Brush on meat.

title: teacakes
directions: Mix egg, sugar, vanilla and oil.
Add flour until thick enough to knead.
Roll out and cut with cookie cutter.
Grease cookie sheet.
Bake at 325° until bottom is brown.

title: twinkie dessert
directions: Cut Twinkies in half lengthwise.
Put soft sides up in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare pudding according to directions on box.
Let cool.
Put pudding on Twinkies.
Then put drained pineapple on top of pudding.
Spread on Cool Whip and nuts.
Make the day before. Keeps well.

title: tuna fish spaghetti sauce
directions: Brown tuna fish, garlic and parsley in oil over gentle fire for 10 minutes.
Add salt, pepper, tomatoes and tomato puree and simmer 1 hour.
Add oregano and basil and cook 5 minutes.
Serve over spaghetti or fine noodles.
Makes enough for 1 pound of spaghetti.

title: creamy ranch potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in a 3 1/2-quart crockery cooker. In a small bowl, combine cream cheese and salad dressing mix. Stir in soup. Add to potatoes.

title: hot seedy rolls
directions: Cover whole wheat kernels with water. Soak 2 to 4 hours. Drain.
In a large bowl, dissolve yeast in warm milk. Add salt, oil and cottage cheese. Blend. Add 1/2 wheat kernels, all whole wheat flour and most of the all-purpose flour.
Mix.
Knead dough until smooth. Cover and let rise in warm place 40 minutes. Turn out onto lightly floured board.
Knead.
Cut into 20 even pieces. Form rolls.
Put on cookie sheets.
Let rise 20 minutes. Brush rolls with warm water.
Sprinkle with remaining, slightly crushed wheat kernels.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes. Remove, cover and cool.
Makes 20 rolls

title: golden cornbread
directions: Sift cornmeal, flour, sugar, baking powder and salt into bowl. Add egg, milk and oil.
Beat until smooth.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Peel and cut apples.
Boil sugar, water, cinnamon and apples until tender.
Roll biscuits; fill with apples.
Fry in 1/2 cup of cooking oil until golden brown, then serve.

title: easy carrot cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Beat Miracle Whip, cake mix, eggs, water and cinnamon at medium speed with mixer until blended well.
Stir in carrots and nuts.
Pour into a greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake 30 to 35 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: bacon cheese rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Spread bread with cheese spread.
Then trim crusts and cut bread slices into 3 strips.
Roll up each bread strip, then wrap with 1/3 slice of bacon.
Secure with a toothpick.
Place roll-ups on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes or until bacon is partially cooked.
Remove from oven and cool.
Wrap in foil and freeze.
To serve, open package of frozen roll-ups just enough to expose tops.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 12 minutes or until bacon is crisp and bread is golden.

title: hearty vegetable soup
directions: In a large saucepan, saute the zucchini, onion, celery, carrot and garlic in oil until crisp-tender.
Stir in the tomatoes, picante sauce or salsa, water, bouillon and cumin; bring to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
After the stew has simmered, add the beans and heat through.
Serve with your choice of garnishes (extra chopped onions, some grated low-fat cheese, sliced black olives, shredded lettuce or chopped peppers).
Rice or corn bread are good accompaniments as well.

title: grapefruit chiffon pie
directions: Combine gelatin, 1/2 cup sugar and grated rind in saucepan. Beat egg yolks; combine with juice and stir into gelatin mixture. Cook over low heat, stirring constantly, until gelatin dissolves and mixture thickens slightly.
Chill.
Stir occasionally until mixture mounds when dropped from spoon.
Beat egg whites until frothy.
Gradually beat in 1/4 cup sugar, beating until stiff. Fold into gelatin mixture.
Fold in half of whipped cream.
Turn into baked pie crust.
Chill until set.
Top with remaining half of whipped cream.

title: white sugar cookies
directions: Use enough flour to roll out without sticking, 3 to 4 cups approximately.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in a buttered dish and bake at 325° until rice has absorbed milk and is brown on top.

title: individual pineapple meat loaves
directions: In large mixing bowl, stir together egg, oats, onion, green pepper and salt.
Add beef and pineapple; mix well.
Divide mixture into 6 equal portions.
Shape each portion into a 4 x 2-inch loaf.
Place loaves in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes, or until meat is no longer pink.
Top each loaf with 1 teaspoon of the sweet and sour or barbecue sauce, if desired.
Serves 6.

title: impossible pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 or 10-inch pie plate.
Beat all ingredients until smooth, one minute in blender on high or 2 minutes with hand beater.
Pour into plate.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Garnish with whipped cream, if desired.

title: frozen dessert
directions: Cream together cream cheese and sugar. Fold into the cream cheese the Cool Whip, strawberries, pineapple and nuts. Spoon into a 9 x 13 pan and freeze overnight.

title: salmon-vegetable stew
directions: Debone salmon, mix all vegetables together with salmon in 10-quart stew pot.
Heat on medium for 30 minutes.
Add V-8 juice as needed to keep stew thin.

title: syrup muffins
directions: In medium bowl, combine water and syrup, stirring until well blended.
Stir in milk until blended.

title: italian slop
directions: Brown hamburger, onion and green pepper; drain fat. Add sausage and spaghetti sauce; combine. Add lasagna; stir gently. Pour into casserole dish. Combine cheeses, as much as you like. Sprinkle on top of casserole. Cover. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: men only lemon pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt in pan. Add hot water. Cook over direct heat, stirring, 6 to 8 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir 1/4 cup hot mixture into beaten yolks. Stir into hot mixture. Cook 6 minutes over low heat. Remove from heat and add juice, peel and butter. Cool slightly and pour in pie shell.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In a 4-quart saucepan, place chicken with water to cover; cover.
Cook over medium heat until tender.
Remove chicken, bone and cut into bite size pieces.
Chill broth until fat congeals on top; remove fat.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix crushed pretzels and butter.
Pat into a 9X13-inch casserole dish.
Place in 350 degree oven for 10 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool.
Beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth. Add Cool Whip and spread mixture over completely cooled pretzels. In another bowl, mix Jello and hot water until dissolved.
Add frozen strawberries and place in refrigerator until Jello sets, then pour over Cool Whip layer.
Return to refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: south of the border meal
directions: Brown meat and chopped onion.
Pour mushroom soup, enchilada sauce and green chilies over meat; mix.
In baking dish, break half of taco shells, then layer on half of the hamburger and cheese.
Repeat layer of taco shells and layer of hamburger; end with grated cheese.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: baked chicken salad
directions: In large skillet melt oleo over medium heat.
Add celery and onion, cook about 4 minutes or until tender.
Remove from
heat. Stir in next 5 ingredients until well blended.
Add chicken, almonds and mushrooms, toss to coat well.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with potato chips.
Bake in 325° oven 25 to 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: marinated beans
directions: Mix all ingredients in 2-quart dish. Cover and refrigerate 8 hours before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: dump cake
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Drain pineapple and spread over bottom of pan, corner to corner.
Spread the pie filling the same. Dump the cake mix (dry) on top of the fruits.
Spread as evenly as possible. Sprinkle on the nuts.
Melt the butter and pour all over the top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Easy.

title: best ever banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Do not try to double recipe.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar
well;
add flavoring.
Add eggs, 2 at a time alternately with small amount of flour beating well after each addition.
Add salt.
Mix well.
Pour into tube pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Test for doneness.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt cheese and butter together over low heat.
Sift powdered sugar and cocoa together.
Add melted cheese mixture.
Blend well. Add vanilla and nuts.
Spread into 9 x 13-inch pan and cool.
Cut into squares.

title: winter salad
directions: Cook succotash according to label directions, omitting salt. Drain.
Place in medium size bowl. Toss lightly with oil, vinegar, seasoned salt and pepper.
Chill.
Fill salad bowl with bite size pieces of salad greens; top with celery, onion, cheese and marinated vegetables.
Toss just before serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix lemon juice with sweetened condensed milk.
Add Cool Whip to this mixture and mix well. Fold in fruit.
Pour into graham cracker crust. Chill.

title: frozen waldorf salad
directions: Cook over low heat until thick the eggs, sugar, pineapple juice, lemon juice and salt, stirring constantly.
Cool and then pour in fruit.
Mix well.
Fold in 1 cup of whipped cream.
Freeze and serve frozen.

title: golden potato surprise
directions: Peel and dice potatoes.
Boil until half done.
In saucepan, add onion and butter; saute.
Add the flour and stir into the onion mix.
Add the half and half slowly, stirring constantly, until all mixed in.
Add salt and pepper.

title: ziploc meat loaf
directions: Put all ingredients into a large freezer Ziploc bag.
Squeeze out excess air and seal tightly.
Let your child squeeze and squish the mixture around until well mixed.
Open bag and shake mixture into a lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corned beef dinner
directions: Place corned beef in Dutch oven barely covered with hot water. Add onion, garlic and bay leaves.
Cover, simmer about 3 hours or until tender.
Remove meat from liquid and add potatoes and carrots.
Cover and bring to a boil.
Cook 10 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 20 minutes.
Carve meat across the grain, making thin slices.
Serves 6.

title: danish dessert
directions: Heat to boiling point.
Thicken with 3/4 cup Clear Jell and 1 cup water.
Cook until thick; add 1/2 cup jello (any flavor).
Add fruit.

title: chocolate eclair dessert
directions: Mix instant pudding and 3 cups milk together until thickened, then fold in whipped topping.
Make a layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Spread 1/2 of pudding mixture over crackers.
Make another layer of crackers, then pour remaining pudding mixture over crackers.
Make 1 more layer of crackers on top of second layer of pudding mixture.
Mix 2 tablespoons of milk with can of chocolate frosting while smooth. Spread over top layer of crackers.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Can be frozen and thawed out later.

title: broccoli and cauliflower salad
directions: Cut up cauliflower and broccoli, stems and all.
Add olives, onion and eggs.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Add mushrooms last.
Stir and refrigerate.

title: nanny's double chocolate mint cookies
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, milk and peppermint.
Beat with spoon until a nice smooth batter.
Start to add the dry ingredients, leaving flour until last.
Gradually add the flour until you get a very stiff batter.
(Tip:
The cheaper the margarine the more flour you have to use, otherwise your cookies will be flat.)
Last of all, add the chocolate chips.

title: crab cakes
directions: Saute onion in margarine until tender.
Remove from heat; stir in crab meat and next 8 ingredients.
Mix well and shape into 8 patties.
Coat with additional bread crumbs.
Pour oil to a depth of 1/4-inch in heavy skillet.
Fry in hot oil (375°) for 4 to 5 minutes on each side.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together and roll into small balls.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Mix boiling water with Jell-O and dissolve.
Add other ingredients.
Pour into long baking dish. Chill until set.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Combine soup and water; stir well.
Spoon evenly over chicken; mix stuffing mix with melted margarine.
Spoon over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.

title: quick chili with beans
directions: Brown the first 3 ingredients, then add salt.
Next, add the rest of the ingredients and bring to bubbly boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 25 minutes.
If you like it hot, add a dash of crushed red pepper.
This may be doubled, if you want a large quantity.

title: smooth and creamy peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugars, half and half and corn syrup in a Dutch oven. Cook over low heat, stirring gently, until sugars dissolve.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes to wash down sugar crystals from sides of pan.
Uncover and cook to soft ball stage (235° on candy thermometer), stirring occasionally.

title: cornbread
directions: Cook at 375° until center is done and browns.

title: white bean chili
directions: Saute chicken with garlic until done.
Add remaining ingredients and heat completely.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: eggplant parmesan
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut eggplant into 1/4-inch rounds. Combine the flour and salt in a bowl.
Now the eggs and milk in another bowl, and lastly the cracker crumbs and pepper in another bowl.
Now take an eggplant slice and dip both sides in the flour mixture, then the egg mixture and lastly the cracker crumbs. Repeat with all the eggplant.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. (Glass is best as eggplant won't discolor.)
The slices may overlap, but shouldn't cover each other completely.

title: rich sweet dough
directions: Scald milk; stir in sugar, salt and oleo.
Cool to lukewarm. Put warm water into large warm bowl.
Sprinkle in yeast; stir until dissolved.
Stir in lukewarm milk mixture, egg and half the flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in remaining flour to make a stiff batter.
Cover tightly with foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Dough may be kept in refrigerator for 3 days.

title: vegetable hot dish
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake covered for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: herb glaced carrots
directions: Add 2/3 cup water to carrots; bring to a boil.
Add butter and sugar.
Simmer on low heat for 6 minutes.
Add basil and oregano. Add 2 tablespoons water.
Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Uncover and simmer until all liquid is absorbed.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serves four.

title: tater tot hot dish
directions: Pat raw ground beef in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Season.
Put layer of sliced onion.
Mix together the soups and cover.
Top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: mexican vegetable casserole
directions: Combine Vegeburger, milk, onion, green pepper, salt and chili powder in a heated microwave skillet.
Cover and cook 3 minutes on full power.
Add tomato sauce and chili beans.
Mix well.

title: 5 cup salad
directions: Combine all in a large bowl.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: hungarian chicken paprikash
directions: Melt Crisco in large frypan.
Season chicken with salt, pepper, paprika and flour.
Brown chicken.
Transfer chicken to large pot.
Saute onion.
Put with chicken.
Rinse frypan and put enough water in pot to cover chicken.
Cook over medium heat for about 1 1/2 hours.
Mix milk, light cream and flour thoroughly. Cook over medium heat until boils.
Pour immediately over chicken. (If too thin, add more flour.)
Salt to taste; sprinkle with paprika.
Cook until sauce thickens.
Serve over waffles.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Heat milk, bread crumbs and butter in double boiler.
Clean salmon.
Beat eggs and mix with salmon.
Mix salmon mixture with milk, bread and butter mixture, stirring well.
Place into a greased baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: christmas bread
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Let rise in a very low heated oven.
Put mixture in 1-pound coffee cans, 2/3 to 3/4 full. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, peanut butter, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat at medium speed of electric mixer until well blended.
Add egg.
Beat until blended. Add flour to creamed mixture at low speed.
Mix until blended. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2 inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.
Flatten slightly in crisscross pattern with tines of fork. Bake at 375° for 7 to 8 minutes or until set and just begin to brown.
Do not overbake.
Cool 2 minutes.

title: chili cheese
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes until browned lightly.
Cut in 1-inch or larger squares to serve.
Serve hot!
Makes a great breakfast dish.

title: spaghetti squash pancakes(an original creation.)
directions: Key Idea:
Substitute zucchini (or summer squash) puree for milk in prepared pancake mixes.
Add steaming juice to thin, if necessary.

title: coconut pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Strain pineapple slices in a bowl and use juice in the cake mix.
In a mixing bowl, put cake mix, eggs, oil and 1 cup pineapple juice.
Mix well for 3 minutes with hand blender.
Blend mix on low speed until blended together, then on high speed for 3 minutes.
Spray a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place pineapple on bottom. Sprinkle 1 cup brown sugar over pineapple.
Pour coconut cake mix over pineapple and brown sugar.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until done.

title: pat's picante pintos(first place winner 1993 fun fest)
directions: Wash pinto beans and begin cooking.
Add bacon to beans.
Use grease from bacon to cook onion slightly.
When onion is cooked, add cilantro, jalapenos and tomato.
Cook about 1 minute.
Add to beans and continue cooking until beans are done.
Add salt and black pepper to taste.

title: coconut macaroons
directions: Mix coconut and sugar.
Blend in egg and almond extract.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Drop from teaspoon onto greased baking sheet. Bake for 15 minutes or until golden at 350°.
Remove from baking sheet at once.

title: raw apple cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add apples and nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Add to apple mixture.
Do not use an electric mixer.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked shrimp with garlic
directions: Mix oil, garlic and salt.
Add shrimp, turning to coat; sprinkle with minced parsley. Cover and refrigerate for at least 4 hours or to next day.
Transfer to a 10 x 15-inch baking pan. Bake at 375° until shrimp are opaque when cut, about 10 minutes. Arrange in bowl and garnish with parsley sprigs.

title: bacon-spinach salad
directions: Cook bacon in 12-inch nonstick skillet over low heat, stirring occasionally, until crisp.
Stir in vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Heat through, stirring constantly, until sugar is dissolved; remove from heat.
Add spinach and onions to bacon mixture.
Toss 1 to 2 minutes or until spinach is wilted.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In mixing bowl, combine syrup, sugar and margarine.
Stir in eggs and pecans.
Pour mixture in shell and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 30 minutes longer.
(I bake mine at 325° for about 40 to 45 minutes instead of 400°.)

title: lime salad
directions: Dissolve Jello, marshmallows, cream cheese and water together. Add pineapple, mayonnaise and nuts.
Beat 1 small can Carnation milk until stiff and stir in.
Place in refrigerator for about 4 hours or until chilled.

title: creamy rice pudding
directions: In a stainless steel pot, beat eggs thoroughly.
Add sugar, milk, vanilla, water and rice.
Mix well.
Bring to a slight boil, then lower heat and cook for about one hour, stirring frequently. Pour into a bowl, when slightly cooled off, and refrigerate overnight or 8 hours.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Grease casserole dish and put in 5 tablespoons chicken broth. Add 1/2 of the chips.

title: spring pea salad
directions: Rinse peas in hot water; drain. Combine vegetables, nuts and bacon with sour cream. Mix dressing, mustard and garlic together; pour over salad mixture. Toss gently. Chill.

title: honey butter
directions: In a 1-quart saucepan, combine honey and butter.
Bring to boil and cook, stirring constantly, for 3 minutes.
Cool slightly; stir in evaporated milk.
Serve hot or cold over ice cream.

title: "dressing" for raw turnip greens
directions: Beat egg; add sugar, salt and vinegar.
Bring to a boil; add minced onion; cool.
Pour over raw turnip greens; sprinkle with bacon bits.

title: marshmallow candy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients together to the soft ball stage. Pour over gelatin and cold water that has soaked while syrup boiled.
Beat for 10 minutes.
Add egg whites and salt.
Pour into a pan lined with nuts, coconut or powdered sugar.
Cool in refrigerator.
Cut into squares and roll in the nuts.

title: dirt cake
directions: Blend cookies in blender.
Cream 10x sugar with margarine and cream cheese.
In bowl, mix milk with pudding; add Cool Whip to pudding.
Add cream cheese mixture.
Put foil on bottom of flowerpot.
Layer cookies (dirt), pudding, cookies (dirt), etc. Add silk flower on top.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour 2 large loaf pans or 1 large and 3 small. Mix dry ingredients.
Mix wet ingredients in separate bowl.
Fold together and pour in pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until tested done.

title: meatballs in white sauce
directions: Mix first three ingredients and pour over meatballs. Heat thoroughly.

title: cherry coke salad
directions: Bring to boil 1 can sour pie cherries and sugar.
Add jello and stir.
Remove from heat.
Add Coke, pineapple and nuts.
Pour in mold and chill.

title: caramel salad
directions: Mix lemon and lime Jell-O as directed until it is partly jelled.
Add pineapple (jell until firm).
Mix Dream Whip as directed.
Soften and whip cream cheese.
Add cream cheese to Dream Whip and spread over Jell-O mixture.
Make sauce.

title: ted's barbecue chicken
directions: It is better to burn charcoal for about an hour before cooking chicken to get rid of starter taste.
Also helps if top can be covered for smoke.
Good, but hot.

title: chocolate oatmeal squares
directions: Cream margarine and sugar; add eggs and vanilla. Mix in dry ingredients. Fold in chips. Pat into 13 x 9-inch pan and bake about 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a baking dish.
Mix stuffing mix and melted margarine. Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture in bottom of dish.
Add a layer of chicken.
Dilute the can of celery soup with 1 can chicken broth and pour over the chicken layer.
Add another layer of stuffing mix, then another layer of chicken.
Dilute the can of chicken soup with 1 can of broth and pour over the chicken layer. Sprinkle
a few crumbs of dressing mix on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
(Use water, if not enough broth.)

title: strawberry brownie tort
directions: Grease 2 (9-inch) round cake pans.
Line with wax paper extending up sides of pan.
Grease waxed paper.
Prepare brownie mix as package directs for cake like brownies.
Pour into prepared pans.
Bake at 350°
for 20 minutes or until top springs back when touched.
Cool.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Stir pineapple cheese, flour and sugar together until moistened.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Place crushed crackers on top.
Melt margarine and pour over crackers.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.

title: fresh apple squares
directions: Melt oleo; add sugar and egg.
Add remaining ingredients. Place in a greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle with a cinnamon and sugar mix (1/4 teaspoon cinnamon and 1/4 cup sugar).
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cut in squares and serve.
When doubling recipe, bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pickled cabbage
directions: Quarter cabbage and let stand in salt water 24 hours.
Then cook in clear water until you can pierce with a straw.
Mix sugar, vinegar, nutmeg, mustard, ginger, horseradish and turmeric.
Let stand for 24 hours.
Mix in cabbage and put in stone or glass jars. Keep about 14 days, then put in quart jars with same brine and seal jars.

title: cinnamon orange butter
directions: Cream together until blended well.
Serve on crackers or bread.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Combine margarine, peanut butter, powdered sugar and Rice Krispies.
Shape into balls and chill 24 hours.
Melt over hot water the paraffin wax, chocolate chips and chocolate Hershey bar. Dip the refrigerated balls in the chocolate mixture and put on wax paper to cool.

title: bacon bites(breakfast appetizer)
directions: Blend cheese, onion and bacon pieces with mixer.
Roll out each can of crescent rolls into two long pieces.
Spread cream cheese on top.
Roll together to form a log.
Slice pieces of 1/2-inch and bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: shrimp dish
directions: Cook rice in boiling salted water until tender.
Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice; cook for 3 minutes.
Add soup and shrimp. Cook 5 minutes.
Mix with mayonnaise just before serving.
Makes 2 servings.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream 1 cup sugar and Crisco.
Add molasses, then the egg. Mix well and add all dry ingredients together with creamed mixture.
Form into small balls.
Roll in sugar.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder.
Mix with mixture alternately with chocolate syrup and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Let cool.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Put chopped rhubarb in a greased 12 x 15-inch pan.
Sprinkle sugar and red jello over the top.
Then sprinkle cake mix over the top.
Put thinly sliced margarine over cake mix.
Pour cold water over everything.
Top with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Heat in saucepan, then pour over chicken.
Baste once or twice. Bake covered for 45 minutes, then uncovered for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Mix altogether; roll into small balls and flatten with a fork. Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes at 325°.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Drain and rinse with cold water until completely cool.
In a large salad bowl, thoroughly blend Italian dressing and pepper sauce.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cover and chill.
