Makes 10 side dish servings.

title: diabetic cake
directions: Cook raisins and prunes until tender.
Dredge nuts, raisins and prunes in flour.
Beat eggs and applesauce together.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Crumble cookies into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dribble melted margarine over cookies.
Cut ice cream into slices and arrange over cookie crust, pressing down to make a smooth layer.
Freeze. In double boiler or microwave, heat the margarine with the condensed milk and chocolate syrup until mixture is bubbly.
Cool thoroughly, then pour over ice cream and return pan to freezer until ready to serve.

title: hungry jack casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
Drain.
Add brown sugar, barbecue sauce and pork and beans.
Pour into large casserole.
Top with Hungry Jack biscuits.
Sprinkle cheese over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until biscuits are done.

title: lumpia(egg rolls)
directions: Mix hamburger, onion, carrots and soy sauce; cook until onion and carrots are tender.
Drain.
Put the mixture in a wrapper; roll with the ends, so the mixture doesn't fall out.
Then wet your finger, so the wrapper will seal the roll.
Then fry them until golden brown.
These can be frozen in uncooked stage.

title: sour cherry cupcakes
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs.
Gradually add flour and baking powder, alternating with milk.
Mix well.
Stir in drained cherries.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.

title: cucumber molded salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add remaining ingredients. Chill until set.
Serve with mayonnaise on crisp lettuce.

title: mexican potatoes(serves 24)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Bring 4 cups of water to a boil and add sliced potatoes or steam until almost done, but not breaking apart. Add garlic, salt, bouillon and onion to potatoes before cooking. Pour 1/2 of potatoes into long steam pan.
Cover with cheese and half of chilies.
Top with remaining potatoes and cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and spread with sour cream and egg mixture on top.
Arrange chilies on top and more cheese.
Bake an additional 10 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions until done.
Mix together with remaining ingredients.
Sprinkle more of the bread crumbs across the top and bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: topping for pancakes
directions: Blend supplement, blueberries or strawberries, sweetener and hot water.

title: molded pineapple cheese salad
directions: Heat pineapple.
Add
lemon juice and sugar; stir until dissolved.	Dissolve
gelatin
in
hot
water.
Add gelatin to pineapple mixture.	Chill until it begins to set.
Add 2 types of cheese.
Fold
in cream (do not whip).
More cottage cheese may be added (I use 1 cup).
A very delightful salad.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except tortillas; cut them in fourths. Layer tortillas and mixture alternately, starting with tortillas. Bake at 375°
for 25 minutes.
Last 5 minutes; add grated cheese to top.

title: 5 hour no-peek beef stew
directions: Mix well in a large casserole and cover with foil.
Bake in a 300° oven for 5 hours.

title: orange oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream fat and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, sift salt and soda with flour and add.
Add remaining ingredients, mix well and drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Yields about four dozen.

title: dirt pie
directions: Pour milk into a medium bowl.
Add pudding mix.
Beat with a wire whisk until blended, 1 to 2 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes. Fold in whipped topping.
Stir 1 cup of the cookies into pudding. Pour into pie crust.
Sprinkle with remaining cookies.
Freeze until firm (about 4 hours).

title: caesar salad
directions: In large wooden bowl, mash garlic and anchovy paste with 2 forks until smooth; spread mixture around inside of bowl to season. Add Worcestershire sauce, mustard and egg yolks, mixing constantly. Squeeze the lemon juice into the mixture and add the oil and vinegar.
Toss with lettuce, croutons and Parmesan.
Serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine beaten egg yolks, sugar, milk, water, cocoa and flour in top of double boiler.
Cook until thickened.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Pour into 2 cooked pie shells.

title: zucchini squash bread
directions: Mix first
5 ingredients together, slowly adding flour. Add remaining
ingredients.
Pour
into
greased loaf pans. Bake at 325° for about 1 hour or until done.

title: pudding pie
directions: Cook the pudding as on the box.
Bake pie shell then let cool. Add the pudding to the shell.
Let stand until firm.

title: beef soup
directions: Boil soup bones in Dutch oven with enough water to cover bones.
Boil 2 hours.
Remove bones.
Let cool.

title: skinny chili
directions: Brown meat; drain off fat.
Mix meat and onion and saute until onion is translucent.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and simmer for about 1 1/2 hours.
Remove bay leaf before serving.

title: layered hamburger pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Recipe uses a 9-inch pie pan.
In a bowl, combine beef, egg, bread crumbs, salt, herbs, mustard and garlic powder.
Pat evenly in pan.
Layer with potatoes, onion and mushrooms.
Reserve some mushrooms to garnish pie.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Remove foil, top with cheeses, sprinkle with parsley; arrange reserved mushroom slices around ring of pie.
Return to oven until cheese melts. Serves 6.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Boil macaroni until tender; drain.
Add other ingredients in order listed with exception of eggs.
Add eggs last.
This makes a delicious covered dish and recipe may be doubled if needed.

title: carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix together carrots, sugar, oil, eggs and vanilla, then add salt, cinnamon, flour, baking soda and walnuts.
Mix well.
Bake for 1 1/4 hours.

title: easy shepherd's pie
directions: In skillet, heat margarine.
Cook onion and celery until tender, about 10 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Spoon mixture into 2-quart casserole.
Prepare potatoes according to label directions.
Set aside.
Heat oven to 400°.
Drain liquid from peas and carrots into 1-cup measuring cup.
Add enough water to make 1 cup liquid.
In the same skillet, prepare brown gravy mix as per label, but substitute the vegetable liquid for water.
Add gravy, peas and carrots, ham, salt and basil to onion mixture.
Gently stir until well mixed.
Spoon potatoes in mounds around edge of casserole.
Bake for 30 minutes or until hot and bubbly and potatoes are lightly browned.

title: macaroni and cheese deluxe
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Rinse and set aside.
Combine next six ingredients.
Add macaroni and stir well.
Spoon mixture into greased 2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: rhubarb crunch
directions: Combine flour, oats, brown sugar, butter and cinnamon in a bowl.
Mix until crumbly and press half in greased 9-inch pan. Cover with rhubarb.
Combine granulated sugar, cornstarch, water and vanilla in a small saucepan and cook, stirring until thickened and clear.
Pour over rhubarb and top with remaining crumbs. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.
Cut in squares and serve warm, plain or topped with whipped cream or ice cream. Serves 8.

title: "dolmathes kima me avgolemono" - meat balls with egg lemon sauce
directions: Mix beef, mint, parsley and rice; season with salt and pepper and add 1/4 cup of beef stock.
Mix well and form into walnut-size balls.
Bring remaining stock and water to a boil and drop meat balls into it.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Beat egg yolks; add lemon juice.
Slowly add some of hot stock to egg yolks while continuing to beat.
Stir egg yolk mixture into remaining stock.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes (off the heat).
Makes 4 servings.

title: oatmeal raisin cookies
directions: Beat well and drop on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: coxinhas - chicken croquettes(brazilian finger food)
directions: Boil chicken with seasoning until meat comes off bone.
Skin and debone chicken, breaking meat into small pieces.
Save 1 pint of broth.
Cook potatoes and drain.
Over low heat add 1 pint of broth and whip potatoes.
Next stir in flour until dough no longer sticks to pan.
Dump out onto a floured board and let cool.
Knead in extra flour if sticky.

title: broccoli and cheese sauce
directions: Cook broccoli in microwave until tender, 3 to 4 minutes on High.
In 2-cup Pyrex cup in microwave, melt margarine; stir in flour, then add milk.
Cook 1 minute on High, stir well and cook another 2 1/2 minutes.
Stir in grated Cheddar cheese and pour over drained broccoli.

title: vietnamese lumpia (cha gio)
directions: Soak black fungus in cold water until softened, 30 to 45 minutes.
Drain and finely chop.
There will be about 2 tablespoons; set aside.
To measure bean threads, cut from bunch with kitchen scissors; pack into 1/4-cup measure.
Place bean threads in a bowl and cover with cold water; let stand about 30 minutes or until softened.
Bring 1 1/2 cups of water to boil in a small saucepan.
Add drained bean threads.
Boil 2 minutes; drain and set aside.
Grind pork and shrimp in a meat grinder or food processor until finely chopped.
Place in a medium-size bowl.
Add crab meat, black fungus, bean threads, water chestnuts, green onions, salt and pepper.
Mix thoroughly.
Combine lemon-lime soda and 1 1/2 cups water in a small bowl.
Place 1 rice paper on a flat surface; brush each side lightly with water/soda mixture.
Using your fingertips, soft brush or paper towel or pour liquid in a large dinner plate and dip wrapper in water mixture.
When wrapper has softened, place 2 tablespoons filling above bottom edge. Spread slightly, leaving sides clear.
Fold bottom of wrapper over filling.
Fold sides over filling toward center and roll up to top. Continue until all wrappers are filled.
Heat oil in a wok to 360° or until a 1-inch bread cube turns golden brown in 60 seconds.
Add rolls, a few at a time; fry about 10 minutes or until golden brown, turning as needed.
Drain on paper towels.
To serve, tear off a piece of lettuce.
Place roll half on lettuce and dip in the sauce. Makes 16 rolls.

title: squash patties
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender; drain and mash.
Stir flour into mixture until well blended.
Add Accent, salt and pepper to taste.
Form into patties and fry.

title: mostaccioli salad
directions: Cook mostaccioli until tender; drain and coat with oil.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over coated mostaccioli.

title: zucchini cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients.
In a separate bowl add all dry ingredients.
Then add to other bowl.
Then add zucchini, carrots and nuts.
Bake in a greased loaf pan for 1 hour at 350° or until done.
Makes 2 loaves.
Or bake in 7 mini pans for 50 minutes at 325°.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco.
Add sugar.
Sift flour with 3/4 cup cocoa, baking powder and salt.
Sift this 3 times.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition to butter and sugar mixture.
Beat and add flour mixture.
Add sweet milk and red cake coloring.
Beat well.
Bake in tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Ice with Chocolate Icing.

title: easy fudge
directions: Cook all ingredients except almonds, in double boiler until chocolate is melted.
Add almonds if desired.
Line 9 x 13 pan with aluminum foil. Pour fudge mixture into pan and cool for 1 hour in refrigerator.
Turn out onto board and cut into squares. Makes 48 pieces.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake by package directions.
Cool.
Prepare pudding. Crumble cake and make layers using cake, pineapple, nuts, pie filling and cool whip.
Continue layering until all ingredients are used.
On top layer, use nuts and cool whip.
Use a large bowl or punch bowl.
You may use your favorite pie filling.
You may use cherries or strawberries on top for decorations.

title: zebra stripe cookies
directions: Mix flour, sugars, vanilla, margarine, salt and egg until dough forms.
Divide dough into halves.
Mix cocoa into 1 half. Pat or roll each half into 9-inch square.
Cut each square into three (3-inch) strips.
Cut strips crosswise into halves.

title: turkey gravy
directions: Pour drippings from roasting pan into large measuring cup. Place 4 tablespoons fat from drippings into roasting pan.
Spoon any remaining fat from drippings.
To drippings, add enough liquid to make 4 cupfuls.
Blend flour into fat in roasting pan and stir and heat to brown.
Gradually add liquid, stirring to blend.
Stir and heat to make a smooth gravy.
Add finely chopped cooked giblets, if desired.
Season with salt and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Stir and cook 5 to 10 minutes.
Yield:
4 cups.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake as directed.
Put 1/2 of batter in bottom of pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Heat and melt 14 ounce package caramels, 5 ounce can evaporated milk and 3/4 cup oleo.
When caramels are melted, pour over cake.
Then pour 1 cup nuts, 1 cup chocolate chips and then the rest of batter over this.
Bake another 20 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: eggnog
directions: In a large pan add eggs, sugar and salt; stir in milk and cream.
Cook on low heat.
Add vanilla and nutmeg.
Refrigerate ASAP!

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken breasts until tender.
Cut into pieces and put in bottom of large casserole dish.
Put pieces of margarine over chicken.
Mix soup and chicken broth together.
Add peas and pimentos, chopped.
Pour over chicken.

title: christmas breakfast
directions: Butter the bread and cut into cubes.
Put in the bottom of a 9x13 inch baking dish.
Brown the sausage.
Drain and crumble over the bread.
Put cheese over the sausage and bread.
Mix together eggs, half & half, salt and dry mustard.
Pour over the cheese. Cover and refrigerate overnight (8 hours).
Heat oven to 350°. Bake for 40-50 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve with biscuits and fresh fruit.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Bake pie crust.
Mix cocoa, sugar and flour together.
Add beaten egg yolks, milk and vanilla.
Cook in a saucepan until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar and flavoring; beat well.
Spread on top and bake until golden brown.

title: chocolate trifle
directions: Bake cake as directed, using 2 round 8 or 9-inch pans. Prepare chocolate pudding as directed.
Cut each cake layer in half (you will have four round layers).
Place first layer in bottom of trifle bowl.
Sprinkle with Kahlua.
Cover with 1/4 of pudding.
Cover with 1/4 of whipped topping.
Sprinkle with crushed Heath bars.
Repeat until you use all ingredients.
Chill and serve.

title: applesauce ornaments
directions: Mix cinnamon and applesauce together.
Roll in ball. Place in plastic.
Chill for one hour.
Roll out to 1/4-inch thick.
Use cookie cutters to cut out desired shapes.
Use straw to make hole for ribbon to hang.
Air dry on cooling rack for a few days until dry.
Decorate with ribbon, miniature pom pom balls and anything else in your scrap box.

title: pear mincemeat
directions: Wash, cut, press through sieve.
Measure pulp.
For each cup of pulp, use 1 cup sugar.
Heat, stirring constantly 20 minutes. Cook slow, do not boil.
Pour into sterile jars, leaving 1/4-inch headspace.
Adjust scalded lids and place in boiling water bath for 10 minutes.
One cup pulp equals 1/2 pint jam.

title: pasta salad
directions: Mix in blender oil, garlic, salt, pepper, mayonnaise and red wine vinegar.
Chill for 1 hour.
Cook pasta.
Cook vegetables halfway.
Mix all together.
You may use all of oil mixture.
If you do not, it freezes well.

title: blackberry cobbler
directions: Preheat oven to 425° degrees.
Heat the berries, sugar and flour together in a saucepan.
Add the lemon rind, cinnamon and cardamom, stir.
Sift together the cake flour, baking powder, salt and sugar.
Cut in the butter with a pastry cutter or fork, until the mixture has the consistency of cornmeal.
Add the cream, stir with a fork, and turn dough onto a floured board.
Knead lightly for 1/2 minute.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Soak beans overnight; brown sausage, onion and peppers (drain grease).
Add all ingredients together in crock-pot and add water to top of crock.
Cook on high for 10 hours.
Take lid off at 5 hours.
The more you stir, the thicker your beans will be.
Serve over rice.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture.
Add milk, bananas and nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato cake
directions: Mix potatoes, oil and sugar in a bowl.
Add 1 egg at a time to mixture.
Mix well after each egg.
Sift cinnamon with flour and add slowly to egg mixture.
Stir in nuts.
Pour mixture into greased and floured 9-inch cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Cool completely before frosting.

title: stella's ginger cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Sift dry ingredients and add to first mixture.
Chill several hours.
Form into 1-inch ball and roll in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: michigan sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients with tomato sauce, adding hamburger. Cook for 2 hours.

title: pork shoulder with ham
directions: Place shoulder in a baking pan with little water, put more seasoning on top and cover pan.
Bake at 350° for 3-4 hours.

title: crispy baked fillets
directions: Wash and dry fillets.
Season and dip in oil.
Coat with cornflake crumbs.
Arrange in single layers on a rack on a cookie sheet that has turned up edges.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
(I like crappie best.)

title: lemon cool whip cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients (except powdered sugar) with mixer.
Roll a spoonful of dough in powdered sugar.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 350° in preheated oven for 7 to 8 minutes.
May be made with any flavor cake mix.

title: houston summer salad
directions: Break spaghetti into thirds.
Boil and rinse in cold water. Mix salad dressing and 1/2 jar of Salad Supreme Seasoning; add spaghetti and diced vegetables.
Mix and chill.

title: brown sugar ham
directions: Place ham in baking dish.
Stud with cloves.
Combine sugar, bread crumbs and mustard in a small bowl.
Spread mixture on top of ham and press firmly.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave 10 minutes on High.
Rotate dish 1/2 turn.
Microwave 25 minutes on Roast.
Let stand 10 minutes, covered, with aluminum foil.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onions. Drain.
Pour into buttered casserole dish. Cover with layer of French fried onions, layer of cheese and can of mushroom soup (not diluted).
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: diet mayonnaise
directions: Mix all ingredients well in blender.
Use sparingly.

title: peanut butter potato chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream butter and sugars until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat until smooth. Add flour; stir until a soft dough forms.
Stir in peanut butter chips and potato chips.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls 1-inch apart onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until edges are light brown.
Transfer to a wire rack to cool completely.
Store in an airtight container.
Yield:
about 8 dozen cookies.

title: cornish hens
directions: Defrost hens completely; rub pan with margarine in plastic bag.
Shake the hen halves in Shake 'n Bake; put hens skin side up in pan.
Put salt, paprika and garlic powder on top, then cut 2 lumps of butter on each half.
Bake in 375° oven for 1 hour.
Good with spiced rice.

title: diabetic savory cheese pie(contains 351 calories)
directions: Spread 1/2 teaspoon of butter over the bottom of an individual casserole.
Place 1/4 cup of mashed potatoes in casserole.
Cover with one-half the amount of milk.
Sprinkle with pepper and salt as desired.
Mix the grated cheese, chopped and minced onion and walnut mixture to the remaining milk.
Pour over the mashed potatoes in the casserole.
Spread the mixture evenly.
Cover with the remaining potatoes and bake in a moderate oven until lightly browned.
Serve at once.

title: butterscotch bavarian cream
directions: Beat eggs with salt; add milk and cook until of custard consistency.
Pour cold water in a bowl and sprinkle gelatin on top of water.
Add to hot custard and stir until dissolved.
Cook brown sugar and butter together for 2 moments and add to hot custard.
Cool and when mixture begins to thicken, fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.

title: salmon scramble
directions: Drain and flake salmon into a bowl. Fold in eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Melt butter in skillet over low heat. Slowly pour salmon mixture into skillet. Continue stirring until eggs are done, but not dry. Add paprika.

title: cabbage and pork sausage
directions: Shred cabbage coarsely; place in saucepan with stock and salt. Saute onion in butter until limp.
Add to cabbage; cover and cook slowly until cabbage is tender.
Add sour cream.
Blend in flour, white pepper, nutmeg and sugar.
Heat.
Serve with pork sausages, allowing 3 per serving.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, corn syrup, salt and vanilla.
Add butter and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Makes 2 (9-inch) pies.

title: vermont corn chowder
directions: In saucepan, melt butter.
Saute onions and celery until tender.
Add cooked potatoes, milk and corn.
Heat to serving temperature.
Add cheese until melted.
Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle a little parsley.
Tastes better next day when flavors blend.
Serves 7.

title: fat-free pancakes
directions: Using mixer on lowest setting, combine flour, eggs, milk and applesauce.
Once all the ingredients are moist, increase speed of mixer.
Add cinnamon and mix thoroughly.
Add blueberries last and hand-stir only, to ensure berries are intact.
Spray frying surface with Pam and cook slowly to ensure centers are well cooked. Topping is your choice.
They're good as is.

title: taco salad
directions: Core, rinse and drain lettuce well.
Chop into bite sized pieces in a large bowl.
Add tomatoes, onions, olives, avocado, ground meat, kidney beans and grated cheese.
Mix dressing and taco sauce together and toss with salad.
Just before serving add corn chips, toss and serve.
Serves 6.

title: creamy cheese ball
directions: Let cheeses soften to room temperature.
Mix all ingredients well until blended. Cover bowl with plastic wrap and refrigerate until firm.
Form into 1 large or 2 small balls. Roll in chopped walnuts.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Put popcorn in a large 4-inch deep buttered baking pan (like a roaster).
Keep popcorn warm in oven. Combine sugar, syrup, water, butter and salt in saucepan.
Stir over medium heat until sugar is dissolved.
Cook until mixture reaches 250° on candy thermometer, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat and immediately stir in vanilla. Remove popcorn from oven.
Pour syrup mixture over popcorn, stirring to mix well. Form into balls.
(Make sure hands are well buttered; popcorn will be very hot and very sticky.)
Makes approximately 8 large or 12 to 14 small.

title: chocolate oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix the butter, sugar, milk, cocoa and Nestle Quik together and boil for 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Add and dissolve 1/2 cup peanut butter, then add oatmeal and mix.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper and let cool.

title: sparkling pineapple punch
directions: Heat sugar, water and cinnamon to boiling; reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes. Cover and refrigerate at least 2 hours or until chilled.

title: grilled lemon chicken
directions: In a small saucepan, combine butter, lemon juice, water, soy sauce, paprika, honey, cayenne pepper, mustard, garlic and salt. Heat until butter melts, stirring well.
Place chicken in a shallow dish and pour mixture over chicken.
Marinate about 1 hour.
Grill the chicken over medium-hot coals for about 15 minutes per side.
Brush frequently with the marinade.

title: coconut sour cream cake
directions: Prepare cake according to package directions.
Make 2 (8-inch) layers.
Split both layers horizontally after they cool.
Blend together sugar, sour cream and coconut.
Chill.
Spread all (but 1 cup) between the four layers.
Blend the remaining cup of mixture with the whip cream.
Spread on top and side of cake.
Seal in airtight container.
Keep refrigerated for three days before serving.
Keep in airtight container and refrigerated after cutting.

title: oyster dressing
directions: Saute onion and celery in 1/2 cup butter until tender. Combine well with bread cubes, cornbread, eggs and oysters.
Add enough broth to moisten dressing.
Spoon in a greased 9-inch square baking dish and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Drain pineapple.
Melt butter in 9-inch square pan.
Remove from heat and stir in brown sugar.
Arrange pineapple and cherries. Prepare cake mix as directed on package and pour over.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until done.
Loosen edges, cover with serving plate, turn over and lift off pan.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: For Chocolate Flavored Fudge, add 1 large package chocolate chips to first part of mixture.

title: zucchini lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Pour Egg Beaters and water into bowl; mix.
In another bowl, put Kellogg's Corn Flakes crumbs.
Slice zucchini.
Dip slices in egg, then in crumbs.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 1/2 hour.
Layer 1/2 of the zucchini, sauce and cheese in casserole dish.
Layer remaining ingredients. Bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well!
Pour in pie crust.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: corn and pepper hash
directions: Place peppers and onion in microwave-safe 2-quart casserole dish.
Stir to combine and cover tightly with plastic wrap, venting edge.
Microwave on High 6 to 8 minutes or until peppers and onion are tender.
Mix in corn and cumin.
Re-cover and microwave on High 4 to 6 minutes more until heated through. Drain.
Season with salt and pepper, and serve.

title: hot bacon dressing
directions: In a glass 2 cup measure, beat egg slightly and add other ingredients.
Mix well.
Microwave, uncovered, 2 minutes or until thickened, stirring every 30 seconds.

title: annette richards chicken breasts
directions: Combine dry ingredients.
Melt butter.
Dip chicken into butter until coated, one piece at a time, then dip chicken into dry mixture.
Roll chicken into balls.
Place in buttered baking dish.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: slaw
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in saucepan.
Bring to a boil approximately 1 minute.
Cool and strain.
Shred cabbage and onion.
Pour sauce over cabbage and onion.
Chill.
This will keep in refrigerator for 3 to 4 days.

title: cecilia's potato casserole
directions: Pour 1/2 cup melted margarine into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish. Add 1/2 package of frozen hash browns.
Mix soup, sour cream, milk and green onions in a separate bowl.
Pour 1/2 of mixture over hash browns.
Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese on top.
Add remainder of mixture and hash browns on top.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top, then cover with crushed corn flakes.
Drizzle 2 tablespoons melted margarine on top.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: cauliflower casserole
directions: Place cauliflower and a small amount of water in a saucepan. Cover and cook for 5 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain. Combine cauliflower, sour cream, cheddar cheese, cornflakes, peppers, and salt.
Transfer to a greased 2 qt. baking dish. Sprinkle with Parmesan Cheese and Paprika.
Bake uncovered at 325 degrees for 30 - 35 minutes or until heated through.
Yield 6 - 8 servings.

title: no-fuss lasagna
directions: In a large saucepan, brown ground beef; drain.
In a bowl, combine eggs with cottage cheese, half of the cheddar cheese and half of the mozzarella cheese.
Set aside.
Combine beef and spaghetti sauce.
Spoon 1/3 of the meat sauce into a 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking pan.
Place half of the uncooked noodles over sauce. Top with 1/3 of meat sauce and press down.
Spoon cottage cheese mixture over all.
Cover with remaining noodles and meat sauce. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 1 hour.
Uncover, sprinkle with remaining cheddar and mozzarella cheeses.
Bake an additional 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Serves 8.

title: panic pie
directions: Put cherry pie filling in lightly greased cake pan (I spray with Pam).
Sprinkle cake mix over filling.
Dot generously with butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: tamale pie
directions: In a saucepan, bring 3 cups water to a boil.
Meanwhile, combine cold water, corn meal and 1 teaspoon salt.
Pour into boiling water, stirring constantly.
Cook until thickened, then cover and continue cooking 10 to 12 minutes.
Stir occasionally. Start heating oven to 350°.
Butter a 10-inch juice-saver pie plate.
In large skillet, saute onion in butter until tender and golden.
Add ground meat.
Brown beef, stirring constantly with fork.

title: italian green beans
directions: Combine all ingredients and boil on medium heat until most of liquid is gone.

title: jello cake
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add cold water and set aside.
Bake cake according to directions.
Cool cake 20 to 25 minutes.
Use a fork and poke holes in cake 1/2-inch apart.
Pour jello in holes.
Top with Cool Whip and refrigerate.

title: sunshine salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and salt with 4 cups of boiling water.
Cool in refrigerator about 20 minutes, then add marshmallows.
Stir. Add bananas and crushed pineapple.
Return to refrigerator while making topping, so that mixture will be completely cool before adding topping.

title: fried rice
directions: Cook Minute rice according to package directions.
Fry bacon in skillet, remove and drain on paper towels.
Saute chopped vegetables in bacon drippings until tender-crisp.
Crumble bacon and return to skillet with vegetables.
Add cooked rice, stir and sprinkle with soy sauce to season.
Make well in mixture and scramble egg in well.
Mix well and serve.

title: oil and vinegar dressing
directions: Combine vinegar and dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Gradually beat in oil. Pour into bottle.
Shake well. Makes about 1 cup dressing.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake(earthquake cake)
directions: Mix coconut and pecans; place in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Prepare cake mix as directed on the box.
Pour into pan over pecans and coconut.
Heat and stir margarine and cream cheese until warm and creamy.
Add sugar; mix well.
Spoon on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Flip each serving over as you serve.
Very good.

title: curry chicken delight
directions: Rinse chicken, pat dry.
Coat chicken with flour.
Set aside. In large skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Drain bacon on paper towels, reserving drippings in skillet.
Crumble bacon.
Set aside. In same skillet, brown chicken on both sides about 10 minutes. Place chicken in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine honey, mustard, salt and curry powder.
Drizzle honey mixture over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes more.
Top chicken with crumbled bacon. Serves 8.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix together cottage cheese, pineapple and dry Jell-O.
Add Cool Whip and mix well.
Refrigerate.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Have pie crust ready.
Melt margarine. Add sugar and salt.
Add flour and milk.
Add beaten eggs, Karo syrup and vanilla.
Stir well.
Add pecans.
Pour into pie crust and bake 30 to 40 minutes or until set in middle.

title: fried corn
directions: Fry bacon crisp; drain and crumble.
Place both corns, bacon crumbs, green peppers and pimentos over medium heat until it starts to simmer.
Add sugar, pepper and salt.
Stir frequently. Reduce heat.
After it starts to simmer, continue to cook 15 to 20 minutes.

title: banana cake(old recipe is more like a bread)
directions: Cream sugar and shortening, then add eggs and mix.
Add all the rest and stir together.
Pour in a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Check for doneness.

title: cheese straws
directions: Knead well. Use any size cookie press and bake on greased tins at 275° for 30 or 40 minutes. DO NOT BROWN.

title: pork medallions with green peppercorn sauce(serves 8)
directions: Flatten pork slightly with palm of hand.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Spray large skillet with cooking spray and heat over medium-high heat.

Add pork and cook until brown, about 3 minutes per side. Transfer to plate. Add shallots to same skillet and saute for 2 minutes. Add vermouth and boil until reduced to glaze, about 5 minutes. Add chicken broth, peppercorns and minced thyme and boil until reduced to 3/4 cup, about 10 minutes. Whisk in mustard, then cream.
Season with salt and pepper. Return pork and collected juices on plate to skillet.
Simmer until pork is cooked and sauce thickens slightly, about 3 minutes. Divide among plates. Sprinkle with fresh thyme leaves and serve.

title: cracklin bread
directions: Take 1 quart sifted corn meal and a tea cup of cracklins.
Rub the batter in the meal as fine as you can.
Add salt and make up with warm water into a stiff dough.
Make into pones.
Bake and eat hot.

title: cheese dip
directions: Pour 2 cups boiling water over dried beef while preparing other ingredients.	Blot beef with paper towels and chop into small pieces.
Mix all ingredients and form into a ball.
Chill. Best when served with Wheat Thins.

title: spinach quiche
directions: Mix spinach and celery with eggs, milk and Feta cheese.
Put in pie crust.
Slice tomatoes; cut in half and place on uncooked quiche.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes.

title: vidalia onion deep dish
directions: Cook rice in a large pot of boiling water for 5 minutes. Drain well.
Melt butter in saucepan.
Add onions; cook, stirring, until tender.
Mix cheese and cream.
Add rice, parsley, salt and pepper.
Place in a greased buttered casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake one hour at 325°.

title: pineapple cookie sheet cake
directions: Mix ingredients by hand.
Bake at 350° in a large jelly roll pan for approximately 25 to 30 minutes.
Cool.

title: cranberry bread
directions: In a bowl, stir together the flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and baking soda.
Make a well in the center of this flour mixture. Add the egg, orange juice and butter; stir just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° until bread is golden brown on top and a wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean (about 45 minutes).
Turn out onto rack; let cool completely.
Enjoy!!
Yields 1 loaf.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/4 batter into a well-greased 8 x 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle cheese over top and then add remaining batter.
Bake at 375° until golden brown.

title: fried wild turkey breast
directions: Dip
turkey
strips
into egg batter and roll in flour. Fry in	an
electric
fryer
on approximately 200° to 225° in cooking oil.
Salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly turning only	one time while cooking.
Make sure that a fork is easily inserted into the turkey to make sure it is done.

title: spaghetti salad("a summer delight")
directions: Combine cucumbers, tomatoes, bottled salad dressing and Schilling Salad Supreme to cooked spaghetti.
Mix.
Refrigerate until chilled.

title: cream of potato soup
directions: Saute onions.
Dice potatoes.
Cover potatoes and onion with water.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cook until mushy.
Add soup, milk and cheese.
Mix and heat on low until cheese is melted.

title: molasses taffy
directions: Boil first 3 ingredients to hard ball stage.
Add fat, soda and salt.
Remove from fire; stir until soda is blended and pour into greased tins.
When cool, pull between ungreased fingertips until candy is white in color and stiff.
Cut in 1-inch pieces.
Wrap in oil paper.

title: hawaiian loaf bread
directions: Drain pineapple well.
Beat cream cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sugar until smooth.
Blend in vanilla.
Beat in egg.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture alternately with sour cream.
Stir in pineapple and nuts.
Turn into greased 9-inch or two (7-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes for small pan, 70 minutes for larger pans.
Cool on rack 10 minutes.
Remove from pans.
Cool overnight before slicing.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Mix jello with cottage cheese; add pineapple, marshmallows and Cool Whip.

title: honey beets
directions: Place beet juice in saucepan.
Add vinegar, honey and cornstarch; bring to a boil.
Add beets; simmer for 5 minutes. Contains no fat.
One-half cup contains 45 calories.

title: romanian bread with milk(piine cu lapte)
directions: Mix the sugar with yeast in a small bowl. When it reaches the consistency of sour cream, add 2-3 Tbsp. of warm milk, a little flour, mix well and cover with a cloth, leave it until it rises. Take a larger bowl and place the warm milk, salt and dough (after it rises). Add flour and knead, adding a little oil as you knead. Knead until bubbly. Cover with towel and leave in warm place to rise up. After dough has doubled in size, place in greased baking pan, shape dough into a log. Allow dough to rise again after handling it. Preheat oven to 250F while dough rises. Bake at 250F until the dough starts to rise in pan, after it rises increase heat to 350F and bake to a light golden brown on top.

title: brown-bag s'mores
directions: In a heavy saucepan, melt chocolate over low heat.
Stir in milk and vanilla; cook and stir until smooth.
Making 1 S'more at a time, spread 1 tablespoon of the chocolate mixture on two whole graham crackers.
Place 5 to 6 marshmallows on one cracker; gently press the other cracker on top.
Repeat with remaining chocolate, crackers and marshmallows.
Wrap with plastic wrap; store at room temperature.

title: congo squares
directions: Beat eggs.
Combine remaining ingredients and bake in greased pan for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: american swiss steak
directions: Combine 1/4 cup flour, 1 teaspoon salt, dry mustard and 1/4 teaspoon pepper.
Spread half of mixture over one side of steak. Pound in with side of saucer or mallet.
Repeat other side of steak.

title: holiday fruit dessert
directions: Mix together well.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Serve in chilled sherbets or desserts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: sunday glazed carrots
directions: Cut carrots in 1/2-inch slices.
Place in 1 1/2-quart casserole with margarine and brown sugar.
Cover and cook in microwave oven 10 minutes.
(Stir after 5 minutes.)

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix well the pretzels, oleo and 1/3 cup sugar. Put in 3-quart Pyrex long pan greased with butter. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Cream together cream cheese and 1/2 cup sugar. Add Cool Whip. Spread over cooled crust. Dissolve strawberry jello in hot pineapple juice. Add sliced frozen strawberries and drained crushed pineapple and bananas. Pour over creamed mixture. Refrigerate.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Let set in a 9 x 13-inch pan
Mix the rest of ingredients together and put on top of jello part. Refrigerate.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together until smooth. Serve with sliced apples, bananas, strawberries or any fruit.

title: granny's peanut brittle
directions: Cook all ingredients together. Add 1 teaspoon soda after the mixture reaches 290°.
Stir well and pour on greased foil in a thin layer.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Add rest of ingredients; mix together and use 1/2 for first layer.
Use an extra large Pyrex dish.

title: easy crock-pot beef stew
directions: Wash, peel and chop first 4 ingredients.
Place into crock-pot.
Add rest of ingredients and mix well.
Cook on crock-pot on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Feeds 6.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Set aside.
Boil together oleo, cocoa, water and shortening in a saucepan.
Pour cocoa mixture over dry ingredients and beat well.
Add buttermilk, eggs, soda and vanilla.
Thoroughly mix.
Grease and flour an 11 x 16-inch cookie sheet.
Bake 20 minutes at 400°.

title: deviled eggs
directions: Cut boiled eggs lengthwise.
Put yolks in small bowl.
Mix all ingredients except mayonnaise.
Stir in enough mayonnaise to moisten well.
Fill eggs; sprinkle with paprika.

title: pizza snack
directions: Press biscuits flat on cookie sheet.
Top biscuits with cheese and pizza sauce.
Bake at 425° until biscuits are done.

title: low calorie fruit and vegetable salad
directions: Toss first 6 ingredients together.
Combine salad dressing, orange juice and poppy seed and shake well.
Chill.
When ready to serve salad, pour dressing over all and toss.

title: sausage potato casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Line bottom of casserole with sliced potatoes.
In saucepan, heat soup and water until smooth; add cheese and stir until melted.
Add sausage pieces, green peppers and pimento.
Pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake for 55 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: homemade pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan over medium heat, and stir until thick.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake at 325° for one hour.

title: roly polies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Beat in the eggs.
Add flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Chill dough.
Roll into small balls.
Roll each in a mixture of 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon cinnamon.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 350°.

title: mashed turnips
directions: In a saucepan of boiling water, cook turnips for 2 minutes; drain. Cover with water and cook for 20 minutes or until tender; drain. Mash them in another container.

title: pizza meat loaf
directions: Combine all except cheese.
Mix thoroughly.
Divide in thirds. Put 1/3 in bottom, then layer of cheese, layer of ground beef, etc., in a 9 1/2 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Pour fat out of pan halfway through recipe.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream the shortening, sugar and eggs.
Make paste of food coloring and cocoa. Combine salt with vanilla and add to buttermilk.
Add alternately with flour to creamed mixture.
Mix soda with vinegar and fold into batter mixture.
Use 3 pans, wax paper lined.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or less.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: peanut butter cups
directions: Combine crumbs, butter,
peanut butter and sugar;
work until smooth.
Press into
buttered
pan,
1/2 x 13-inches. Melt chocolate chips over
hot
water, spread over mixture and cool. Cut in squares.

title: pink cole slaw
directions: Quarter and core cabbage.
Slice into thin slivers.
Place in large bowl.
Cover with ice water.
Refrigerate one hour.
Drain well.
Add beet, onion, carrots, sugar and salt to drained cabbage.
Toss.
Combine mayonnaise, sour cream, lemon juice and pepper in small bowl.
Stir well.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Toss to coat vegetables.
Cover.
Refrigerate several hours. Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Melt butter and brown sugar in cast-iron skillet.
Arrange pineapple and cherries on top.
Mix eggs and sugar together; add flour and remaining ingredients.
Beat egg whites until stiff. Fold into batter.
Pour over brown sugar mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or less until done.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix ingredients in order given.
Place in 2 (9-inch) pie plates and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
Lower temperature and finish baking at 375°.
Do not overbake.

title: garlic bread
directions: Slice bread.
Melt margarine in a small saucepan, then add garlic, cheese and pepper.
Spread on both sides of bread and then put loaf back together and wrap tightly in foil.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes, turning once so that margarine will soak through.

title: pralines
directions: Cook first 4 ingredients until full rolling boil.
Add 1/2 stick margarine and 10 large marshmallows.
Continue to stir on heat until marshmallows melt.
Remove from heat and beat until it thickens.
Add vanilla and pecans.
Drop on wax paper.

title: banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Mix oil, sugar and egg whites; mix well.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to oil mixture, alternating with the buttermilk.
Add banana, nuts and vanilla, beating after each addition.
Pour into 2 (9-inch) pans sprayed with nonstick spray.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat eggs until very light.
Beat in sugar, salt and vanilla. Melt margarine in hot milk and beat into mixture.
Sift together flour and baking powder and beat into mixture very quickly.
Pour immediately into prepared 9 x 13-inch sheet pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°, or until top springs back when lightly touched or comes away from sides of pan.
Cool.
Serve in squares topped with sliced strawberries.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Place in loaf pan.
Cover with strips of bacon. Pour over; add tomato sauce.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours or until done.

title: seafood rigatoni
directions: Cook pasta according to box instructions.
Shell and devein shrimp.
Wash scallops.
In a 10 x 16-inch glass casserole, put layer of pasta, layer of seafood sauce and cheese.
Repeat one more time.
Bake in a 400° oven until cheese is melted and lightly browned, about 30 to 45 minutes.
Let cool about 20 minutes before cutting into sections and serving.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together first 5 ingredients.
Add oil.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add carrots, nuts and vanilla.
Bake in 3 round pans at 350° until cake is done.
Ice cake with cream cheese icing.

title: macaroni and tomatoes
directions: Cook macaroni according to package directions.
Do not overcook.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Bring to a boil, then serve hot.

title: old timey peanut butter crisscross cookies
directions: Cream shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Sift dry ingredients.
Stir into creamed mixture.
Mix well.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on one large cookie sheet.
Bake as directed. Cool.
Mix cream cheese, Ranch mix and mayonnaise; spread on crust.
Clean and chop vegetables in food processor.
Spread on top of cheese mixture.
Cut and keep refrigerated.

title: new year's crabmeat casserole
directions: Cook green pepper in butter until tender.
Stir in flour. Combine soup, milk and pepper and gradually stir into flour mixture. Cook until smooth and thickened, stirring constantly. Add 1 3/4 cups of cheese and crabmeat and blend.
Pour into casserole. Top with bread crumbs and 1/4 cup Cheddar cheese. Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pineapple meat loaf
directions: In a large bowl, combine beef, onion, bell pepper, egg, crushed crackers, 1/2 cup catsup and 1/2 cup pineapple.
Press in a loaf pan.
Sprinkle with remaining pineapple.
Combine 1/3 cup catsup and pineapple juice.
Pour over meat loaf.
Bake at 425° for 1 hour.
(Bake covered for the first 30 minutes.)
Serves 4 to 6.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Mix last
5 ingredients together and bring to a boil to dissolve sugar.
Let cool while vegetables are draining.
Pour over vegetables and marinate overnight, the longer the better.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Grate the cheese and spread over the sausage.
Mix the Bisquick, eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over grated cheese. Bake in a 400° oven for 30 minutes.

title: heavenly pineapple mold
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add pineapple juice and lemon juice. Chill until slightly thick. Fold in drained, crushed pineapple, cheese and whipped cream. Pour into 1 1/2-quart mold; chill until firm. Unmold. Must do ahead.

title: lisa's breakfast casserole
directions: This must be prepared the night before.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, crumble bread slices to cover bottom.
Fry sausage and drain completely on paper towels.
Layer sausage on top of bread.
Beat eggs with milk; pour over all.
Cover top with shredded cheese. Chill overnight.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix together and bake at 325° for 25 minutes; let cool.

title: apple cider punch
directions: Heat and let simmer for 20 minutes.

title: gooey cake
directions: Mix cake mix, butter, egg and water.
Press into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Batter will be stiff.
Stir together pineapple, coconut and pecans.
Press onto first layer.
Mash cream cheese.
Stir in eggs, powdered sugar and pour over first two layers.
Bake
at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes or until top is golden brown.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: better than sex cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Mix cake mix, pudding mix, eggs, sour cream and water until well blended. Fold in grated German chocolate and chocolate chips.
Bake for 55 to 60 minutes.

title: beef and chow mein noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add green pepper and simmer until tender.
In separate pan, cook celery, onion, salt and water until celery is tender.
Add mushroom soup; blend well, add to meat mixture.
Add 1/3 chow mein noodles to meat mixture.
Pour into a buttered casserole.
Sprinkle remaining noodles on top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: In 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup and milk.
Stir in beans and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken south texas
directions: Boil chicken in lightly salted water until tender.
Remove bone and cut into 1-inch pieces.
Dip tortillas in the hot broth and place in bottom of 3-quart casserole dish.
Layer all the ingredients, beginning with all the chicken.

title: broccoli, rice and cheese casserole
directions: Stir onion in margarine until tender.
Turn off heat and add cheese soup; melt.
Add chosen soup, rice and broccoli; mix and bake in 350° oven until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut into bite size pieces.
Grease a 9 x 14-inch casserole.
Place layers of broccoli, then chicken. Combine soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Pour over chicken and broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese, bread crumbs and margarine.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Heat milk and pour over first 4 ingredients.
Fold in beaten eggs.
Drain Veg-All and stir in.
Cover top with corn flake crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: best peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Cream shortening, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in peanut butter.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Drop by teaspoons into granulated sugar.
Put on baking parchment lined (or ungreased) cookie sheet.
Press with back of floured fork to make crisscross. Bake in 350° oven for about 10 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen cookies.

title: five hour stew
directions: Combine all ingredients in roaster pan and cover and bake at 250° for 5 hours.
You can also put in slow cooker or in Dutch oven on stove at 300° for 5 hours.
Serves with biscuits or rolls.

title: jack-o-lantern burgers
directions: Make hamburger patties and fry or cook over charcoal grill. Take one slice of cheese for each burger and cut round with a drinking glass or biscuit cutter.
With a knife, cut out jack-o-lantern faces in round cheese.
Lay "face" on top of cooked burger barely melting cheese (can be done in the microwave).
Makes spooky burgers for Halloween!

title: sausage-cheese quiche
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook two 9-inch pie shells for 5 minutes.
Pour mixture into shells.
Cook at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 325° for 40 minutes.
Can be frozen for later use.

title: picnic punch
directions: Combine punch, lemonade concentrate and cranberry juice.
Mix well.
Add ice cubes and orange slices.
Makes approximately 14 servings (4 ounces each).

title: nun's cake
directions: Mix dates and soda with hot water and set aside to cool. Cream oleo and sugar; add eggs and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix well, then stir in vanilla and date mixture.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch pan or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and nuts over top.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350°. Keeps well.
Can dress this up with topping of Cool Whip.

title: tomato pie
directions: Drain cut-up tomatoes well.
Lay in pie shell.
Put spices over the tomatoes.
Mix onion, cheese and mayonnaise and top the tomatoes.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes uncovered.
Cover and bake 45 minutes longer.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar.
Add egg yolks, beaten until light colored.
Sift together dry ingredients and add alternately to creamed mixture with milk and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 10 minutes.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add beaten eggs.
Add sifted dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture, alternately with milk and vanilla.
Grease and flour a 10-inch tube pan or spray with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: turkey or chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except chips.
Place in greased dish and cover top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: vegetable cheese bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place thawed vegetables in 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Mix soup, milk and cheese together and pour over vegetables.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake 30 minutes or until bubbling.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix lightly.
Place in a greased 1 1/2 to 2-quart casserole and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream
sugar,
oil
and shortening; add vanilla and egg yolks; beat well.
Add buttermilk alternately with flour, soda and salt that
has
been
sifted
together.
Beat egg whites stiff and combine
with batter.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) cake pans for 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and frost.

title: ground turkey meatballs
directions: Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: peanut butter play dough
directions: Mix peanut butter and powdered milk together thoroughly.
Give to the kids and let them have a ball.

title: anson's favorite french fried okra
directions: Turn deep fryer on first so oil will be hot when needed.
Mix cornmeal mix and flour together in a Ziploc bag.
Place partly thawed okra, egg, milk, salt and pepper into a bowl and toss until thoroughly coated.
When oil is real hot, spoon 1/2 of the coated okra into the Ziploc bag of cornmeal and flour and shake.
Put the breaded okra in deep fryer and cook until golden brown.

title: susan's meatballs and rice
directions: Roll meat mixture into large balls. Brown on all sides (about 20 to 30 minutes). Add soup, milk and cooked rice. Cook about 1/2 hour more.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Combine mushrooms and rice in a greased slow cooker.
Mix well.
Layer chicken breasts on top of mixture and sprinkle with onion soup mix.
Cover and cook on low 4-6 hours.

title: easy green bean casserole
directions: Combine ingredients.
Mix and heat in a greased casserole dish for 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Serves 4.

title: po' boys
directions: Preheat pan to medium heat.
Melt butter; saute onion and garlic.
Simmer for 2 to 3 minutes.
Add celery, peppers and jalapeno.
Sprinkle with seasoning (use only 1/2; will season more later); simmer for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and refrigerate, uncovered, to cool (before adding uncooked shrimp).
Grind shrimp in meat grinder.
Combine everything; season with remaining seasoning.
Mix well; form eight 3 1/2-inch (3/4-inch thick) patties.
Cover; refrigerate until ready to use.
Heat oven to 225° and toast bread.
Grill patties and baste with Worcestershire sauce.
Sprinkle with grated Swiss cheese, if desired.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage, stirring until crumbly.
Drain.
Beat eggs and milk in bowl.
Add sausage and remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: bean casserole
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Cook beans; drain (reserve small amount).
Add tomatoes, sauce and onion.
Mix all ingredients together and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: brat kabobs or beef kabobs
directions: You will need skewers.

title: dinner rolls
directions: Mix all together and let rise.
Shape into rolls and let rise again.
Bake about 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Spread tops of warm rolls with butter and serve.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix all ingredients in a bowl at room temperature for 10 minutes.
Place mixture into graham cracker crust and freeze for 2 hours.
Then refrigerate before serving.

title: pasta with roasted eggplant and peppers
directions: Cut bell peppers in half lengthwise; discard seeds and membranes.
Place peppers, skin side up, on a foil lined baking sheet.
Flatten with palm of hand.
Broil peppers 3-inches from heat for 10 minutes or until blackened and charred.
Place peppers in ice water and chill 5 minutes.
Drain peppers; peel and discard skins.
Cut peppers into julienne strips; set aside.

title: oven clam chowder
directions: Saute onion in butter or margarine.
Add all other ingredients and bake for 4 hours at 275°.
Makes 7 quarts.

title: salmon patties
directions: Flake salmon, mashing the bone well.
Mix all ingredients together.
Form into 8 or 9 patties.
Brown in 1/4 ?? oil over medium heat for about 15 minutes.

title: scotch eggs
directions: Dust the eggs with seasoned flour.
(Season the flour with your favorite spices.)
Add a few drops of the sauce to the sausage meat and divide into 4 equal portions.
Form each quarter into a flat cake and work it around the egg, making it as even as possible to keep the egg a good shape and making sure there are no cracks in the sausage meat.
Brush with beaten egg and toss in the breadcrumbs.
Heat the fat until it will brown a cube of bread in 40 to 50 seconds.

(As the sausage meat is raw, it is essential that the frying should not be hurried unduly, as the fat must not get too hot and the sausage must get cooked all the way through.) Fry the eggs for about 7 to 8 minutes. When they are golden brown on the outside, remove them from the fat and drain on crumpled kitchen paper.
Cut the eggs in half lengthwise. Garnish each half with a small piece of parsley and serve either hot with tomato sauce, or cold with a green salad.

title: donna's squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Place in baking dish and bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter with brown and white sugars; beat in eggs and vanilla.
Blend in sifted dry ingredients.
Chill dough.
Drop on cookie sheet (can be shaped into small balls and then slightly flattened). Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool before frosting.

title: mexican meat loaf
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cinnamon stew
directions: Cut up meat into cubes.
Brown the meat in the Crisco.
Add chopped up onion and carrots.
Add cinnamon, sugar, salt and pepper; simmer for about 2 minutes.
Add V-8 juice and potatoes. Simmer for 2 to 2 1/2 hours, until thickened.

title: quick shrimp creole
directions: About 20 minutes before serving in a 2-quart saucepan, heat oil until hot over medium heat.
Add pepper and onion.
Cook until tender (about 5 minutes); stir in spaghetti mix, tomatoes with liquid and water.
Cover; simmer 10 minutes.
Add shrimp; cook until shrimp turns pink (about 3 minutes).
Serve over rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: apricot bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients in to bowl.
Mix liquid ingredients and add to the first bowl all at once.
Stir until flour is moistened. Very quickly, stir in apricots and nuts.
Turn into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan and bake at 325° for about 1 1/4 hours.
Turn up the oven heat during the last few minutes if the loaf doesn't seem to be browning.
Remove from pan at once; cool on a rack.
Store overnight before slicing.

title: 4 layer pie
directions: Layer One:
Mix 1 stick oleo and the flour. Add the pecans. Spread in long baking dish. Bake until light brown.
Cool for 15 minutes.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Drain cherries.
Add enough water to liquid to make 2 cups liquid.
Heat to boiling.
Mash cream cheese.
Add dissolved Jell-O; let cool.
Add other ingredients and refrigerate in a 9 x 9-inch pan.

title: toni's buttermilk pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mom's date cookies
directions: Combine dates with sugar and water.
Cook over low heat until thick, stirring constantly, about 5 minutes.
Add nuts and mix. Cool.

title: magic cookie squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass dish).
In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, melt margarine in oven.
Sprinkle crumbs over margarine.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over crumbs.
Top evenly with remaining ingredients.
Press down firmly; bake 25 to 30 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool; chill thoroughly, if desired.
Cut into bars.

title: ice cream sandwich
directions: Take the cookies and turn them upside down.
Using a tablespoon, place the ice cream on the cookie and place another cookie on top.
Smooth the ice cream.
Place sprinkles on the smooth area of the ice cream sandwich.
Serve.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Drain salmon reserving 1/4 cup of liquid.
Remove skin and bones.
Mix with other ingredients and pack into lightly greased loaf pan.
Bake at 370° for 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and serve.

title: red slaw
directions: Combine cabbage and remaining ingredients in bowl; mix well. Chill for 1 hour or longer.
Serves 12.

title: round steak supreme
directions: Cut into pieces. Place in foil-lined ovenproof container.
Mix soups together in bowl. Pour over steak. Do not dilute soups. Cover with foil. Bake 3 1/2 hours in 300° oven. Stir once during baking to separate meat.

title: new england baked beans(the real thing)
directions: Soak dry beans overnight in water (2 cups of dry beans covered completely with water).
Rinse beans next morning.
Add water to cover.
Put ingredients into pan and parboil them together for 45 to 60 minutes.
(Beans are ready for baking when you can remove one with a spoon, blow on it and the skin shrinks back.)

title: gougere
directions: Stir the above ingredients thoroughly into the dough.
On the prepared baking sheet, arrange rounded tablespoonfuls of the choux in a complete circle; you may want to make 8-inch in diameter circle to guide you.
Make sure that each mound touches the next. When you have completed the circle, make a second layer by placing rounder teaspoonfuls on top and in between each of the larger mounds.

With a pastry brush, paint the top of the gougere with one egg, mixed with 2 tablespoons cream, taking care that the egg does not drip down the side and adhere to the baking sheet (this would inhibit the puffing).
Sprinkle the top with the reserved cheese.
Refrigerate at this point.

title: super bean casserole
directions: Drain all beans, except 1 can of pork and beans.
Empty all beans into a 2-quart casserole.
Mix remaining ingredients. Simmer for 10 minutes.
Stir again and pour over beans.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or at 300° for 4 hours.
Put bacon strips on top and bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes.

title: tin can ice cream
directions: Combine egg, milk, sugar and cream in a 1 pound coffee can, mixing well.
Stir in chocolate and seal with lid.
Place in ice and rock salt mixture in 3 pound coffee can; seal with lid.
Roll back and forth on ground for 15 minutes or until firm.
Makes 3 to 4 servings.
(May substitute mashed fruit for chocolate.)

title: chicken and ritz
directions: Boil the chicken; take off the bones.
Place uncooked rice in a 7 x 11-inch pan.
Use 1 cup broth from boiling the chicken over the rice.
Cover with a layer of chicken.
Mix the sour cream and soup together; pour over the top.
Sprinkle on crushed Ritz.
Pour melted margarine over the top.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes, or until bubbly.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
In a small bowl, mix pumpkin and milk. Add dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin mixture.
Add nuts and raisins.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground chuck, onion and mango.
Drain some of the fat off.
Save some fat to add to flour.
This will make a gravy in this recipe.
After adding flour to hamburger mixture and browning it, add your salt, garlic, carrots, peas, noodles and water. Simmer about 25 minutes on medium heat.
Stir often.

title: coney island sauce
directions: Cook all ingredients together for at least 20 minutes.
Add a little water, if needed.
Serve over hot dogs.
Garnish with chopped onion and shredded Cheddar cheese, if desired.

title: mountain-orange cake
directions: Mix all together and beat 2 to 3 minutes. Makes 3 layers.

title: spinach stew with beef
directions: In a large Dutch oven, combine water, beef, 1 cup onion and 1 teaspoon ginger root.
Bring to a brisk boil; lower heat, cover and simmer 1 hour.
While beef is simmering, wash spinach; chop and set aside.
In a large frypan, heat oil.
Add tomato, remaining onion, tomato paste and beef stock.
Cook 15 to 20 minutes over low heat.
Add beef; cover and simmer 15 minutes longer.
Add salt to taste, cayenne pepper, remaining ginger and spinach.
Cover and let simmer 10 minutes.
Serve with rice, yam or plantain.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: applesauce fruitcake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar. Add beaten eggs and applesauce. Mix in fruit, nuts, soda, water, salt, flour and spices. Bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour or until done. Makes 4 loaves.

title: peach jello
directions: Bring jello and pineapple and juice to a boil.
Cool, then add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Serves 6.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix 3 cups of milk with pudding until creamy.
Mix sour cream and Cool Whip
with
the pudding.
Layer cut up bananas, mixture and wafers.
Chill in refrigerator for 30 minutes.

title: barbecue sauce for 50 servings
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour over meat.
Follow cooking directions for meat.
For cooked sauce, delete 1 cup vinegar; use 2 tablespoons salt and 4 ounces sugar.
The remaining ingredients stay the same.
Add 1 teaspoon black pepper, 1 teaspoon chili powder, 1/4 cup Worcestershire sauce, 1 tablespoon hot pepper sauce.
Combine all ingredients.
Simmer 10 minutes.
Baste meat with sauce during cooking.

title: chinese fried rice
directions: Cut bacon into small pieces.
Cook bacon slowly in skillet until crisp, then pour off drippings.
Break eggs into pan and scramble.
Add rice and mix thoroughly; let heat well.
Mix in green onions, soy sauce, salt and pepper.
Continue to cook until entire mixture is well heated.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie with vegetables
directions: Saute onions in butter until transparent.
Add and cook gently until half tender the peas, carrots, zucchini, potatoes and parsley.
Stir in
the
flour
and the milk; cook and stir until thickened.	Taste
for
seasoning.	Remove from heat and add the chicken.

title: lucy's coleslaw
directions: Shred cabbage.
Add salt, oil and vinegar together and boil. Use layer of cabbage, onion and sweet pepper alternately.
Pour sugar over this mixture and let set for 30 minutes.
Pour boiling vinegar and oil over cabbage.
Refrigerate for at least 6 hours to marinate.
Stays crisp for a week.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 450°.

title: english scones
directions: Cut butter into dry ingredients.
Add eggs (keep 1 white for brushing top).
Add milk and currants.
Roll 1/2 inch thick.
Cut in triangles.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Brush with unbeaten egg white and sprinkle with sugar.
Bake 15 minutes at 450°.

title: sour cream cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add sour cream, egg yolks and vanilla; mix well.
Add combined dry ingredients alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, or until wooden pick inserted in center comes out clean. Cool 10 minutes; remove from pans.
Fill and frost with Chocolate Sour Cream Frosting.

title: sweet potato biscuit
directions: I used	can of sweet potatoes.	Good with pork chops or for breakfast.

title: canned zucchini
directions: Grind zucchini and onions in food processor and mix with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Next day drain and squeeze dry.
Mix all with drained zucchini.
Cook 15 minutes.
Pack in jars.

title: chicken and broccoli
directions: If fresh,
cook broccoli until tender.
Put broccoli in a buttered pan
or
Dutch oven.
Layer out chicken mix and add rest of
the
ingredients.
Top
with
cheese (or mix cheese). Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: microwave quick fudge
directions: Place sugar in an
x
x
2-inch micro-proof glass dish. Measure cocoa and add to confectioners sugar.
Mix well together using a wooden spoon.
Measure milk; add to sugar-cocoa mix. Blend all together using wooden spoon.
Place butter on top using whole
stick cut into squares.
Heat in microwave oven on Full power
2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir together with wooden
spoon until well mixed.
Measure vanilla and nuts and add to other mixture.
Place fudge in freezer 20 minutes or refrigerator
hour.
Cut
into
1-inch
squares. Store in airtight container. Makes 4 to 5 dozen pieces.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Cook and stir celery, carrot, onion and green pepper in margarine in large saucepan until celery is tender, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Heat just until hot.
Do not boil.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Cut up vegetables.
Pour in bowl with onion rings on bottom.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Boil shredded zucchini in salted water 5 to 8 minutes. Drain. Saut onions in small amount of oleo. Beat eggs. Add cheese and mayo, onions, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix with zucchini. Pour into buttered casserole. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine cubed apples, Crisco oil and vanilla.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt and cinnamon.

title: bar-b-que green beans
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: confetti bake
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a large bowl combine soup, cheese, mayonnaise and milk; mix well.
Fold in cauliflower, peas and carrots, pimento and mushrooms.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
In a small saucepan melt margarine; stir in bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle over casserole.
Bake uncovered 35 to 45 minutes.

title: fruited chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple; reserve 2 tablespoons juice.
Combine pineapple and next 6 ingredients.
Combine mayonnaise, concentrate juice, salt, pepper and reserved pineapple juice until smooth. Toss with chicken mixture.
Chill several hours or overnight.
Add almonds just before serving.
Yields 40 to 50 servings.

title: baked turkey
directions: Wash turkey and remove packets inside. Place in baking pan. Melt butter and pour on top. Apply liberal dose of hot sauce. Stuff apple into cavity in turkey. Cover with aluminum foil. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and then reduce to 200° and cook 2 more hours. Ready to eat!

title: breakfast pizza
directions: In skillet, cook sausage until brown; drain off excess fat. Separate crescent rolls into 8 triangles.
Place in an ungreased pizza pan (12-inches) with points to the center.
Press over bottom and up sides to form a crust.
Seal perforations.
Spoon sausage over crust.
Sprinkle with potatoes.
Top with Cheddar cheese.

title: broccoli turkey supreme
directions: In a large bowl, combine all the ingredients. Transfer to a greased 3-quart baking dish or use a 9 x 13 pan. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Uncover. Bake 15 to 20 minutes longer or until rice is tender. Yields 8 servings.

title: praline strips
directions: Put crackers in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put sugar and margarine in boiler; heat to boiling.
Cook on low 2 minutes.
Stir in pecans. Spoon on crackers.
Bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Cut in strips while warm.

title: hamburger quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and onion.
Pour off excess grease.
Beat eggs and milk and add to meat mixture; combine thoroughly.
Stir in cheese.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until slightly brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Heat soup, oil, vinegar, mustard, salt, pepper and tabasco sauce until hot.

title: sharon's slimming soup
directions: Spray frying pan with Pam.
Saute ground turkey, onion, pepper and celery until just done.
Place in a crock-pot.
Add V-8 juice and seasonings.
Simmer all day on low or 1/2 day on high or 20 minutes in a saucepan for 1 quickie meal.
This is a wonderful "fill-you-up-meal".
Eat as much as you like and not gain an ounce.

title: candied dills
directions: Drain pickles, cut into 1/4-inch slices.
Combine slices with vinegar, sugar and spices (tied in small piece of cheesecloth). Let stand at room temperature, stirring occasionally until sugar dissolves, about 4 hours.
Put half of pickles in jar, then spice bag and rest of pickles.
Refrigerate for 4 days before serving. Remove spice bag in 1 week, if desired.

title: xtra-e-z cheesecake
directions: Mix together milk, cream cheese, lemon and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill.
Serve.

title: honey grilled chicken
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large heavy-duty Ziploc plastic bag; add chicken and peppers.
Seal bag and shake bag until chicken and peppers are well coated.
Marinate
in refrigerator 3 hours, turning bag occasionally.

title: curried lamb meatballs
directions: Mix ground lamb, bread crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
Heat garlic in the oil in heavy skillet.
Add meatballs.
Brown and turn until meatballs are cooked through, about 15 minutes.

title: overnight tuna casserole
directions: Whisk soup and milk in a 2-quart micro-dish.
Stir in remaining ingredients, except reserved 1/4 cup cheese.
Cover and refrigerate at least 12 hours or overnight.

title: cucumber salad i
directions: In a bowl arrange the sliced cucumbers, salting them in layers. Cover with a saucer and weigh down with something heavy.
Let stand for several hours or until juices run out.
Pour off cucumber juice, which will take most of salt.
Combine all other ingredients and add to the cucumbers.
Mix and chill.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: blue cheese soup(serves 8)
directions: Place stew meat in a large pot, cover with water and bring to a boil.
Add basil and parsley.
Lower the heat and cook, covered, at a slow boil for 3 hours.
Cook the noodles separately.
Drain and add them to the beef broth.
Salt and add 1/2 teaspoon pepper. The Blue cheese goes in last, and cooks just long enough to melt completely.
Do not boil.

title: creamy vanilla cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese at high speed of an electric mixer until light and fluffy.
Gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each.
Stir in vanilla.
Pour over graham cracker crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Turn oven off and partially open oven door.
Leave cheesecake in oven for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and let cool on wire rack in a draft free place.
Cover and chill for 8 hours.
Yields 1 (10-inch) cake.

title: chocolate brownies
directions: Cream sugar and butter; add eggs.
Mix cocoa and water to form a smooth paste.
Add to creamed mixture.
Sift dry ingredients. Stir in.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Bake 30 minutes at 275°.

title: cranberry nibble bread
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and flour; beat in the first egg and orange peel.
Set aside.

title: decadent fat-free chocolate cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray a 9 x 9-inch pan with cooking spray.
In a large bowl, combine the flour, cocoa, cornstarch, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
In a medium bowl, beat together with a fork for 1 minute the sugar and water. Add the egg whites and water.
Blend ingredients and add to dry ingredients in the large bowl.
Mix until smooth.
Pour into pan and bake 35 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: fresh peach pie
directions: Bring sugar, salt and water to boil until thick and clear. Add jello; stir until jello is dissolved.
Pour over peach slices in baked pie crust.
When set, serve with whipped cream.

title: white chocolate party mix
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Melt chocolate; pour over dry ingredients and stir.
Spread onto cookie sheet to dry.
Store in covered container.

title: easy mexican pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown meat in large skillet coated with Pam.
Then put meat in Dutch oven.
Pour water and salsa over meat.
Cover and bake until very tender, about 2 - 3 ours.
If liquid boils away, add more water.

title: coconut chews
directions: Cream together shortening, butter and the 3/4 cup powdered sugar.
Blend in the 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press mixture in bottom of ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 350°.
While this is baking, mix together the eggs, brown sugar, 2 tablespoons flour, baking powder, salt, vanilla, nuts and coconut.
Spread this mixture over the hot baked layer.
Bake an additional 20 minutes. Make icing from the 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar, 2 tablespoons melted butter, orange juice and lemon rind and spread over mixture while still warm.
Cool and cut into bars.

title: methodist salad
directions: Drain pineapple; measure juice and add hot water to make 4 cups.
Pour over Jell-O and stir until dissolved.
Add sugar, vinegar and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Add pineapple, apples (cut fine) and celery.
Serve with salad dressing topping.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer ingredients in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cut and serve.
Makes 8 generous servings.

title: apple salad
directions: Core and chop apples into 1-inch pieces (do not peel apples). Mix apples and sour cream in large bowl.
Stir in walnuts and raisins.
Slice bananas into 1/4-inch pieces and gently stir into mixture.
Serve within an hour.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix sugar, pumpkin, shortening and orange peel. Stir in flour, baking powder, soda, cinnamon and salt. Stir in raisins and nuts. Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a 375° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Cool.
Spread on Light Brown Glaze.

title: hot chocolate
directions: Mix together all ingredients well.
When ready make hot chocolate, put 1/4 to 1/3 cup of mixture per cup of hot water.

title: pecan crescent cookies
directions: Cream butter until soft and smooth.
Add sugar and flavorings; blend until smooth.
Stir in flour gradually; finely stir in nuts. Mold into small, crescent shaped rolls, using about 1 teaspoon for each one.
Place on ungreased baking sheet; bake at 350° for about 20 minutes, or until bottom is lightly browned.
Allow to cool slightly, then roll in powdered sugar.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen cookies.

title: apple pecan pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Place apple slices in bottom.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients, reserving a few pecan pieces, and mix well.
