Bake at 425° for 10 minutes, then at 300° for 1 hour or until set.
Top pie with remaining pecan pieces.

title: monkey bread
directions: Use Bundt pan or loaf pan (or 13 x 9-inch pan).
Cut biscuits in halves.
Mix cinnamon and sugar.
Coat biscuits with cinnamon and sugar mixture; place in pan.
Mix melted oleo, vanilla and rest of sugar mixture; pour over biscuits.
Nuts can be placed in pan first, in the middle or at the end.
Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.
Watch carefully.

title: tomato pudding
directions: Cook in saucepan
on top of stove on low heat or simmer until bread
crumbs
and	tomatoes are free of lumps, stirring often. (Cover saucepan with lid.)	Take off stove and pour in greased baking dish.
Broil
in
oven
until bubbly and brown. Keep check so it won't burn.

title: maple walnut brittle
directions: Combine sugars, water and syrup in a large, heavy saucepan over medium heat. Stir to dissolve. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly. Continue cooking, without stirring, until candy thermometer registers 300° (a teaspoonful of syrup will separate into hard brittle threads when dropped in cold water).

title: peanut butter pie filling
directions: Cook over medium heat until thick.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Bake for 2 hours at 250°.

title: orange pineapple salad
directions: Mix Jell-O with 2 cups boiling water.
Add pineapple and cream cheese.
Let set until almost jelled.
Add marshmallows, cherries and nuts.
Refrigerate until set.

title: chicken rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spread rice evenly over bottom of pan (9 x 12-inches).
In small bowl, mix soups with water.
Pour over rice.
Arrange chicken over rice.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over top of chicken.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 2 1/2 hours.
Do not peek.

title: mice cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees. In a large bowl, cream butter, peanut butter, and brown sugar until fluffy. Add egg and vanilla; beat until smooth. Add flour to creamed mixture; stir until a soft dough forms. Shape dough into 1- inch balls. Pinch each ball to form a nose. Decorate each cookie using peanut halves for ears, small pieces of licorice for eyes, and a sugar crystal for nose. Use a toothpick to poke a hole in back of each cookie for tail. Transfer to an ungreased baking sheet. Bake 10 - 12 minutes or until bottoms are lightly browned. Transfer cookies to a wire rack. While cookies are warm, insert 2 inch long pieces of licorice into holes for tails. Cool completely. Store in an airtight container. Makes about 4
1/2 dozen mice.

title: joy's vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix above ingredients well (all except whole milk).
Finish filling ice cream freezer with whole milk.
Freeze as directed. Makes 4 quarts.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Mix the first four ingredients.
Cook for 15 minutes at 350°. Top with bread crumbs and cook for 5 more minutes.

title: cheese rolls
directions: Layer ingredients beginning with cheese, then spinach, tomatoes and cashews.
Roll up with cheese on outside.
Secure with toothpicks.
Chill before serving with deli platter or salad rolls. Add salad dressing, if desired.
Makes 12 rolls.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cut chicken into bite size pieces and boil until done.
Mix soup and sour cream.
Add chicken, onion and mushrooms.
Pour into casserole and mix poppy seed into the mixture.
Add crushed Ritz crackers to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: beet, pear and nut salad
directions: Drain beets and pears.
Cut pears in quarter pieces and beet slices into halves.
Mix salad dressing with pears and beets.

title: my favorite buttermilk pound cake(serves 12)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream sugar and Crisco; let it collect around the sides of the bowl.
Add eggs in center of bowl and beat at very high speed.
Add soda, salt and flavorings to buttermilk and stir.
Stir Crisco and sugar into eggs and beat until light and creamy.
Add 1/3 of flour and mix well.
Add 1/2 of milk; mix well.
Add remainder of milk; add remainder of flour and mix well. Bake in a well-greased and wax paper-lined tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes, or until done at 350°.

title: grandma's sour cream walnuts
directions: Butter a baking sheet, set aside.
Mix sugar and sour cream in a large heavy skillet.
Bring to a boil over moderately high heat, stirring frequently.
Add nuts and orange peel.
Cook about 5 minutes over moderate heat stirring constantly, until mixture registers 234° or to a soft ball stage (small amount dropped in cold water forms a soft ball).
Remove from heat, stir until syrup becomes creamy and loses gloss.
Turn out on prepared cookie sheet and separate walnuts with fork.
Cool.
When cold, store in an air tight container.
Makes 1 1/2 lb.

title: crock-pot barbecue
directions: Cook pork on low in crock-pot for 10 to 12 hours in vinegar, sugar and salt.
Take meat off bones and remove all fat possible. Cut into chunks or shred.
Mix with remaining ingredients.

title: chicken a la chardon
directions: Bone chicken breasts.
Beat egg with 1 teaspoon garlic powder and salt and pepper.
Mix bread crumbs with Parmesan cheese and 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder.
Dip chicken in egg, then roll in bread crumbs, then put in large shallow pan.
Melt butter with 1/2 teaspoon garlic powder and parsley.
Pour half butter sauce over chicken.
Cook 25 to 30 minutes.
Slice mushrooms; put over chicken with remaining butter.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes longer (375°).
Serves 6.

title: chocolate sin
directions: In bottom of large glass bowl, layer brownies.
Place ice cream over brownies and top ice cream with chocolate syrup.
Add a few chips and nuts.

Top with chocolate chip cookies and continue to layer in same order until all ingredients are used. Top with Cool Whip and garnish with remaining nuts and chips. This is a very rich desert and will serve approximately 20 people.

title: soft buttermilk biscuits
directions: Cut butter into flour until coarse crumbs.
Add buttermilk. Knead lightly for 10 seconds.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 425° for 13 to 15 minutes.
Reheat in microwave very well.

title: stovetop pie
directions: In a 10-inch oven-safe skillet, cook turkey, onion and chili powder over medium-high heat until turkey is cooked through and onion is tender, stirring to break up turkey.
Stir in half the soup, the water and pepper.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat to low; simmer 5 minutes.

title: turkey cordon bleu
directions: Cook and stir ham and turkey in hot margarine until lightly browned.
Stir into soup, water and mustard; add green beans and bring to boil.
Stir in rice, top with cheese, cover and remove from heat.
Let stand for 5 minutes.
Fluff with fork.

title: emerentz's grasshopper pie
directions: Melt marshmallows in milk; cool.
Add creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Whip cream and fold in.
Place in graham cracker pie crust.

title: tuna macaroni treat
directions: Prepare macaroni and cheese according to package directions. Decrease butter if desired.
Combine remaining ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.
Stir in macaroni and cheese.
Spoon lightly into a greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yields 6 or more servings.

title: mile hi pound cake
directions: Butter and eggs should be at room temperature.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time and alternate with flour. Then add vanilla.
Bake in well-greased tube pan 1 1/2 hours at 300°
or until done.

title: chicken salad
directions: Cook chicken, debone and chop up.
Mix with other ingredients.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Put spinach in casserole dish.
Put mushroom soup over spinach and crumbs over soup.
Bake about 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: low-fat beer bread
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients; make a well in center of mixture. Add beer and egg substitute, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened.

title: coconut cookies
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients together, then add flour, salt, soda and baking powder.
Mix well, then add nuts and crushed pineapple. Mix well and drop by 1/2 teaspoon on slightly greased baking sheet.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Cut marshmallows in half.
Place the halves on cookies as soon as they come out of oven.
Press down.
Cool, then ice.

title: jalapeno corn bread
directions: Combine corn meal, salt and soda.
Stir in corn, milk and oil. Add onion, peppers, cheese and eggs.
Mix well.
Turn into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° until set, about 1 hour. Let stand 10 minutes.
Cut in squares to serve.

title: doughnuts
directions: Cream fat, sugar and egg.
Add vanilla.
Stir in all remaining ingredients.
Roll dough to 1/4 inch thick.
Cut with doughnut cutter and deep fry until golden brown.
Drain and coat with powdered sugar.

title: best ever banana split cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed on box.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool.
Spread chocolate topping on cake, then top with bananas, pineapple and Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and add cherries.
Store in refrigerator.

title: microwave cobbler
directions: Mix fruit with sugar.
Cook on High power approximately 4 minutes (until mixture bubbles).
Put batter in deep, 2-quart, buttered microwave dish.
Pour fruit mixture over batter. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Dot with margarine.
Cook on High 8 minutes.
Batter will rise to top.

title: quick jambalaya
directions: Cut sausage links into 1-inch diagonal slices.
Place in skillet; brown as directed on package.
Add remaining ingredients except green pepper.
Heat to boiling, stirring occasionally. Reduce heat; simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes, stirring occasionally. Stir in green pepper; heat through.
Yields 6 servings.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add buttermilk, oil, eggs and corn.
Mix and beat well.
Stir in jalapenos, green pepper and onion.
Grease a 9 x 14-inch baking dish with bacon drippings or margarine.
Heat dish.
Pour in 1/2 of batter, sprinkle with 1/2 of cheese.
Pour in remaining batter and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 375° for 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: italian fried chicken strips
directions: Mix eggs and water together in bowl.
Completely blend.
Set aside.
In a bowl with lid or Ziploc Baggie, place 1 to 2 cups of Italian bread crumbs.
Add garlic powder.

title: chocolate cake - fat free
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients until well mixed.
In medium bowl, whisk egg whites, water and corn syrup.
Stir into dry ingredients until smooth.
Pour into prepared 9-inch square pan that has been sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched, in a 350° oven.

title: delightful salad
directions: Mix together and serve on lettuce.

title: chicken "old ladies on a bus"
directions: Mix first four ingredients.
Salt and pepper chicken pieces. Put into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour mixture over chicken and bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting occasionally.
Increase heat to 400° and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: In a two-quart saucepan, combine brown sugar, granulated sugar, flour and salt.
Add water, butter, corn syrup and vanilla. Cook, stirring occasionally, over medium heat until mixture boils.
Remove from heat.

title: one bowl chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients. Stir in oil, milk and eggs. Add water and stir well. Pour in greased 9 x 13 pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: scotchies
directions: Mix all ingredients in order as listed.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Cool and cut.

title: pineapple tea
directions: Combine tea and sugar.
Add boiling water; stir to dissolve. Add pineapple juice, water and lemon juice.
Chill tea.
Serve over ice.
Makes 17 cups.

title: cinnamon cucumber pickles
directions: Day One:
Peel and seed cucumbers, slice into 1/2 to 3/4 strips.
Cover with water and lime.
Let stand 24 hours.

title: canned corn
directions: Cut corn from cob; do not scrape cob.
Put into pint jars. Shake lightly, but do not pack.
Add enough cold water to cover corn, then 1/2 teaspoon fresh lemon juice to each jar.
Seal and cook in hot water bath for 3 hours.
After reaches boiling point, do not boil at high temperature.
If using quart jars, use 1 teaspoon lemon juice per can.

title: cold medicine
directions: Boil water, cinnamon and cloves.
Boil for 5 minutes; add lemon juice and whiskey and heat.
Add honey.

title: crab dip
directions: Combine all ingredients. Bake in small casserole dish at 425° for 20 minutes. Serve warm with toasted pita triangles or crackers.

title: lime and cheese salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and let set for 30 minutes before serving.

title: broccoli with cream cheese sauce
directions: Wash broccoli and cut into flowerettes.
Cook until crunchy tender, drain.
Put into 2 qt casserole dish.
Melt butter and saute onion until golden.
Blend in flour and boullion, cool for 1 minute.
Remove from heat and stir in milk.
Heat and cook until thickened, stirring often.
Stir in cream cheese and blend in yogurt and dill.
Pour over broccoli and heat through.

title: three bean salad
directions: Mix Crisco, vinegar, salt, pepper and sugar to make marina sauce.
Mix beans, peppers and onions in sauce and marinate for at least 8 hours.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add topping and bake 10 minutes more.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mash potato up.
Add salt, vanilla and powdered sugar until it works like dough.
On waxed paper, roll out.
Spread peanut butter on. Roll back up.
Wrap roll in waxed paper. Chill 30 minutes and slice.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Save ginger ale until ready to serve. Add fresh fruit, if desired.

title: meatless spaghetti
directions: In a large skillet fry bacon until well done.
Remove from pan and drain.
Add onion and green pepper.
Saute until tender. Drain.
Add tomatoes, bacon, garlic and seasonings.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Brown hamburger, drain and add diced onion.
Stir in pork and beans.
Add salt and pepper to taste and about 1/2 cup ketchup. Turn on low heat and simmer.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Drain all the fruit; dump into bowl.
Add pudding and Cool Whip.
Optional ingredients are just added.

title: lemon layer cake
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients.
Add buttermilk, Crisco and vanilla. Beat on low 1 minute, then on high 2 minutes more.
Pour into 2 greased and floured layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: california vegetable medley
directions: Prepare vegetables as directed on package, cooking in the chicken bouillon.
Add wine and seasonings.
In the meantime, cook pasta al dente and drain.
If the sauce in the vegetables is too thin, thicken with some cornstarch.
Mix vegetables together with pasta.
Serve with Parmesan cheese to taste.
Frozen broccoli can be substituted for mixed vegetables.
Serves 4.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Melt margarine and mix with onion. Add all other ingredients. Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish. Top with sharp cheese. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: dirt cake
directions: Grind oreo's and set aside.

title: salmon stuffed tomato salad
directions: Sprinkle lemon juice over apples.
Add peas, salt and mayonnaise; toss to mix.
Add salmon; toss gently.
Chill 1 hour. Peel tomatoes; chill until ready to serve.

title: ruby's cheese ball
directions: Cut dried beef into small pieces.
Mix softened cheese and dressing together.
Add dried beef.
Form into a ball.
Serve with crackers.

title: chocolate chip marble squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour oblong pan 13 x 9 x 2-inch.
Mix oleo and shortening, sugar and vanilla.
Beat in eggs.
Blend in flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix in nuts. Spread dough in pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top of dough. Place in oven 2 to 3 minutes to melt chips.
Remove from oven and run knife over chips and through dough to marbelize.
Return to oven; bake 18 to 20 minutes longer.
Place in refrigerator to cool.
Cut in squares.
Do not overbake.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add milk and cook until thick. Take off heat.
Add beaten egg yolks and butter.
Add pinch of salt.
Cook 1 minute longer.
Pour into pie shells.
Beat egg whites.
Add a little sugar and vanilla.
Spread over pies and brown in oven.

title: crab-shrimp casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients in large baking dish or casserole. Serve with corn muffins and salad for an easy buffet.
This is fairly hot and spicy.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and soda.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Combine egg, relish, orange juice, water and nuts.
Add all at once to dry ingredients.
Stir until just moistened.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool thoroughly.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream sugars and butter.
Add egg to peanut butter mixture. Add cream and sifted dry ingredients.
Form into balls the size of marble.
Place on a greased cookie sheet.
Press with a fork.
Bake about 8 minutes at 350°.
(If batter is dryer than desired, add more cream.)

title: crazy cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients together, then add rest of ingredients. Bake at 325° in 13 x 9 x 2-inch Pyrex for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: lemon snaps
directions: Cream sugar and butter. Add eggs; beat. Add syrup and extract. Add dry ingredients. Roll into small balls, dip into granulated sugar and place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350 about 15 minutes till golden brown. Remove at once.

title: chicken curry
directions: Add soup and curry powder to diced chicken in a saucepan.
Add milk slowly.
Should be saucelike.
Serve warm over cooked rice.

title: eclair dessert
directions: Blend milk and pudding.
Fold in whipped topping and combine until thick.
Butter a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
With whole graham crackers, put a layer of crackers.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix well and pour into 2 (8-inch) pans.
Cook at 350° until done.

title: chicken soup
directions: Combine chicken, salt, margarine and water in large kettle. Cook until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Cool and remove from bones.
Set aside.
Add potato and onion to broth. Cook until tender.
Add chicken and remaining ingredients to broth.
Simmer 30 to 40 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: danish orange cake
directions: Set aside first 2 ingredients for topping.
Sift dry ingredients and mix well.
Add shortening and milk.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add egg.
Beat 2 more minutes.
Fold in ground raisins, ground orange peel and nuts.
Bake in tube pan at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes or until tests done.
Pour brown sugar and orange juice (heated) over cake while still in pan.

title: pave au chocolate
directions: Melt chocolate; fold beaten yolks into melted chocolate and then fold in melted butter.
Whip egg whites until stiff; fold into mixture.
Pour into mold:
an 8-inch cake pan lined with paper. Chill overnight.
Serve with sweetened whipped cream.

title: orange sauce
directions: In a medium, micro-proof bowl, combine juices and water.
Add sugar and cornstarch, stirring to dissolve.
Stir in rind, lightly beaten egg and butter; microwave on High 5 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens.
Allow to cool and store in airtight container in refrigerator.
Serve warm or cold.
Yields about 1 2/3 cups of sauce.

title: chocolate marshmallow haystacks
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Mix well.
Gradually add sugar. Stir in chocolate, salt and vanilla.
Fold in marshmallows.
Drop rounded teaspoonfuls of mixture in coconut; toss until well covered.
Chill until firm.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: vira's potato rolls
directions: Measure sugar, Crisco and salt into large bowl.
Add 1 cup boiling water and 1 cup mashed potatoes.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water and add to cooled mixture.
Add beaten eggs. Gradually add about 7 cups flour.
Mix well until dough is not sticky.
Turn onto floured board and knead until dough is satiny and elastic, about 10 minutes.
Cover and let dough rise until double.
Punch down and refrigerate until needed.
Mold into rolls and let rise until double in bulk.
Bake at 375° until lightly brown.

title: glazed strawberry tarts(diabetic)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Wash and stem berries.
Add liquid sweetener.
Press 1 cup of the berries through a strainer. Add food coloring, if desired.
Add lemon juice; bring to a boil. Remove from heat.
Add softened gelatin, stirring until dissolved. Chill until mixture begins to thicken.
Arrange remaining 2 cups whole berries in tart shells, dividing them evenly.
Cover with glaze.

title: garlic oyster crackers
directions: Place all ingredients in a bag (large grocery bags work well) and shake in bag until well combined.
Place crackers in pan and warm in a 200° oven for 1/2 hour, stirring every 15 minutes or until a light golden brown.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Pour vegetable oil in skillet; heat on low heat.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge pork chops in flour until well coated on both sides.
Place in skillet and brown on both sides.
Remove pork chops and saute onions and bell pepper in drippings.
Remove skillet from heat.
Place pork chops in skillet.
Place onions and bell pepper over pork chops.
Mix nectar and remaining ingredients.
Pour over pork chops and place on stove.
Cover and simmer for about 1 hour or until chops are tender.

title: apple dapple cake
directions: Mix in order given. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: handy pastry
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, salt and sugar in a large bowl. Cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in egg, water and vinegar.
Divide into equal parts of 5. Shape in balls.
Wrap tight.
May store in refrigerator for 5 weeks.

title: toffee bars
directions: Line 2 cookie sheets with aluminum foil.
Place graham crackers on top of foil.
Mix the butter, margarine and sugar together; bring to a boil.
After it starts boiling, boil for 5 minutes.
Pour over crackers, then cover the crackers with chopped up pecans.
Bake in oven for 8 minutes at 400°.

title: old time vegetables
directions: Sprinkle sugar over rutabagas & potatoes in sauce pan. Dissolve cube in boiling water.
Pour over veggies.
Bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer till tender.
Drain and mash veggies.
Add pepper, onions, cheese.
Beat until fluffy.
Serves 6.

title: sundae bubble crown
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Heat water and 1/2 cup butter to rolling boil.
Stir in flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat about 1 minute or until mixture forms a ball.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs all at once.
Continue until smooth.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade ravioli
directions: You can also use pepperoni, mushrooms or any other filling you wish.

title: german potato salad
directions: Fry bacon until delicately brown (about 5 minutes); if very fat, drain, reserving at least 1/4 cup in skillet.
Add onion and saute about 3 minutes.
Add flour, sugar and seasonings and blend well.
Add vinegar and water gradually and cook until thickened (about 5 minutes), stirring constantly.
Pour beaten egg over hot potatoes, coating potatoes well.
Add hot vinegar mixture and toss gently with a fork.

title: pierogi casserole
directions: Add grated cheese to mashed potatoes and beat with mixer. Saute onions in margarine until soft.
Add 1/3 onion margarine mixture to potatoes and salt to taste.
Generously butter a 13x9 inch pan.
Place a layer of noodles in pan then a layer of potatoes mixture.
Repeat ending with noodles.
Pour remaining onion and butter mixture over casserole.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 degrees until heated through, about 45 minutes.

title: chutney grilled lamb chops
directions: Combine chutney, butter, lemon juice, curry powder and ginger and cook in saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally for 10 minutes.
Grill chops 4 to 5 inches from coals, about 20 to 30 minutes, basting frequently with sauce.

title: settler's beans
directions: Cook beef and drain.
Mix with all other ingredients.
Simmer like chili.

title: ham and swiss pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate. Sprinkle ham, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth. Pour on ham and cheese.
Bake until golden brown and knife comes out clean. Cool for 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: tortellini and sausage soup
directions: Cook and stir sausage and onion until sausage is light brown. Drain and stir in remaining ingredients.
Heat to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until vegetables and tortellini are tender. Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Simmer raisins until plump (20 to 30 minutes).
Add enough water to raisin liquid to make 1/2 cup.
Cream together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Stir in liquid. Sift together flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, and cloves. Add to creamed mixture.
Stir in oats, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: salmon loaf(low calorie, low sodium)
directions: Mix ingredients well and form into loaf shape.
Place in nonstick pan or spray with vegetable oil.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Pepper to taste.
Serves 4.

title: kraut balls
directions: Mix eggs and milk together.
Cook sausage and onion until brown.
Drain.
Mix well with kraut and 4 tablespoons cracker crumbs.
Set aside to cool.
Combine cream cheese, parsley, mustard, garlic and pepper.
Mix well and stir in sausage mixture. Chill.
Shape into 3/4-inch balls.
Roll balls into flour.
Dip in egg mixture.
Roll in cracker crumbs.
Deep fry until golden brown; drain.
Place in pan.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: anytime, anything pasta salad
directions: Cook any kind of pasta.
Pour bag of frozen mixed vegetables or fresh vegetables in the colander.
Drain pasta over veggies.
This thaws frozen variety or lightly blanches fresh veggies.
Rinse pasta and veggies with cold water.
Use hands or a spoon to mix while rinsing.
In a mixing or serving bowl, mix pasta, veggies, one can cooked chicken, turkey or shrimp.
If you prefer, add diced ham or leftover meat.
Add diced cheese if you like.

title: unusual chocolate cake
directions: Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan.
In bottom of pan layer coconut and pecans.
Prepare German chocolate cake mix according to directions.
Pour on top of coconut and pecans.
Melt margarine, combine with cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Drop in "blobs" on top of cake mixture.
Bake at 350° until white "blobs" turn brown or disappear.

title: pie dough
directions: Place flour and salt in large bowl.
Cut shortening and butter until mixture is coarse and mealy.
Sprinkle in ice water. Lightly knead until dough forms a ball.
Divide dough in half. Place in plastic bag and chill at least 1 hour or overnight.

title: 5 layer cookie
directions: Melt oleo in 9x9 pan; spread crumbs over bottom of pan, then coconut, next chocolate chips, next pecans, and pour cond. milk over all. DON'T MIX.
Bake at 350° for 30 min.
cut into bars.

title: party mix
directions: Slowly melt butter in pan.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce, garlic powder and salt.
Add Chex and nuts.
Mix until the pieces are coated.
Heat in a 250° oven for approximately 45 minutes.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Yields 6 3/4 cups.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Season pork chops with salt and pepper and brown on both sides.
Arrange potatoes in a baking dish.
Mix soup, milk and onions and pour over potatoes.
Place pork chops on top and sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: chicken a la king
directions: Saute mushrooms and onion in a small amount of butter.
Cook the peas; set aside.
Cook the carrots; set aside.
Melt 3 tablespoons butter; blend in flour.
Gradually add chicken broth. Cook and stir until thick.
Add the chicken, the vegetables and salt.
Heat to boiling.

title: black bean chili
directions: In small skillet toast cumin seed, oregano, paprika and cayenne over medium heat, stirring 2 to 3 minutes or until paprika turns dark.
Transfer to small bowl and add pasilla chili.
In large saucepan, heat 3 tablespoons oil and saute onion for 5 minutes.
Add spice mixture, chipotle chili, green pepper, garlic and tomatoes.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add dried black beans (soaked), water, bourbon and bay leaf.
Cook partially covered over low for 2 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add more water if necessary.
Stir in cilantro and salt.
Ladle chili into bowls and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and a dollop of sour cream.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Mix and microwave for 3 minutes on High.
Stir and turn 1/2 way.
Pour into buttered pan and refrigerate 1 hour.

title: pink salad
directions: Sprinkle jello and sugar over pineapple in saucepan. Bring to a boil. Simmer and stir 1/2 to 1 minute until jello is dissolved. Add cream cheese and stir until well mixed. May set overnight or in refrigerator until just set. Whip Dream Whip according to directions. Whip or beat well the set jello and mix with the Dream Whip. Whip all together. May use some cut up fresh strawberries with this to make more.

title: hamburger vegetable soup
directions: Note:
Can use 5 cans of mixed vegetables with the liquid in the pan.

title: cherry coke jello
directions: Dissolve Jello in hot juice, drained from pineapple and cherries.
Add coke.
When Jello starts to jell, stir in fruit and chill.
Serves 16.

title: ritz cracker pie
directions: Beat egg whites until almost stiff.
Add sugar gradually and beat well.
Fold in crumbs, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch pie plate.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes at 350°. Let cool completely.
Top with whipped cream.
Let chill at least 2 hours.
Keep refrigerated.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Cut shortening into flour, mixed with sugar and salt.
Beat egg with vinegar in 1-cup measure and add enough water to make a cup of liquid.
Add this to flour and mix well.
Refrigerate before using.
Keeps up to 8 weeks.

title: citrus salad
directions: In a large bowl, combine the fruit, sour cream, marshmallows and coconut.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and sliced onion until tender, drain.
Add cheese while squash is hot.
Add dressing mix, chicken soup and pimento.
Mix well.
Pour into baking dish and bake at 300° for 30 minutes.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Brown onion with hamburger. Add remaining ingredients. Mix and place into casserole dish. Bake at 350° approximately 30 minutes or until squash is done. Top with cheese while hot.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 oleo and saute onion and celery.
Add to other ingredients (chicken, rice, water chestnuts, pimento, sour cream and cream of chicken soup) and put in casserole or other baking dish.

title: zucchini soup
directions: Place all ingredients in large pot.
Simmer for 1 hour and then put through blender.
Good for freezing.

title: never fail pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and Karo.
Mix well. Add salt and vanilla.
Mix real good.
Pour over 1 cup chopped pecans in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 to 60 minutes at 350° or until firm.

title: grilled or broiled pot roast
directions: Place beef in shallow baking dish.
Saute garlic in oil until golden.
Blend in mustard, soy sauce, rosemary and vinegar.
Pour sauce over meat.
Cover and refrigerate 24 to 48 hours.
Turn occasionally.
Place roast on cold broiler grid about 4 to 5 inches from heat.

title: pecan pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry. Combine the eggs, sugar, salt, corn syrup and vanilla in a bowl and blend well.
Stir in pecans.
Pour into pastry.
Bake 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for another 35 minutes.
Serve with cream.

title: biscuits(plain and simple)
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder.
Add shortening and mix well.
Add milk and knead well (use your hands).
If a bit sticky, add a bit more flour.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Beat together the flour, sugar, cocoa, shortening and/or applesauce, soda, baking powder, vanilla and salt.
Add 1 cup cold water and 1 egg; mix well.
Add 1/2 cup cold water and 2 eggs; mix well.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, or until it tests done.

title: crab meat spread
directions: Rub mixing bowl with garlic.
Combine softened cream cheese and milk, mixing until well blended.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Spread on toast or crackers.

title: rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice.
Cook broccoli and onion in butter.
Melt cheese a little and mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: peanut butter mousse pie
directions: Put
1 cup whipping cream in a large saucepan. Stir in gelatin.
Allow to soften about 5 minutes.
Place over low heat and scald (do not boil).
Remove from heat. Add chips and stir to melt.
Mix in peanut butter and stir until smooth. Chill at least 15 minutes until lukewarm.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar. Continue beating until stiff peaks form.
Fold into vanilla mixture.
Return to icebox.
Beat remaining cup of whipping cream until stiff.
Fold into vanilla mixture.
Pour into prepared crust (graham cracker or chocolate). Chill until firm.

title: fresh fruit sauce
directions: Mix together corn syrup and fresh crushed strawberries, blueberries, peaches or sweet cherries.
Chill and serve over ice cream, pancakes, waffles, fritters, French toast, plain cake or pudding.
Makes 2 cups sauce.

title: hawaiian snowballs
directions: Mix together until blended.
Roll into 1/2-inch balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet at 350° for 12 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while cookies are still hot.

title: guacamole dip
directions: Puree avocados in food processor.
Add lemon juice to thin. Remove from processor.
Add chopped tomatoes, onion and mayonnaise. Serve with nachos or corn chips.

title: aunt agnes' blackberry brandy
directions: Combine all ingredients in large jar.
Invert daily until sugar dissolves (4 or 5 days).
Store in cool, dark place 2 months.
Strain and enjoy.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple and mandarin oranges.
(Hint:
Save pineapple juice and dip bananas in it to keep them from turning brown so quick.)
Mix all fruit together and peach pie filling and serve chilled.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: cranberry salad
directions: In food grinder, grind cranberries, apples and oranges.
Mix in red food coloring and sugar.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: zucchini sweet relish
directions: Grind zucchini.
Grind the onions and green peppers.
Mix zucchini, onions and peppers.
Add salt and let stand for 30 minutes, then drain well.
Add sugar, vinegar, turmeric, celery seed, mustard seed, black pepper and green food coloring.
Boil 3 to 5 minutes and pack in sterilized jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: pineapple treats
directions: Cream the cream cheese and fold in the Cool Whip.
Drain the pineapple and add to mixture.
Fill the ladyfingers and refrigerate.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix well and refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour cocktail meatballs
directions: Mix beef, oatmeal, egg and onion; shape into 1-inch balls. Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add meatballs and cook, shaking pan occasionally, until evenly browned.
Remove with slotted spoon to paper towels to drain.
Add green pepper to drippings in skillet.
Cook over medium heat 2 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Drain with meatballs.
Pour off all but 1 tablespoon fat from skillet.
Add remaining ingredients and stir over medium-low heat until sauce is smooth, transparent and thickened. Add meatballs and peppers; stir to coat with sauce and heat through.
Serve with toothpicks or on small plates.
Makes 10 servings, 4 meatballs each.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Scrape and slice carrots;
cook until tender in salted water and drain.
Saute until tender the minced onion and chopped celery in margarine.
Mix all ingredients together in baking dish and top with Ritz cracker crumbs and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: lime scallion chicken
directions: Slice scallions into thin rings (use most of scallion).
Cut breasts into about 8 to 10 pieces; coat with flour.
Heat oil and 1 tablespoon margarine in a large skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken; brown on each side until golden, about 4 minutes on each side.
Remove chicken to a serving tray and keep warm.
Add 1 tablespoon margarine and scallions to pan; cook for 2 minutes.
Add lime juice; cook 30 seconds.
Pour over chicken and serve.
Yield: 4 servings.

title: very berry fruit leather
directions: Puree berries, lemon juice and sugar in a blender; strain to remove seeds.
Prepare dehydrator tray with a light spray of nonstick cooking spray.
Pour berry puree into prepared tray to approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Spread puree with rubber spatula to evenly distribute.
Dehydrate at 135° for 4 to 5 hours or longer, until puree is leathery, pliable and no longer tacky to touch.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, cream the butter.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Combine sugar and flour; add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts; pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes, or until golden brown.
Cool about 1 hour; serve warm.

title: scallops edwardo
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Stir in bread crumbs.
Add garlic, paprika, Romano cheese and white wine to taste.
Mix to make a thick mixture.
Put scallops in a casserole or shallow baking pan with butter.
Spread bread crumb mixture on top of scallops.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until scallops are white and firm.

title: fresh blueberry cream pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients; beat 5 minutes at medium speed. Fold in blueberries.
Pour filling into pastry shell.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Combine remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Sprinkle over top of pie.
Bake 10 additional minutes. Chill before serving.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Combine soup and corn.
Pour Tater Tots on bottom of pan.
Add corn, soup and meat.
Then top with Cheddar cheese. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: 2 hour yeast rolls
directions: Heat milk/water to lukewarm.
Add sugar, oil and salt.
Then add dissolved yeast and beaten egg; stir well.
Add flour, one cup at a time; stir well.
Do not knead dough.
It will be sticky.
Let rise until double.
Turn onto bread board and mix a little flour until workable.
Do not knead.
Make into your favorite shape rolls.
Let rise and bake at 425° until golden brown.
Makes 24 plus rolls.

title: hawaiian pineapple banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine flour, sugar, baking soda, cinnamon and salt.
Stir in nuts.
Combine remaining ingredients in a separate bowl; mix well.
Pour wet mixture into dry mixture, stirring just until dry ingredients are moistened. Spoon batter into 2 greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pans.
Bake about 1 1/2 hours or until a wooden toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pans for 10 minutes.
Remove from pans and let cool on a wire rack.

title: authentic fox head inn pie
directions: Slightly beat the eggs and add the sugar, Karo, salt, butter and vanilla.
Pour into pie shell and bake 45 minutes at 325°. After 30 minutes, baked (or 15 minutes before finished), add the chocolate chips and over this, the nuts.
Return and bake the remaining 15 minutes.
Cut into small wedges with whipped cream on top.
(Add 1 to 2 tablespoons bourbon, do not let curdle, to fresh whipped cream.)

title: baked crabmeat spread
directions: Mix together first 6 ingredients, adding crabmeat last. Sprinkle with almonds and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve with thin sliced French bread or crackers.

title: mexican dip
directions: Place all ingredients in a 13 x 9-inch Pyrex baking dish. Microwave until cheese is bubbly, about 5 minutes.
Serve warm with corn chips for dipping.

title: lime soup
directions: Saute chicken in margarine until browned.
Add onion, celery and pepper.
Saute, stirring, until tender.
Add chicken broth, stewed tomatoes (broken up with spoon) and lime juice.
Heat through.
Add salsa and cook over low heat until hot.
Serve with garnish of cilantro sprig and lime slices.
Good with tortilla strips.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Cook beef, onion and celery in a large skillet until meat is brown.
Drain drippings.
Stir in soup, thyme and salt.
Spoon meat mixture into a greased 2-quart shallow casserole dish. Spread potatoes over meat mixture.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Remove from oven and sprinkle cheese over top.
Return to oven. Bake for 10 minutes more.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients in order, cutting in the shortening as you do for biscuits or pie crust dough. Stir in buttermilk, also the water and yeast mixture. Blend thoroughly. The dough is ready to be refrigerated in large bowl or made into biscuits.

title: no crust nutty apple pie
directions: Butter large pie plate.
Mound with sliced apples.
Combine cinnamon, nutmeg and 1 tablespoon sugar and sprinkle over apples. Melt butter.
In a bowl, mix 1 cup sugar, flour, nuts and salt. Beat eggs slightly and add to dry mixture.
Mix in melted butter and pour over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
